reviewText: The design is near perfect for listening without the hassle of continually trying to maintain in your ear... The qaulity of these ear phone are excellent.

These little ear buds are great.  The sound is really good and they are actually durable.  I go on a lot of business trips (flying) and so I like to bring along some of my own ear buds for better sound quality and to save myself 2 bucks.  These ear buds have been exactly what I was looking for: very inexpensive, great sound and have lasted for nearly a year now with no failures.

My son liked the colors, the sound, and the fit.  I bought them to go with his ipod otter box that had similar colors.  He was very happy with both.  He wanted Beats which were too expensive but seemed to like these just fine.
I'm a careless person and usually obliterate earbuds in less than a month. These however, lasted 6 months (pretty good i spent less than 9 dollars on it). I loved the sound and it was comfortable.

Fits in ears with a tight sealed comfortable fit. I can hear partial traffic noise while walking home. The right side went off after 3 months of use. So , I bought a pair of buds from another company to replace these.

Needed another set and came across this.... For the price, it was worth the try and I can honestly say that these aren't bad at all. Decent sound quality with a good balance of treble and bass.... As far as the noise reducing factor.... Well, for the price, it isn't bad at all either... But keep this in mind..... Do not compare these to Bose earplugs because you will probably hate these... But for 100 dollars Bose, you expect perfect sound and noise reduction. I actually used these while I was vacuuming, and they actually held the sound out pretty well... Again, for the money, it's worth the try for yourself.

While the cliché title of this review might imply this product is cliché, don't make that mistake!This set of headphones offers excellent sound blocking with the flexible earplugs, the cord is plenty long, and for the price, you simply cannot go wrong here.Especially if you are upgrading from the default iPod earphones, or a cheap equivalent, you will be quite impressed when you can, once again, catch all the subtle, quieter nuances of your favorite songs.
summary: The best bang for the buck!

reviewText: I can't believe I never reviewed these earphones! I first got this pair 3.5 years ago, but they had a slight defect and eventually resulted in the left earbud not working. When I contacted JLab Audio support, they were extremely friendly and immediately shipped me a new pair (which fixed the previous issue as I noted that they reinforced the structure). Since then, I have been using this pair frequently, either keeping it on my desk for use at any time or storing it in my backpack for when I go on trips.Pros:Durable!Decent sound quality (great for the price)Looks decentGreat customer serviceCons:Just the mishap with the first pair, but I haven't encountered any issues with my current one!

Good sound and actually does keep out some sound (its not like BOSE noise-reduction, but for the price, one does not expect that).  Not great for working out as the buds do come out of the ear, but they nonetheless fit very comfortably.

I have some good ear buds that are significantly more impressive than these. but I use these more so i don't tear up my good ones. They are decent for an ear that doesn't know the difference. I am a musician and work a sound board. I know
summary: good for someone that isn't an audiophile (good for the price)

reviewText: for a cheap pair of headphones i'm a big fan of these. i'd definitely recommend these to anyone looking for a comfortable pair of ear buds at a good price.

I'd rather use the earphones that came with my iPod than use these.  It takes some real maneuvering to get them to stay in the ears.  Once they're in and secure, the sound quality is average.  I listen to different types of music and didn't hear anything great about these ear buds.

I can only give one star because i wanted these ear buds just for the colors....... I'm a Pittsburgh Steeler fan and I never got to enjoy this product because Amazon could not deliver them to my place of business. which really sucked for i have recieved many items from Amazon. it does not make sense
With 3 dogs and  a 13 year-old human child, it can get pretty loud around here.These ear buds are comfortable, block outside noise and seem well made.

They sounded pretty good at the beginning but it wasn't long before that changed.  The sound quality started going fast, and the cheap construction showed up in the fact that they started to literally fall apart.  I wasn't abusing them or overworking them or anythiing and I believe they should have stood up better than they did.  I wouldn't waste my money on them.  There are better buds out there.
Took these on a plane trip to Washington DC. These work so well at reducing the outside noise that I couldn't even hear the planes engine. Excellent item for the money.

I bought this almost two years ago to use with my laptop computer.  I use it to watch movies online, youtube videos, etc. and it's worked great.  The sound quality works for my uses and I have had no problems with the unit.  I have a small 2" round case that I use to store the buds in a coil so it doesn't get tangled or mangled.  I'd purchase it again if I ever have the need for another earbud.
summary: Two years and still working great!

reviewText: I was looking for a replacement of my Sony ear buds. I ran into good reviews of JBuds and decided to give it a try. It was very disappointed to find out that JBuds didn't have bass at all, it was like listening to the phone. High frequency were fine, the buds fit into ears OK. I tried to lie on the pillow with ear buds in, but it was not comfortable. If you like to listen to music, stick to Sony, for about the same money their buds are much better.
summary: I was deceived by good reviews

reviewText: Very ergonomic and fits well in the ear. The low and high sounds are great. I would recommend this for anyone looking for a cheaper alternative.

These earbuds are simply made for comfort. If you listen to audio for a long period of time using earbuds, then you know how uncomfortable regular ones feel after just 30 mins, or even less sometimes. That's not an issue with these though.They fit well into the ear, sometimes you have to push it in a bit to fit, but even so, They're still very comfortable.They sound good, not the same as some of the more expensive, or well-known brands, but still, they're better than the stock earbuds you get with MP3 players for sure.The cord length is good enough for MP3 player use, but not for computer use.They come with replacements for the soft parts on them.Finally, they're very cheap for the comfort they provide. Considering the regular earbuds hurt my ear so much, and so quickly, i'm loving these.
summary: Very comfortable, noice reducing, good sound, and cheap.

reviewText: These earbuds have very poor bass and poor sensitivity.  Overall tone is flat and tinny, and these earbuds have to be played at high volume levels.  If you want cheap, go to Big Lots and pay $2.  If you want decent tone at a reasonable price, buy Sony MDR-EX36 series earbuds.  Don't bother buying these.

These are the greatest ear buds!  I first bought them because I was looking for something comfortable to replace the horribly uncomfortable ear buds that seem to come with all MP3 players, such as the Sandisk Sansa which I bought.  (You'd think by now the MP3 manufactureres would get it).  Well, from the moment I first put them in my ears, I knew they were great.  I've now used them all around, including some major traveling, hiking, etc, and they've held up great.  They SOUND great, they FEEL great, and they come at a great price!
These are very nice, comfortable earbuds, and the sound is good too.  I would order them again in a heartbeat.

These do just what was stated fit really nice, have different ear sets to tailor to your ears,and sound really good. Really love these myself. You could pay more, but for the price, these really do a super job!

I myself don't know what the hype is all about. I have purchased several pairs of ear buds from Amazon; to date the only buds that are rocking, and continue to do their thing are the Skull Candy in ear 003 ink'd 2.0. They have the greatest high end, mid range, and low end that you would expect from a better quality in ear. And they were only $15.00 from Amazon. I should have known from the first pair of JLabs that I bought that these shouldn't be that much greater. For my money Skull Candy is by far a better bargin. I own 15 different pairs of in ears, including my Klipsch which there is no comparison to. I buy these off the wall brands as an extra pair for emergency purpose. I guess I will stick to Skull Candy after this experience. The only way you can determine the difference is to actually try them on and compare. See for your self. My go to for listening to my own recordings or any sound that I want the complete experience with are my Klipsch hands down. My kick around pair for just enjoying music for the best quality of it, will by no doubt be my Skull Candy. Enough said. After having throngs of amplified music in my ears from amp cabinets and front stage monitors for years on end, I know the difference in sound quality. Jlabs Needs to focus on frequencies that produce any given high, mid and bass response, for the listening pleasures of their customers. I'm just saying..........Aja
Good price! Good Sound! and Good Quality!, I have played with my cell and my computer in both has worked so good, I use too in Meeting and the voice sound so good as well.
I use them every day. They offer a great quality and very useful for your office, cycling, jogging or gym
I'm not an audiophile, but I know the difference between crappy and decent earphones.These are pretty good, I don't think you can find better at this price.
The sound quality is decent and the ear fit is fine, but I hate that it echos every other call.  Have requested a return.
for the price is ok .. i pick this one for replace my old J3 Mic.. the sound is ok , no like my old J3 but... the price ... say's everthing... is nice .. !!

I bought a couple of pairs of these as backup ear buds for the office etc. Fit is decent, not great, but the speaker quality is a little below par in my mind. My previous pair of Sony ear buds were only a few dollars more expensive and the fit and sound quality were superior to these.
summary: Nice price, but the sound quality is rough at best.

reviewText: I actually prefer the ear buds that came with my mp3 player better. I'm not sure what the problem is but they just ain't right!
Price was good, colors are great, got what I wanted and Daughter is very happy with them. Thanks again ,

Very flat sound [Think alarm clock radio sound]. No low end at all. Songs like Nelly Furtado's "Say It Right" which has a lot of bass, just sounds distorted and weak. I probably wouldn't buy them again.

I bought these because of the cheap price and some of the more positive reviews.The main complaint I have is they aren't very comfortable at all. They constantly slide out of my ears so I spend a good amount of time readjusting and trying to sit still so they don't wiggle out. This is my first pair of every day in-ear speakers so perhaps I don't have the proper technique for inserting them?It's good for stationary music listening but that's it.
summary: My first in-ear...Good but not great

reviewText: Everything sounds like your in a tunnel, not very clear at all. Would not recommend. Panasonic makes a great headphone set for around this price, they are so much better! Panasonic RPHJE120K In-Ear Headphone

Don't expect these to beat the $100 headphones, but they are better than the other headphones within the similar price range. The sound quality is better than average and the quality is pretty good. They don't fit snug so it is not great for running. Beware that these are not noise-canceling at all. The reduce noise of course but just like any other in-ear buds.I would recommend these headphones overall for anyone on a budget.

reviewText: The headphones are decent. I used to listen to music and the quality is music acceptable. These are headphones that you buy when don't want to spend more than $30 for headphones.However, if you willing to spend a bit more, the Sennheiser Earbuds below is also good value for moneyhttp://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001EZYMF4/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp;=1789&creative;=390957&creativeASIN;=B001EZYMF4&linkCode;=as2&tag;=travguid0ca-20

The noise cancellation quality is great on these headphones, but the sound quality is not very good at all. It doesn't sound much better than a super cheap brand. The sound is hollow and flat. For the price and review levels I would have expected better quality sound.
summary: Noise cancellation is good, sound quality is subpar

reviewText: Compared with all the brand named like Sony , JVC, this has the best sound quality. I meant the price is under $40.- range group.
summary: Sound Quality is very nice, better than most of the branded name

reviewText: bought a few weeks ago sound pretty good at about the price i wanted to pay.I not a expert on sound but they sound better than the ear buds that came with my mp3 player.I use them when I work out so far so good.
Great ear buds. Hey they're JBuds! Great music reproduction and good at noise cancelling. All you hear is your music!

How can you beat this deal. for likr 5 or 6 bucks get some great headphones. So what if you end up loosing them. The ear bud pieces feel great too. No discomfort. Well worth it if you are like me a misplace earbuds all the time.

I have used these for several years while traveling. A frequent flier, I like to listen to audiobooks to pass the time. For a while I used a pair of those battery-powered noise canceling headphones, but they became uncomfortable after an hour or so, and they are a nuisance to schlep around. After I got these earbuds I never looked back. While the noise reduction is no match for active noise cancellation, it is quite adequate and I can wear the earbuds much longer before they become uncomfortable.

I normally use Motorola Rokr Bluetooth headphones, but the battery only lasts a few hours, so I had a pair of Bose earbuds to use while recharging. The insulation on the Bose earbuds started to crack after several years of use and would zap me in the face once in a while, so I bought these JLab JBuds based on their very low price and okay amazon reviews. I'm neither impressed nor upset by the JBuds. While these earbuds don't hiss or pop like some cheap headphones, they also lack richness, and the bass response is simply not there. The sound quality is not nearly as good as the Motorola or the Bose, which I would rate upper but not high-end. The medium-sized gels fit my medium-sized ears well. The build quality seems good, especially for the price.
summary: Worth your money to get one pair but not a second pair

reviewText: Pretty good headphones. These were a pretty good price and they came in a variety of colors and work well.

The first set I ordered was missing some of the silicone tips so I did an Amazon refund (awesome service as usual). The second set had a wire coming out near the end of the plug so instead of using Amazon (which is great), I decided to test drive JLABs warranty claims process that everyone is talking about. They were fantastic and the new headsets were delivered fast.The overall sound quality of this particular model is less than impressive to say the least. I would not recommend these for any type of music. The lack of quality and low price point would better suit someone that listens to talk radio or learning a language on a tablet. At best get them for the kid that looses headsets all the time. But if you care about your sound, JLABS offers much better quality headsets and earbuds that still rivals the expensive competition. So take the time to research their entire product line and you should find the quality you want yet still remain very reasonably priced.
these are great earbuds! i love the noise reduction and i was pleasantly surprised when i realized i can take phone calls with them in! Awesome!
These ear buds with their foam cushions are very comfortable.  The biggest ones are too big for my ears, but I have saved them in case the smaller ones wear out.
The title says it all.  For "light" use substitute 1x week.  IMHO, unacceptable.
summary: 15 months of light use -- one earbud is dead

reviewText: Very good at this price. More comfortable than many  expensive ear buds I've used and not unpleasant to listen to. I bought a second pair.

JLab JBuds Hi-Fi Noise-Reducing Ear Buds  are a great product more so for the money. The come with various attachments to fit any ear. The sound is deep and rich with the high fidelity you’d expect in a more expensive set of buds. The cord will tangle but all will unless you get the flat cord.Great buy.

because it's base on bose 100 dolllars headphone.the sound is good, good feeling to the ears, and last very long.one promble, my opinion is I hate the wires becase it the two wires connet to each others like this II instead of this I. too heavy for headphone but it cheap. Go and buy one!

I am not particularly nice to earbuds, and have an amateur but demanding standard for sound quality. Here is what I found:* Whether speakers or headsets, I always start with Billy Thorpe's Children of the Sun, an amazingly complex and challenging piece. Passed with flying colours.* For bass (voice), I tested with Crash Test Dummies, Josh Turner and Johnny Cash. Beautiful lower register, rich and lush.* For treble (instruments), I used Nickel Creek and Chris Stills. Crisp. Brilliant highs with impeccable note distinction.* For wide-ranging vocals, I used Sweet Honey in the Rock and the majestic Pavane Op 50 (Paper Music by Bobby Ferrin). Amazing. Every voice is distinct and rich.* For precision, I use Beggerman (Gaelic Storm), Heard it on the X (ZZ Top), Radar Love (Golden Earring) and Yo Yo Ma's Appalachian Journey. Just blew it out of the park. I could hear Ma's fingers slide along the cello and Dusty's finger slip across frets.Now for some misses:* Werewolves of London (Warren Zevon) lacked the depth I get from even Altec speakers.* Friends of the Devil (Grateful Dead) lost the precision I expect from the vocals; the instrumental opening is perfection, but I guess Jerry's voice just doesn't fit into the spectrum these are designed to portray.* Volume is WEAK. If you like obliterating your eardrums, skip these earbuds. They top out at "old guy" (me) loud.Overall, I consider these and excellent purchase. They fit nicely, stay in place and deliver amazing sound for the obscenely low price.
summary: Worth FAR more than the price

reviewText: I got these as a back-up set for my Sansa Clip Plus mp3 player.  The buds that came with the player actually sound noticeably better than these JBuds do, but they do block out more noise.  I'll use them when I expect to be somewhere noisy.  For less then $10 I'm still happy with the purchase, and am glad to have something in case my other ear buds get damaged or lost. Shipping was really speedy, and this is a good deal for the price.

*Update 09/03/13Initially, I thought these were a nice alternative to the white Samsung Galaxy S3 headphones as they were definitely a lot louder and the bass was stronger.  But unfortunately, the build quality is cheap and the left earphone's volume ended up being significantly lower than the right earphone.  I'll use these as a back up from now on.  I do not recommend purchasing these headphones.
summary: These sound good at first, but they suffer from quality issues

reviewText: These are amazing. Forget the price tag (which itself is a bargain), these ear buds sound really good. I did a side-by-side comparisons with Apple (in-box), Creative (in-box), Phillips noise reduction and Sennheiser PXC 250 noise reduction and I could not believe that JBuds sounded better! The ambient noise blocking is pretty good too. However, I am not sure how well it will work in a plane. The in-ear fit is pretty comfortable. Although no audiophile, I am pretty fussy about my sound quality. JBuds definitely made me happy.

These inexpensive earbuds definitely won't win any awards for sound quality, as they lack the clarity and brilliance of (say) the Sennheiser CX300-B.  Also note that these are not "noise canceling" earbuds, but "sound isolating"; like the Sennheisers (and the Shure series) they use a soft rubber earpiece to block out (but not eliminate) ambient noise.  For whatever reason, however, the JBuds' earpieces do not seem to be as effective as those of the Sennheisers or the Shures.  For this product, at least, "you get what you pay for."
summary: mediocre sound quality, ineffective noise reduction

reviewText: The sound is excellent specially the bass. But it doesn't make miracle. With ipod nano 3rd gen you feel the bass inside your head. With ipod nano 2nd gen the sound is acceptable. The problem is the source. The ear bud is wonderful. And the price is the best part. You don't need to buy the others that cost much more.
I used them in the gym and found they worked well in cutting out the noise of others.  They were sent to me within two days.
I am so sad to say i never received these earphones. I am still waiting for them.I wanted these for my little girl to use in her tape player. Please send them to me. thank you.

I bought these for my ipod nano when mine got stolen. They are much more comfortable and the sound quality is good. I would recommend them. They come with three different pad sizes so they're comfortable for anyone.

These are great!  I ordered a pair just to see if (and how) they would work!  They are wonderful.  They don't fall out when you walk/jog/run and the neoprene adapter comes with small, medium, large to adjust to you ear!  I lost my trial pair to my husband, so I bought 2 more pair, now my boys fight over who gets the extra.  I may have to invest in another pair or 2!  They muffle the surrounding noise so you can concentrate on the music or video or what ever you are listening to.  They are great for studying, you can't hear kids fighting in the backgound!  I would purchase these over skullcandy, they are 1/3 of the price!  I definatley recommend these!

I didn't think it was possible, but I've found a pair of earbuds that are even worse than the ones that come with an iPhone. It's hard to describe sound quality, but I'd call these things "muffled." It sounds like you're standing outside your teenage kid's bedroom door while he listens to loud music. Furthermore, every time I touch the cord or rotate the jack when it's plugged in I get static. Lastly, These things come packaged in a very cheap foil pack that would make them totally unsuitable to give as a gift. I'd return these but since I paid about $5 it's not worth the hassle.
summary: Poor Sound, Poor Plug Construction, and Cheap Packaging

reviewText: OK.  First of all, I am not expecting high end performance from an $8 pair of earbuds.These ear buds sound tinny.  They have no base, and only passable midrange.  I was very disappointed.

JBuds Hi-Fi Noise-Reducing Ear Buds (Black)I JUST RECIEVED THESE IN THE MAIL AND TO SAY THE LEAST I AM VERY DISAPOINTED. THE BASS IS NON-EXSISTANT AND THERE IS ALOT OF DISTORTION NOT HAPPY. this was my first reaction to these now after a few months they sound awesome. give them about a week our so to break in.
These ear buds look really good and look like a really great deal, but don't be fooled, they're a good price for a reason! The sound quality is kinda poor.

The audio quality is par. It noise reduces by sticking the buds into your ears and cranking the volume. It's not flexible at the input joint. The headphones broke on me in under 6 months of regular usage. I do not recommend.I am sporting Sennheisers PX 100s after that purchase. I'm satisfied. Please look at those.
summary: It Works. But not a set of buds for keeps.

reviewText: These earphones provide decent sound and clarity at a reasonable price. Visually, they aren't aesthetically pretty or look worthy enough of a $10 price tag, which I had paid for. Overall, these earphones are fantastic as a spare and it's good for someone who are on a budget, like I am.
for the price of these headphones, they create excellent sound! i really like using them with my iPad because they cancel out any other noise. great!
Would repurchase. Just as described. Great two toned colors. Fits great. Soft and long wires. I have no "cons" for this product. Great price.

I own a pair of real noise-reduction headphones and these obviously don't compare to those, but for $6 these do muffle some of the noise (I believe the noise reduction comes simply from the design of the rubber; its' more snug in your ear.)  The sound quality is pretty good and they are comfortable, which says a lot because I have small ears and I hate the little phones that come with apple products - they hurt my ears.  If you are using those, do yourself a favor and pick up a couple pairs of these instead.  My fiance just ordered some and he likes them as well.
summary: Work well and I definitely notice the noise-reduction

reviewText: Imagine pushing your finger into your ear, the further you go the more pressure build up, and when you pull it out fast it has the equal opposite effect.  Either way, it hurts!  I know that earbuds are supposed to create a pressure seal, but there is no amount of pressure relief as to balance the inside ear pressure with the outside air.  Also, these things are treble heavy.  Painfully shrill.Look to either JVC, Sony, or Philips when it comes to headphones in this price range.  They are much better.
summary: Overly pressured seal hurts your ears

reviewText: I bought a pair of these in Sept. 0f '07 because Apple headphones suck and hurt my ears.  I enjoyed these for the first few months, the sound quality was much better than my old ones and they were comfortable to wear for long periods of time. Then after about four months, the left ear stopped working unless I turned the cord a specific way and didn't move it at all, which was a pain.  A few weeks later, the left ear stopped working altogether so I e-mailed the company for a replacement (they come with a 1 yr. warranty).  Two months after I got the replacement, the left ear also died completely on that one. My FOURTH pair in under a year also just died and, despite the warranty being valid for a few more months, the company refuses to replace them anymore. These aren't worth the $20 they charge and there are others that are half the price with similar sound that last much longer. Don't waste your money or your time.

Horrible... I did try this Jlab ear buds... It worked for 3 months, after that the mic stop working, and a month after that... The earphone stopped working too... This Jlabs should've been called TEMPORALLY Earbuds with the expiration date on it...
summary: TEMPORALLY Earbuds with the expiration date: 3 months or less

reviewText: Great sound, superior to any other earbuds i have ever bought. They have lasted over 4 months for me (AND STILL WORK FINE), which is great considering most more expensive earbuds last only 3 for me. They fit well. The only thing a little dissapointing is that they do not cancel noise very well even though they are supposed to.

well i  have purchased these in june. i take these with me into the bed..and believe me..these buds have been toppled over my body..and tangled and dropped..and they're STILL PERFECT ^_^ I'm HAPPY ;] but they can be long at times...when im sitting to give plasma..but i just wrap it over and over till it's short :/ but it's a Frecking hot deal with such a cheap price ;] this company is cool cuz they talk at my level..self explantory ;]

I purchased these trying to replace my old Altec Lansing MZX206 MUZX Headphones with Mic and call function (Old Version).With so many reviews I felt that I could give them a try.The pros are that these are cheap, they seem like they will last, they fit nice to the ear and the mic works with my iPhone 5s.The cons (actually the only one but is a deal breaker) is that the sound coming out is horrible.My music sounds "dull". It makes you feel like you need to adjust the equalizer and increase everything.Unfortunately the lower cost comes with a lower quality.

I purchased the Jbuds after reading reviews online at Amazon and seeing the price below $20.  I figured for that price how could I go wrong... right?  Well Right!  They are not noice reducing but a nice pair of headphones. They are not an audiophiles dream but they are as close as you are ever going to get for $20.  I say worth the price and they arrive very quickly.  Great job!
Not sure why there is a hype around JBuds. This is a simple cheap and yet good product to buy.
These buds fit my ears comfortably, deliver excellent sound, and hold up quite well.  In using them over a period of some ten months, I have had zero problems. Well worth the money.

these ear buds are just as good as it gets for the price. I use these for running, and have always had problems with expensive ones breaking after a few months, due to sweat. I paid, I think, $5.99 for these, and they are a great value for the price. Good sound quality and they fit nicely into my ear holes (which are rather quite small).
summary: good headphones for such a cheap price

reviewText: I bought these to replace my year old jbuds as the stereo stopped working on them. I have a pair of [[ASIN:B001RB24TG Sony MDR-XB20EX 9mm High Sensitivity Driver Extra Bass EX Earbuds]  and the sound quality is a little better, but because of the long piece coming down from the bud, they are not very stable when walking/jogging. I use them with my Android tablet (and they were free with Sony rewards points). The jbuds are very comfortable in my hard-to-please ears, and they stay put. The sound is better than average. The only reason these got 4 stars instead of 5 is because they changed the plug from 90 degree angle to straight. The right-angle plug fit into my pocket better.

I bought these for using w/my laptop in the office.  It comes w/3 sizes of rubber tips to ensure a good fit.  I usually have a problem with earbuds falling out of my ears.  These stay in and are very comfortable.  Sound quality suits my needs and the price at $13.50 can't be beat!

Are these headphones the best quality there is? No- but for the low price these headphones are pretty good (and they have a mic too which is a bonus!). I use earbuds all the time and lose them as they often fall out of my purse/ gym bag, so I like to have good quality, cheap headphones on hand. These will do the trick!
summary: Good headphones for a good price

reviewText: Very good product at a bargain price. I bought my first pair a little more than a year ago.  My cat got hold of them.  She bit the buds! Had to get another pair with the travel case.  There may be better on the market but for quality/price comparison, these are great! They cut back a lot of noise and are very good on sound quality.  Skullcandy is no match for these guys.

The sound quality is abysmal. It's grainy and unclear, do yourself a favor and buy the Skullcandy Ink'd headphones for the same price. I have them, and the sound quality is at least twice as good. And they're more comfortable.

These are not only very comfortable ear buds, they are the only ones I've found that actually stay in my ear.  That said, I returned them.  The sound is extremely colored, treble is missing, midrange ok but lacking indetail, bass is very present but boomey and "one-notey" like a cheap subwoofer.The sound has two strengths that should not be diminished, because there may be people for whom these strengths out-weigh the faults:1.  Very easy to listen to.  Not harsh at all.  A LOT of cheap electronics are harsh sounding.  These are not.2.  I suspect that these would be tremendous fun to listen to with RAP music.  I don't know because rap is not on my ipod, but, I suspect these were designed for rap music.  Just a hunch.Anyway, the seller requires the buyer pay return shipping and a 15% restock fee, so there is a penalty for trying these out to see if you like them, but it's not a huge penalty.Feel free to try them, especially if you like bass-heavy music (boom boom) and are willing to experiment.
summary: Very comfortable but sound quality is, um, unusual

reviewText: I looked at lots of different earbuds online at various prices, and, after reading the reviews of this model, decided to order them. I've used them almost daily for about a month, and I think they are excellent. I'm not sure what a set four times the cost would sound like because I can't imagine any earbuds being that much better than the JBuds. I bought them to replace the iPod buds that came with my Nano. Those have to be the worst earbuds ever invented. The JBuds are much more comfortable, fit MUCH better, cut out much more noise, and sound better than the ones that came with my Nano.

I have been using the non-mic version of these for a year, and they have held up well. I was getting tired of re-charging by bluetooth headset so I figured I'd try this one with the mic... it works great! It shipped directly from the factory in the midwest, which took a few more days than the non-mic version would have taken... no big deal. It came in a sealed plastic tear-open bag with two other ear-bud options aside from the big ones shown here; a small one, which I much prefer since they stay in my ears very well, and and oblong pair, which I didn't even bother to try. When I plug them in, they are immediately recognized by the 4.x Android OS of my phone as both a headset and mic... all good! Volume is good, quality of mic sound is good as per my GF, and very little problem with wind noise, which was a BIG problem with my bluetooth headsets...winner!For the price, I don't see how you can beat the JBuds with the Mic for smart-phone use. Sometimes simple and cheap is better... in this case, it is true!
summary: Earbud with Mic version: works great on my Android phone!

reviewText: These are perfect. I love the different size ear pieces, now they stay put and I can even exercise and they will not fall out. And for as small as they are, they deliver big, solid sound!!!

I got a pair of these for Xmas a few years ago and love them. The original iPod earbuds do not mesh well with my ears. I liked that  can choose the insert size with the gel thingies. Had to get these to go with my dad's new nano so he'd have comfy earbuds, too.

These headphones are really comfortable! They do reduce noise to a limit but don't cancel it. The sound is decent, nothing like my Bose but good enough for the price. I highly recommend it. Good sound and great comfort!

The packaging is literally a ziploc bag with a paper inset and some extra rubber part replacements. This lack of packaging may be how they keep the prices down. The earbuds are average to look at, average to use. Mine came in a pearly-pink color, "L" and "R" are marked. As long as inexpensive and average is what you want, these are a solid choice. If you want fancy-schmancy, keep shopping.
They broke the second day. But hey, they're the price that they are for a reason. Get the MDR-J10 headset from Sony, you won't be disappointed.

I'm not an audiophile by any means -- I just wanted some nice fitting earphones with some noise cancelling ability since I listen mostly to Podcasts on the train on the way to/from work.  These buds fit the bill as they fit snugly in my ear compared to the more standard headphones that came with my iPod that would always fall out.  More importantly, they sound much better and block out the train and other traffic noise much better than my original headphones as well.  For the price this was a great pick up for me.

These are comfortable and for me they sound great. But then I am not a audiophile like others out there. I like them, they sound good to me, which is what I wanted. I know you can spend $100's of dollars more, but I am not the kind of person that would tell the difference. Only problem is the cats like to play with and then hide the ear buds from me. So I have to hide them in a plastic box. But this is not a problem with the ear buds.
Not much to say except I would buy these again, great sound and they go with me where ever I go small enough to fit in my back pack or purse.

These are very good, inexpensive pair of noise cancelling headphones... they are not the best, but they do their work pretty good, I used them in flights and they work pretty good isolating the plane sound... just do not expect to be perfect like having a noise cancelling BOSE... The cables are built very good, they don't produce any filtering. They come with 3 different sets of ear buds to have a better fit.So, If you are looking for and inexpensive noise cancelling with decent sound, these are very good

I read the reviews people posted and they made it seem like these are good headphones but I guess you get what you pay for. I don't like the quality at all!! I should have bought a known brand name. JLab is deff not worth it.
These earbuds were low priced and they are OK for the price. I should have spent more. It's my fault.
summary: I got what I paid for.

reviewText: These headphones were very proficient although they did not look too professional,they sounded good. Its just too bad i didnt take better care for them because they lasted only a year for me.
summary: My First pair of JBuds Headphones for ipod

reviewText: I'm pleased. Not looking for high-fidelity. Found GOOD fidelity with these ear buds. Well-pleased for the price. They fit comfortably and medium buds fit my ears just fine. I have years of experience with high tech devices. These work just fine. The rest is largely marketing hype.
These earplugs are much more comfortable than what came with my iPod.  The $10 sale price was too good to pass up so I bought a spare set.

I found the audio performance of the JLAB J1M-BLK-FOIL earbuds disappointing. They lack low end and have a thin sound that doesn't come close to being 'Hi-Fi'. I understand that that they only cost about $10, but they don't sound as good as other earbuds I've bought for about the same price and they are clearly inferior to my old BlackBerry headphones, which you can now buy on Amazon for $1.99.

When I first got these, I enjoyed them (until they broke), but had not had much experience with any after market earbuds or IEMs. I enjoyed these, but looking back now that I have tried several pairs, a few being in the same price range, agree with those that believe that these are overrated. They are cheap enough that if you try them and they are not up to your standards then your wallet is not too angry. While these are much better than stock apple buds (most things are), there is nothing that stands out about them except maybe for the cool colors and cheap price.I would recommend checking out the MEElectronics M9 as it is frequently on sale for about the same price. The Philips SHE850 is great for bass lovers. Also the Monoprice 8323 (not available on Amazon) is known for very good sound and is cheaper than the Jbuds, they are known to be a bit bulky and hard to get a fit without after-market tips though.My recommendation is that you look around because even at this price point, there are better options out there
summary: Better than stock buds, but better option at this price

reviewText: Good:Good sound and construction quality for the price. If you only want to spend $20, it's hard to do better than these.Generally pretty comfortable and can be worn for long periods of time, especially if you're the type who doesn't like an earbud to put things too deeply in your ear canal.Bad:Ear fit isn't very tight, unless you turn them upside down and shove them way into your ear. Even then, I had to use the rubber pads from a different  pair of buds for them to fit at all. The largest size pads that came with the buds were too small and pretty cheap. So while they are comfortable, people with larger ears may have a hard time keeping them in.They also do a poor job of blocking out sound. I normally only listen through one ear so that I can remain aware of my surroundings, so I need good isolation or I end up having to concentrate to hear. Even with both in, you can't really use these effectively on the subway or in the car with the window down unless you have the volume turned way up.The pads have fallen off more than once, which is unusual. Make sure you have spares, in case you lose one.Recommendation:Consider these if you1) are cheap2) like "Y" style headphones (I prefer J because of my one-ear listening)3) don't have large ear canalsBottom Line:I've been very critical of these in my review, but all in all I am pleased with them for listening to audiobooks, which is most of my listening.If you want a better fit, better pads, a case, and a volume control, consider theSkullcandy SC-SBB3.5 Smokin' Earbud Black, which were my former pair until they were eaten by my cat.They're the same price, and sound great once they've been broken in. Though I prefer the smokin buds to these, opinions are divided and you might not agree after reading all the reviews.The cheaper 'inked' buds by Skullcandy should be avoided however - within a week I had lost a pad and one of the phones had inexplicably died, and the fit isn't as good (but still better than the jbuds).

I like this style of earphones, I have small ears and these are the only style that doesn't apply pressure.  I purchased the pink set since it matches my ipod case.  The price is also reasonable.  The only thing is I have had them about six months and I had to order replacement buds - they become detached easily.  I use them to block out noise, while studying and/or working.  They are comfortable to wear for long periods.  I often fall asleep with them in, and most times I wake up and they are still attached.The only drawback I have found is that the bent earphone plug doesn't stay in place with my iphone - it is because it has a thick clear cover.  My next purchase will be similar only with the straight plug.

Noise reduction is decent, they don't hurt my ears like other in-ear headphones do, and seem relativity sturdy. I wish I could say they sounded superb but the sound is iffy at best.  It's muddy and the bass is far too high compared many of my other headphones.I bought these for cheap workout headphones that I wouldn't mind getting ruined and that's exactly what I got.
summary: I expected more from the reviews, but the price was good.

reviewText: THESE ARE GREAT EARBUGS CLEAR SOUND GREAT PRICE LOVE THE COLOR MUST ORDER SOME MORE SO LIGHT WEIGHT CANT TELL YOU HAVE THEM IN YOUR EARS

I am no audiophile so hard to explain exactly what I do not like about these earbuds but they make my music sound a bit different than all of my other earbuds - especially the drums/bass.  For the price, I was not expecting much so I am satisfied.On the plus side, I like that the cords are equal length & not the annoying around the neck style.  Also, they actually fit my ears, whereas other earbuds w/ the rubber ends always fall out no matter what size I use.Overall these are OK buds, especially for the price, but audiophiles may want to look elsewhere.

These sound really good, especially when you consider the price point.Really only good for listening in your easy chair or otherwise sitting still. They just won't stay in my ears during any kind of physical activity.
summary: inexpensive and sound good, but fall out

reviewText: The Good: Great sound, comfortable in ear, can change the ear bud cushion.The Bad: Durability, I go to put the ear buds in and I notice the wire is exposed. For no reason the wire was exposed, now granted i put tape around it and it still works, but I would not buy again.
summary: Sounds and looks good Horrible Durability

reviewText: WOW!I can't believe it, 9 bucks for the best ear-buds I've ever had?!?These headphones are amazing. The sound quality is beautiful, and they fit in my ears perfectly (not to mention you can easily remove the default size, and replace them with one of two additional sizes that are included). I'm so happy I found these, and just before I was about to run out to Radio Shack to buy a more expensive pair of the same or worse quality headphones. And $41 off?!!? THAT's FREAKIN AWESOME.THANKS :D

I read many reviews on these headphones expecting some good bass, extreme comfort, and a quality product for my money. After taking them out of the packaging I instantly realized what a waste of money this was. First off, the headphones themselves and the mic look and feel cheaper than shown in the product pictures. So that right off the bat is false advertisement, regardless I will try and be fair. I admit the cord and plug feel very nice and sturdy. But as much as I try and like these I just can't. The instruments whether it be hip hop or rock, all sound jumbled up and thrown in randomly like it was being played through a dryer. The vocals sounded very hollow and the bass barely even tickles my ear drums. Overall I am not satisfied with these headphones, and probably would get better entertainment if I had burned the money used for these rather than actually buying them. If your looking for some good headphones for under $20 and want a lot of bass then I would recommend the JVC Gummy Plus. Otherwise my overall recommendation would be the Soul by Ludacris SL99's. It is like a sub woofer in your ear but with absolute clarity, no distortion, and block out any excess noise.
I use it for workout and the sound is great. My only complain is that it doesn't come with a clip to clip it to the shirt so it doesn't drop. aside from that, it's very good.
I was looking for some comfortable earbuds that actually stay put. These fit the bill. Sound great and for $10 you can't go wrong. I've had these for a few months now and don't have any complaints.

I bought these for using at work (cubicle environment, sometimes co-workers can be loud and distracting). I have had them about 6 months and they work GREAT! I can notice noise reduction just by putting them in without music on, can turn my music on low volume and it will block out most other noises. Sometimes I'll turn the volume up a little more to make sure no sounds distract me. The sound quality has been great compared to all the other cheap headphones I have used before, I've never been one to spend much on headphones. For under 10 bucks, these are awesome! They are very comfortable too, don't even notice they are there, though I often only listen to my music for a hour or two, sometimes three.Overall, GREAT product, GREAT price; I will be buying another pair for home use!

I was very disappointed with these earbuds.  The cord was stiff and heavy so the earbuds did not stay in my ears at all.  Also I started have trouble with the sound cutting out after about a month of use compared to my last pair from a different company which lasted over a year of heavy use.
I wear these with my iPod when I walk, or on the airplane.  Very comfy, and the sound's good enough to suit me.

These may not have "perfect" sound reproduction for extremely demanding listeners, but for me, they are awesome. They are SO comfortable. C-O-M-F-O-R-T-A-B-L-E! And they stay put in my ears. They never fall out. I have used the ear buds that came with my ipod, and other replacements, but these are by far the best. They block out most background noise, better than others, but not completely. I use my ipod mostly for listening to podcasts, mostly the 1 year daily audio bible ([...]) but I also listen to music, and these are fine for me. When the time comes for a replacement, I will come back for more. What a great price.EDIT: It is now a year later and I am back to purchase another set. My husband's earbuds (another brand) gave out, so I'm getting him some of these. My original pair is still going strong. And now, they are on sale, 4 dollars less. Can't beat that.
summary: Exactly what I was looking for

reviewText: I had these for a week and then I destroyed them by being careless.  While I had them they were great and I will probably get another set soon.

The sound quality is very poor for these ear buds. I use them with my laptop and I can't turn on soft background music because the quality is so poor when the sound is low. When I turn up the volume, the quality improves but really lacks the depth and range that I was hoping for.On the other hand, they fit comfortably into my years.These are $20 ear buds. Don't get your hopes too high.UPDATE:I just noticed the comment attached to my review. The buds do actually sound much better (after the 24 hour "burn-in"). I previously owned a pair of Shure ear buds that were stolen and these buds replaced those (hey, I'm a poor student). My comparison to the depth and range was with regards to my previous buds. That said, the sound is excellent for the money.

If you're looking for a more comfortable and somewhat better isolating headphone than typical earbuds, you could do a lot worse. I think these sound pretty good and with the three different sizes of cushions provided, it should be easy to get a comfortable fit.One simple improvement would be to mark the left or right bud in some obvious manner so I don't have to squint at the microscopic "L" and "R" on the sides. I'm thinking about putting a dot of liquid paper or something on one of them.Edit - so they lasted about three years. I just recently threw them away; one ear just quit working.
summary: Hard to beat for the price

reviewText: I have small ear canals and even when using the smallest pads they would slip out of my ears. Having to constantly reinsert them was a real hassle as I walk in the mornings. The sound quality is ok but nothing special. I finally bought a pair of Koss headphones and they work much better. I cannot recommend this product based on my experiences.
summary: Caution if you have small ears....

reviewText: Bought for my daughter to replace the the earphones that came with her ipod, these are much better quality than others listed here

I bought these based on the shear number of positive reviews, unfortunately, the sound quality was far less than stellar.  The bass was good, but the mids and highs were muffled, like I was listening under water, the OEM ear buds from Apple that came with my Ipod sound better than these.  If you want deep bass then these may be for you, but if you want detail and clean highs then look elsewhere.  I'm going to check out the Sennheiser CX300-S Earbuds which Amazon also sells, they are a little more than double the price but if the sound is even half as good they'll be worth it.
summary: Good bass, horrible mids and highs

reviewText: I purchased the high end earbuds for $80 and then ran across these on the internet.  I read some of the reviews which stated these $20 earbuds were just as good as the high end earbuds and I purchased them to give as a gift to my girlfriend.  I tried them out when they arrived and I must admit that these inexpensive earbuds are GREAT for the price.  Had I known about these before spending $80 bucks I could have about 4 pair of these by now!!!!  Great buy and not as fragile as the high end earbuds.
summary: Item arrived quickly and in great condition.

reviewText: Still in use. These have outlived every other ear bud my daughter has had. Worth the price.
Was on a business trip and one of the earbuds fell off. Very frustrating. When the earbuds are on, they work great and I love them however. 3 stars ***

Was looking for a replacement to my Sony's.These don't at all compare in terms of both sound quality or build quality.These are very flimsy and poor quality, and sound like trash.The two buds are widened by simply prying apart the two wires. There is no adjustment or securing mechanism.I returned these.Worth coughing up the dough for some quality.
No good, there is a distortion / clicking sound in these buds since day 1.I must've gotten a bad pair.

This headphone has worked a long time for me, over a year.I treated it badly and after a year it went bad.The sound quality is great, and it blocks out a lot of sound.I can wear it for a long time and my ears don't hurt.

A little muddy sounding for music. Fine for voice. As noted in other reviews, comfortable, but rubber earpieces fall off too easily.After using these a long time, I bought the J2, the next step up. I suggest you spend the extra $6 or so for those. The following are advantages of the j2 over this one:1. More flexible cord lies more naturally and comfortably.2. Noticeably better sound overall, still a little muddy on the highs.3. Longer body fits in ear further, making it more secure.4. J2 plug is narrow enough to fit the iPhone using the bumper case. The plug of this earphone set will not fit the hole in the bumper case.
summary: OK, good for voice, not so good for music. Get the J2 instead.

reviewText: Do yourself a favor and read the directions.  There is a "burn-in" procedure that needs to be followed before these sound anywhere close to good.  I had them hooked up to a radio in my garage for two days and after that they sounded pretty good.

I received these today and so far, I love them. they are clear and I can take calls easier, pause my music and I like that the mic isn't so far down on the cord that it's hard to hear or I have to lift it to my mouth to use.

I was a bit disappointed with these after reading review that the sound quality was great. I'd say it was average. They door a poor job of blocking out ambient noise too. I have another pair of buds that came with my Ericsson cell phone that are far superior to these at both sound quality and reducing ambient noise. Unless you get a great deal, not worth spending too much.

I god these over the JVC headphones in the same price range that I already have a pair of. These headphones sound bad. Everyone sounds like they have a cold. Talk radio, music, its all bad sounding. But they are just for work so I am not returning them.

For the price I paid for these, you can't beat it. Obviously you need a good sound system to plug into to get good sound but these ear buds do a very good job of keeping external noise out. I use these on my PSP, laptop or mp3 player while my son's at Hockey practice and 90% of all that outside noise is gone, the only outside noise you hear is if someone is right next to you talking or yelling. Anything past a 10 foot radius you can hardly hear. Worth the money

Just bought a Sansa Clip+, and a few of the reviews for that product recommended picking up the very reasonable JBuds as an upgrade. Doing back-to-back tests of the Clip+'s stock buds against the JBuds, JBuds fell short by a mile in terms of sound quality. There's no bass, not even fiddling with the Sansa's EQ functions to bring out the bass. Sansa's buds are by no means mind-blowing, but they at least have some low end.I'm simply looking for a reasonably flat or neutral frequency curve, as much as an inexpensive set of headphones can provide. Not seeking out massive bass. I listen at low to moderate volume. The Sansas sound better, so the JBuds will be an emergency backup. I suppose the one thing to recommend them is their insanely low price.
summary: Tinny sound quality compared to stock Sansa buds

reviewText: Bought in April, broke in August.The let anyone near you listen to what you hear, they suck at blocking out your sound.

The reason I only give it three stars is because: 1. It has no volume control or switch to phone control on the cord.  These are just simple ear buds with no frills.  2.  The "Noise-Reducing" in the name is just pure marketing hype.  I have noticed no noise-reduction at all, unless you crank up the volume so high that your ears buzz the next day.  But I must say that for the extremely modest price, they deliver much better performance than the standard Apple ear-buds.Update: Cord/plug failed after about 6 months.  Not very durable.
summary: Good sound, but cord/plug failed after 6 months.

reviewText: These are JLabs least expensive ear buds and at around $5 these are an incredible bargain!  I like to keep a pair of backup/loaner ear buds on hand for emergencies, either my own or my kid's.  These fill the bill and don't hurt the wallet too badly and don't sound bad, especially for the price.

I originally bought these buds because I wanted something on the cheap side that would deliver good sound quality and decent noise reduction; these buds have met all of my expectations and exceeded them.  Plus, these little buds fit great in both my ears, especially after finding the right combination of earpiece sizes.  The cord length is great too!  These buds passively reduce enough noise in my work environment that I have to take them out of my ears to hear whether I'm talking too loudly or softly to the guy next to me...  Just the way I like it!  No complaints here!

I was looking for some really cheap headphones that were better than the horrible iPod earbuds. After reading all the positive reviews, I decided to go with these. I'm happy with them, the sound isn't incredible, but it's MUCH better than the iPod buds. They come with different sized cups to fit various sized ears. They fit comfortably, don't fall out (unless I'm exercising, I wouldn't recommend these for workouts) and don't become irritating after long listening periods. For $10, you can't beat these. I'd happily buy these again and again.
For the money, great value.  But don't expect any noise-reduction.  They are very comfortable and I would buy them again.
summary: Great Value Ear Buds, but don't reduce Noice

reviewText: The sound is crisp, clean, andcan carry big orchestrations at a high volume level. This unit cannott be beat for the price. You won't find anything even remotely close os performance for this price!!!

For anyone wanting a replacement set of ear buds and don't want to spend a fortune you simply can't beat the sound quality of these which actually outperform many other higher priced units. The fit is great in the ear with superb highs and bass that is produced just right. I highly recommend these for all portable units, cell phones, tablets and such.

I have other earphones that reduce noise better and have the same sound quality and price range. They don't even say noise reducing either o.OThese are somewhat noise reducing, but I've used better ones. When you turn your music on, it's noise reducing alright. If you used them without music as in working out in the gym and you forgot your player you will be able to hear sounds. Sounds that are louder and you won't hear the squeaks on the floor and people walking around and such.The quality is great, their comfortable, but I wouldn't use them for reducing noise without music like some do.
these broke quickly for me with a slight pull of the cord they fell apart. for the price i guess i cant complain

My daughter uses these with her iPod and likes them (well, no complaints -- she's a teenager ;-) ).  After six months one ear went out.  All I had to do was send my invoice via e-mail to JLab Audio and they sent a replacement, in under a week. I had entered a warranty request at www jlabaudio com and they sent me instructions on what to do. That is great service.I've replaced a few other company's headsets/ear buds under warranty and it included sending back the set at my expense with delivery tracking (which adds more cost) and it took more than a few weeks to get a replacement.  They don't seem to get it that it means being without a headset/buds until it is replaced or else keeping multiple pairs around (or buying multiple pairs) just in case one breaks.  Even for inexpensive pairs such as these, treating the customer and warranty like it involves an expensive and important piece of equipment is smarter than making it a trial by ordeal in the hopes the customer will just buy a replacement, because they are so cheap.  People use $1 coupons, so why give up on a $10 piece of equipment?Four stars, because they did fail at 6 months. I'll probably look at jlab products first when I need more because their warranty response was so good.
summary: One ear side died at 6 months - jlab replaced them in under a week

reviewText: These ear buds only lasted 4 months before the one of the ear buds stop working.  While these had decent sound and comfort for the price...they definitely didn't last very long. I wouldn't recommend purchasing these ear buds.
summary: You get what you pay for...

reviewText: this product is really great, it works perfect with my ipod, and it cancels the noise around my desk at the office , which is the best. BUT!!!! it's been only 3 months and just yesterday, one of them stoped working, it is so annoying to have music only in one ear!! if u are into that, go ahead because after 3 months that's what you'll have! i guess that considering the price one should not feel so upset ...
summary: great but won't last for too long....

reviewText: Good cheap earbuds to have if you're always losing them.They have decent bass and treble after you burn them in for a couple of hours.With the price, you can't go wrong.
summary: JLab JBuds Hi-Fi Noise-Reducing Ear Buds with Universal Microphone (Black)

reviewText: If you are looking for an inexpensive pair of earbud headphones that sound good and won't let you down, look no further. I have been using these for about 5 months now and they have lasted really well. Would buy these again. Don't listen to the negative reviews, if you are looking for inexpensive headphones and don't expect audiophile performance, you should be okay.Pros: Great value.Good sound (they are obviously not the best earphones ever, but for 10 bucks its not bad), use them mostly for podcasts and rock/alt/jazz musicComes with 3 sizes of silicone tipsStays in my ear really well, even on long bike-rides and comfortableSilicone tips don't fall off easily (a previous headphone lost its silicone tip very often and finally terminally)Cons: Good sound, not great, sounds a bit mushy at times.I think the cord is a little long, at least for me (I'm 5'8") and they keep snagging.

The 3 star rating is not a reflection of dissatisfaction, these are perfectly good earphones with some strengths. But I closely compared them to my cheaper Sony MDR-E828LP, and they lost. My medicore rating reflects how they compare instead of how they perform.Strengths - they fit snugly and comfortably in the ear. This results in a much better noise cancelling effect. The bass is better in these earphones than the Sony, maybe too good for certain songs or audio.Weaknesses - Though they're good earphones and more comfortable than the Sony, the sound tends to have some distortion and is not as crisp and clear as the Sony.UPDATE 12/15/11:I've bumped it from a 3 to a 4 star review. They sound better since I've used them and the fact is they are very comfortable compared to the Sony's. I use these exclusively now.
Fast shipping and great quality for the price.  I do wish that the cord was a little bit longer, but isn't an issue.
Pros:1. Comfortable Fit2. Above Average Signal Quality3. Great Value For $$$Cons:1. Poor Insulated Wiring2. Prefer The Angled Jack3. No CaseBest "Prime" Choice For The $$$
The sound on these are very 'tinny'. And I hear a crackle while putting them in my ears. I don't think I'd buy them again.

A few bucks, free shipping, what else do you want? It sounds great to me but I am no audiophile. What other options do you have at this pricepoint? Wallyworld costs more, plus you have to pay tax and the gas to drive there.
summary: For the price, it just cant be beat.

reviewText: I originally bought these headphones are backup headphones. They do what they are supposed to, but they do not sound amazing. They will get you by in a pinch.
I bought these to use when I run but they always fall out when I try to run with them. They are still a decent pair of headphones for the price.
Great price, just what I ordered. The item was shipped early in great condition. I will continue to purchase this item on line. Will not choose another brand.

Okay when I first recieved these today and put them on I thought "Wow, these really are noise-isolating" but when I started playing my playlist it sounded bad. It sounds like someone put my treble down to the lowest on all my songs. If you want cheap-kinda-good-quality headphones, purchase some of the newer JLab Jbuds, they're worth your money, not these. SO basically:Noise-Isolation: 5/5Quality: 1/5
summary: Noise Isolating is amazing, but the quality is bad, REALLY BAD.

reviewText: Perfect for music or gaming in tablet or pc with the noise reduction

I had to finally replace the earbuds on my Creative Zen Micro, and I picked these since they were inexpensive ($6) and white to match my Zen Micro.  Hahaha!I'm not enough of an audiophile to really get technical here, and honestly I didn't care that they had the best available sound quality.  I just wanted them to be clear with great sound to a casual listener, and comfortable.  So far, these have fit the bill perfectly.The cabling is a decent length (a bit over 4' total), and the buds themselves feel comfortable.  I didn't notice any noise-reduction per se, but it did a good job of muffling outside noises.I haven't had them long enough to see durability yet, but I'm not really expecting anything unreasonable at this price point.  I feel this is an excellent value for the money I paid.

I don't use plugs very often but these are SO comfortable to wear that I won't hesitate to use them! I've always hated the ones you get when you by a product, ie: cell phone, mp3 - so these are not only comfortable, but you can hear very clearly, and you cannot beat the price! Any plugs worth their weight usually cost a pretty penny....these work extremely well and cost little to nothing. And they shipped SUPER FAST! Definitely recommend!

I have paid a lot for earbuds but I like these little guys. I go through earbuds like crazy, even the expensive ones, so I decided to go cheaper. These have good sound and they are noise reducing. I can use these on the airplane and it cuts out the surrounding engine noise and noisy next seat neighbors. They do not have the best bass sound but then again, you should not expect that from the price. If you want good, noise reducing earbuds that are not expensive....these are great. They come with different sized ear inserts as well.

But it will seem like it because that's how much I love these things. I work at a computer desk job and get bored easily so I listen to podcasts on my phone using earpieces. Most earpieces that come with the phone are hard and my ears hurt after a few hours of continuous use, not these ones. I work 10 hours a day (yes, I get overtime and no, I'm not exaggerating) and I use just for that entire time and my ears are fine.They come with three size gel inserts for your ears, try and figure out which ones are the most comfortable for you. Now I do have one slight critic, occasionally they fall out when I turn my head or if I'm walking with them. These are for indoor use or slow leisurely strollers, I cannot imagine jogging/running or doing any form of strenuous exercise with them. Also, sadly these do not include a mouthpiece for talking on the phone and there is no pause button on the ear piece itself, you'll have to use your phone or music player directly for such actions.Other than that I cannot recommend them enough, likeI said, I make no money off this review in any way, i just think they're a great product. If you want comfort for your earpiece, this is the one for you.
summary: this review was not bought and paid for by the makers

reviewText: My ipod's ear buds finally fell apart recently, and I wanted a decent replacement that didn't cost a fortune. The JBuds are quite satisfactory. I had no idea how crappy the sound from the ipod's standard earphones were, until I heard my music with these. In fact, the sound range is so different that I had to readjust the equalizer to compensate.The rubber seal is very soft and fits snugly (there are several sizes available in the package). This really cuts down the ambient noise; I can finally keep the volume down to non-ear-damaging levels and still hear the music clearly, which just wasn't possible with my old earphones.The headphones and cord are very light, almost too light. I jog with these, and the cord is light enough to bounce around, and the noise of the jostling cord travels up to the buds. However, the cord is long enough to wrap around my wrist, which mostly eliminates the slack.  Overall, I'm happy with my purchase.
Does just what it says. Great sound from a inexpensive product. Really helps reduce outside noice when I am playing music. Without the music playing the noise reduction is minimal.

I'm not quite sure what I was expecting from these headphones, but it was apparently too much. I have a very noisy roommate, and I was hoping that these "Noise-Reducing" headphones, tied with a white noise machine, would drown out his sound. Much to my dismay, these things didn't help much. Fainter noises, yes. They do help with those. Also, the words on the side of the Ear Buds have already faded after only 2-3 weeks of use. But, they were only $9.99. Next time, however, I will be buying a higher quality set.
summary: You get what you pay for.

reviewText: These were great little $10 earbuds. Unfortunately, the right ear shorted out within 2 months of use.

My hearing is not perfect, but these buds provide enough quality to listen to music for the quality of the recording to be decerned.  I have owned many sets of ear buds and feel this is as good as any I have used in recent memory.  They have not blown me away, so I used three stars in recommending them to use on your Player or Phone and if you require ear buds that must have a price tag in great excess to what I paid for these (5.99$), then by all means go for it and rate them even higher than I rated these.  I've left you room to do so.

I purchased these headphones because I needed to replace a pair of cheap ear buds that I thought I had lost. I considered the Skullcandy ones and these on here for about a month before finally deciding on the JBuds. Unfortunately, I made the wrong choice. These sounds absolutely terrible. There is no bass and the sound is just horribly flat. Eventually I found my pair of ear buds and I've been using them ever since. The ear buds that sound better were a $10 pair of Maxwells that we bought at a K-Mart on a road trip in California... looks like I'll need to get a better pair soon...

I guess it must be a new trend to call just about every pair of earbuds "noise reducing". Yes, they reduce noise. Just as anything you would stick in your ears would reduce noise. I have noise reducing q-tips and noise reducing cotton balls that work just as well. If you want noise reducing earbuds, there are not the ones. I get more noise reduction by sticking my fingers in my ears.As for the quality of the product itself, all I can say is that you get what you pay for. I would recommend these for children or for people who aren't that concerned with the quality of sound. They, of course, will not compete with some of the more expensive products on the market, but they work fine. I'll keep mine at my office for mandatory web casts.Overall, better than I expected for the price but nothing to get too excited about.
summary: You Get What You Pay For

reviewText: Sound quality is okay-nothing that's going to blow your mind. It's like 6 dollars so it's not like I was expecting much.If there's one thing I really like about these, it's that they're extremely comfortable. I can wear them and not really notice them, so that's really great. It comes with 3 different sizes of rubber ear tips, so you're should be able find one that fits you.However, these aren't very durable-the wiring next to the connector already broke after ~2 weeks of usage. JLab used to have great customer service with a hassle free warranty, but now they make you return it after it breaks, and the shipping to return this back will cost almost as much as buying a new pair, so why bother.I really wanted to like these headphones, but breaking after only 2 weeks of regular use is a true disappointment.

This review is basically a direct comparison of the JBuds andV-MODA Bass Freq Earbuds - Bling Bling Black. Both being "cheap" earbuds, I felt they needed to be compared.I bought these because my V-MODAs were left at my father's place, which is approx. 4,000 miles or so from my place. I was without a pair of earbuds and really needed some, so I figured I would try these out since they were cheap but got great looking reviews. Sigh...FEEL:- The fit is somewhat comfortable, but for me, quite a bit less comfortable than the V-MODAs. The rubber buds are completely flimsy, almost like the consistency of a popped balloon.AMBIENT NOISE:- For these to be called "Noise-Reducing" is a complete joke. With these in my ears I could clearly hear the outside world both with music on and off. I tried different rubber covers, angles in my ears, etc. to no avail. The V-MODAs hands down win in this department. They actually almost feel like noise-cancelling buds.SOUND:- I don't know if it's because of the amount of air or ambient noise from the outside world, but the sound is very tinny, weak, and basically gives you a headache at mid-range volume levels. There is pretty much ZERO bass response. All the other sounds just mesh together. One plus, is they do have great volume boost, meaning I had to turn the volume down with these headphones to get the same volume level as with the V-MODAs.So, in conclusion, if you are looking at both these and the V-MODAs and don't know which ones to pick, get the V-MODAs. They win across the board.PROS- Inexpensive- Loud- Black- Semi-comfortableCONS- Do not reduce noise at all- No bass response- Low quality sound gives headaches- Cheap rubber + construction- I paid money for them

The earbuds that came with my Zune suck.  After shopping around Amazon, I found these and have been very happy with them.  They were so good that my wife started using them for her Zune, so I had to buy another pair for myself.
summary: Great earbuds at a great price.

reviewText: They fit comfortably and tightly in the ear, blocking out sound better than other earbuds. They seem slightly quieter than my old ones. The cord is the longest I've ever seen on earbuds; I usually have to wind it up or stuff it in my pocket to keep it from catching on things, but I guess that's better than having too short a cord. Great quality for the price.
Good bass, clean highs and the right size to fit my ear.  Nice earbuds for the money. I like them better than my Sony and Coby earbuds.

I've got several other pairs of earbuds that work fine if I'm just sitting around, walking, etc. The problem with others was that when I was cruising on my bike, the wind noise completely drowned out whatever I was listening to.With the large cushions attached to these JBuds earbuds, I can hear my podcasts perfectly clearly, even when whistling downhill at 35 MPH. And when a car comes up behind me, I can still hear it coming, so these are perfect for my purposes, and the price is a bargain. I love 'em.
This is a great product, especially for travel.  Looks nice, durable, produces good quality in sound, and easy to carry around..

These are fabulous earphones. And at the price--wow! The earphones that came with my Sansa e260 were awful; they wouldn't stay in my ears unless I pushed them there all the time. These little JBuds fit in comfortably and stay put all by themselves. Even so, they wouldn't be worth much if they didn't sound good. They sound great! I'm very pleased.
summary: The best 20 bucks I've spent in a long time!

reviewText: For the price you can not beat it, even if you break them at this price you can certainly get new ones when ever.  They fit great and they do last.  These are my second pair, my first pair lasted about 2years, so what else can I say.

These seem like such an amazing value on paper, but straight out of the box, only one side of the earphones works. I was afraid it was my ipod, but testing these with other devices (and my ipod with different earphones) revealed that the earphones were defective.I purchased these to have an inexpensive set of earphones to use while sleeping, as I don't want to risk damage to my favorite Bose earphones. The price was right, and they were very comfortable (even for a side-sleeper like me), where the Bose feel like little rocks in my ears while trying to sleep.If you want them for noise-cancelling, however, do not waste your time with these. Both with the original pads on the earbuds, AND changed to the tiered ones by the same brand, the noise cancelling of these is virtually nonexistent.If you want cheap and comfortable, I say go for it. Just plan on possibly having to return them if you get a pair that is defective.
summary: Comfortable, but defective right out of the box.

reviewText: I bought these earphones to replace the ones that came with my ipod, mostly because I wanted more sound isolation for outside noises, especially for airplane travel.  They seem to do this a little bit better than my old ones, and the sound quality may be better, though I'm not totally sure about that.  The problem I have is that I just find them uncomfortable to wear for very long.  It may be that ear buds like this just won't work for me.  I tried all three sizes, and each was uncomfortable.  I've gone back to the original apple earphones.  At least this was a pretty inexpensive experiment.
The speakers sound OK at best. I tried listening to music, but they distort very easily. Barely any bass and not very loud either
I purchased these earbuds for myself to go with my MP3 player.  They are wonderful.  If you need a GOOD pair, you need to get these!

I bought these as an extra to have lying around and was VERY disappointed at the quality. I wasn't expecting much for the price but the sound quality for these is VERY POOR! I plugged them into my MP3 player which was set at the volume that I like and sounds great on my Skullcandy earbuds but these sounded distorted and the bass was near nonexistant. I will stick to Skullcandy in the future....

These sound really bad, I'm sad though as I liked the built-in MIC part. They have no bass, sound really low quality to me. I don't know, but compared to my other 8$ ear buds, these are garbage._If you are looking for really great ear buds for 8$ with nice, noticeable bass and feel, get the Panasonic RPHJE120P In-Ear Headphone. They are perfect!
I liked that they had them in yellow, green, etc. Stay in your ears did not have trouble with them falling out. Good sound and comfortable in your ears.

These are the most comfortable headphones you can buy, they do have trouble staying in your ear at times, but can be re-secured with ease. I normally use them just to doze off, as they don't bother my ears at all. The sound isn't the best..nor is the bass, but I do like that they isolate noise very well. For only $6 earphones, these do last for quite a while, and does the job for a basic music listening experience.
Nothing fancy.  They work but they don't cancel out any external noise.  Kinda pricey for what you get.
