earbuds certainly have an expiration date, the expiration on them is how you treat them. I could pay $59 for a pair and end up streching the cord by sitting on it and leaning forward on the metro. I could pay $6 and do the same. The jbuds have good sound at an inexpensive price. Also by reading the reviews the company stands by their product.
Quality was very poor. Spend more and get a brand that is reputable. The color was cool, but over all it was garbage and not worth the shipping to send it back.

These really do reduce noise, and are VERY comfortable in the ear.  They come with 3 different sizes of ear pieces, so you're sure to get a great fit.  The replaceable tips are very soft.  After a while you forget you're wearing earbuds at all.

I wore these every day for ~2 hours and now sound only comes out of one of one side.  The wire or the plug end was not durable.  I keep my ipod in my pocket so I may be subjecting them to abnormal wear and force.
summary: Sounded good, fit in my ears, but broke in 2 weeks.

reviewText: Honestly.. JLab? I've never heard of them. But they had good reviews. I didn't really think I was going to get decent sound from these little guys.. but I was wrong. dollar for dollar.. these are real good, considering my normal headphones are Beats by Dre.. yea, good sound, even while bicycling and the wind is whipping by you..

I bought these for my teenage daughter, who mistreats headphones regularly.  I gave up spending a lot of money, but I still expected quality sound, and these give that.  They are certainly noise-cancelling - she never hears me when she has them in, even when I'm standing right beside her.  Although I suspect that may not have much to do with the headphones.  Anyway, she likes them very much and she's had them for three weeks now and they still work, so I guess they're pretty durable!

The JBuds Hi-Fi Noise-Reducing Ear Buds perform well at both reducing surrounding noise and faithfully reproducing the iPod sounds.  These are better than the original earbuds that come standard on the iPod.  I have added to my review after it was first written.  One of the ear pieces failed after about 50 uses.  I had read elsewhere about JLabs commitment to customer satisfaction.  I contacted them and they promptly sent me a replacement.  THAT'S 5 STAR IS MY BOOK!
summary: Improves the performance of an iPod

reviewText: I bought these because I wanted a cheap pair of headphones to match my apple workstation and also leave by my desk so I could listen to music throughout the work day. These are comfortable and fit me well, which is surprising, as I find that often some earbuds are too large (or my ears are very small). Either way these are great, I'm not much of an authority on sound, I do have more pricey over the ear headphones- but for this price point, the clarity is good and I can't find a bad thing to say about them. I might even buy another pair as a back up.
These are the worst headphones I have ever owned. They are cheap and stink of synthetic rubber and cheap plastic. They also broke within a week!

This is my third pair of JLAB earbuds, and it's going to be the last. I've purchased two pairs of J2s, and one J3 pair. The J2s have better sound balance than the J3s, in my opinion. But none of the JLAB earbuds hold up. The J2s I bought two weeks ago are already kaput; the PC jack simply fell off. The other pairs I purchased had a common problem: within a month, one side went dead.I took care of these J2s. I used them only at home; they weren't getting slammed about in a purse or pocket. I have earbuds, from other manufacturers, which have lasted more than a year.Update: I caved and returned the broken pair for a replacement. The replacement stopped working after one week. The headphone jack is flimsy and falls to pieces almost immediately. It's too bad, because for the price the sound is excellent.
I can't say that I notice any noise reducing ability with these, but they are okay for the price. I won't purchase a second pair.
These are a high quality sound ear piece. I use them at the gym to listen to the shows while I work out and also on my computer to skype. The price is great and I will buy again!!!!
I'm not an audiophile, but these sound as good as more expensive 'buds and certainly better than any I've ever heard before.But the real reason I got them is they're *really comfortable*.
Not nearly the bass and fullness as Skull Candy. A bit weak, but didn't cost much either. JLab claims they were better than they are.

These little things pack a good sound.  Ya don't miss a frequency.  The only con, which could be a plus to others, is the cord is quite long.  I only mention it because, when seated, it can get caught on a plethora of things but I just tuck the excess into my shirt pocket.  Great lil headphones!

Though these usually crap out after about 6 months of daily use, getting fuzzy when you move the jack, the sound is very respectable for the price. They stay in my ear when I am exercising. The cord about 6-inches longer than most similar products around the same price, which is nice because I am tall and carry my phone in my pocket.I currently have two pairs of these -- one at work and one at home -- and use them every day. I cannot recommend them highly enough.

My left JBud went south after 14 months. Excellent response via email. They quickly replaced my Jbuds even though they were 2 months beyond warranty.But the new ones have a straight plug, rather than the nicer L-plug.

These headphones worked great. Didn't hurt my ears like most in ear buds. But like every pair of headphones I've ever owned the cable near the connector didn't make a connection anymore after like 8 months of use. Not bad earphones for the price. Just don't expect them to last forever.

These are fantastic.  I use them at a MUCH lower volume than any other headphones.  They are comfortable in my ear.  I haven't had them long enough to talk about durability, but I am buying a second pair for my husband, who tried mine for a weekend and loved them.

These earbuds were cheap without being TOO cheap, which made them seem like the perfect choice to replace the stock earbuds that came with my mp3 player once they shorted out, resulting in the left bud not giving out any sound. I was happy with the JBuds when I got them, since they were comfortable and had better sound quality than the freebies. Overall, I was quite happy with them.However, I bought them in February, a mere three months ago. Today the left bud started shorting out when the jack wasn't positioned just right. Pretty pathetic considering that the free earbuds lasted TWO YEARS. I could get a new set of these under warranty, but I'll save myself from more hassle a few months down the line and buy a better, longer-lived pair of earbuds. Not recommended unless you want a throwaway set of earbuds, in which case you might as well get one of the brands of earbuds that cost ~$10 or less.

I have a Sony Walkman Cell Phone, with the Proprietary ear buds hooked via USB.  I know that speakers on electronic devices are not as good as Head Phones, but last month - with the purchase of myToshiba Thrive 10.1-Inch 16 GB Android Tablet AT105-T1016+Toshiba Thrive Portfolio Case for 10.1-Inch Tablet (PA3945U-1EAB)andHP 16 GB Flash Memory Card Q6305A-AZ (Amazon Frustration-Free Packaging)-(not to mention my regular shopping on here -Mighty Bright TravelFlex Book Light, Purple Mighty Bright TravelFlex Book Light, Purple,Dirt Devil SD20005RED Scorpion Quick Flip 7 AMP Hand Vac - RED, GJO48261 - MIcrofiber Cleaning Cloth, Lint-free, 16x16, Assorted to clean computer and TV Equipment, my premium Pet Food and several other things to furnish my new apartment or help with the move) -So, for the price - these are excellent.  They are equivalent if not better in sound quality than the ear buds for the Sony Walkman.  The bass and stereo is exceptional, and I've finally realized I needed some good headphones for my Laptop.  The first set of ear plugs fit me just fine, so I didn't need to switch out for other sizes.  I could even pull out the Sony ear piece, and put these in the USB connectoid.I do realize that they might last about six months.  However, the Sony Earplugs are about the same quality, and I've had them since 2007, 2008.  Switched them over to a newer model Cell Phone last December (since the newer models don't come with headphones).  In six months - I'll buy a better pair, or splurge on some top of the line headphones, but until then (with Amazon just lapping up my dollars), these will have to do.  And they do just nicely.
summary: Needed Something in My Budget for New Thrive, Does not Disappoint for All Electronic Devices.

reviewText: It was a good deal and worth what I paid for them but not the greatest sound quality.  They included 3 sizes of the actual earbud covers so that helped with finding the right fit but they still fall out at times during a work out. If you are just walking around they are fine.The current model costs 5x as much. Since earbuds are often lost or misplaced, you really can't go wrong.
summary: Good value but you get what you pay for!

reviewText: Sounds good and noise-reduction works well. Very comfortable in use and the microphone is easy to access when I receive calls.

I purchased these ear buds because the ear buds had degraded and one of them fell off of the phones itself and was lost.  I have a hearing disability, so I tend to listen to music through ear phones if my hearing aids are not in.  I thought I was getting good sound quality with my previous ear phones until I put these on for the first time.  What an incredible difference these made to me!  I could hear the voices of the singers much more clearly, the instrumentals in the background, just everything was so much better!  I love music, and my slowly progressing hearing loss has been robbing me of the pleasure of hearing music as I had heard it for so many years.  These ear phones are just incredible.  I can't believe what a difference a little set of Hi-Fi ear phones can make, but these do it.  I'm absolutely delighted with them and the difference they make in how I can now hear music.  You will absolutely love these ear phones!

short cord, trebly, hearing-reducing sound, and an ever-breaking, annoying unraveling thin cord that will drive most men insane.  Maybe all ear buds suck like this except sony.I guess I had no idea how great sony was until I had to buy some replacements.  Some complain about sony's ergonomic design and comfort.  These people are mostly uncivilized fools who don't understand how anything works and with no functioning nerve endings.  If you like ear buds for music rather than the constant annoying distraction of their existence I'd recommend those, not that I have any but the old ones I broke and are no longer made.Otherwise, silence or background noise is far preferable than these phone's tendency to constantly remind you that you are wearing them and you wasted your money on them.I think J stands for junior, so this is fine for kids who don't know any better and have no money and hear too well as it is, but not really good for you.  You deserve better than that.The fit is fine.

Plain and simple, they sound solid. No fuzzy noise, not too trebley or bassy, they fit snug in your ear, the cord is long enough so it doesn't get caught up when you turn a certain way. I also like the color black. Bottom line, they are Solid.

Not bad for the price ($5.99)  Actually I was surprised at the sound quality of the JBuds Hi-Fi Noise Reducing Ear Buds.  I had purchased the JBuds J3 a few months ago and to be honest they sound a little better than the J3's.  The J3's are still a little hollow - these have a crisper sound and deeper bass, now noise reduction was pretty darn good as they drowned out the sound of my BARKING dogs.For the price I will pick up a couple pairs for my sister (in the Pink and Purple) and I will snag a couple more for myself (black of course) I'm impressed!

Great pair of ear buds and for the price they sure are a steal! They cancel a decent amount of noise (obviously not if you're riding a lawn mower or something), but they're great for commuting/the train/etc.  I've had them for almost a year and the music on my ipod/psp sounds great with them. So glad I picked these up.
The sound is clear. Would like a little more base but for the price I'm happy. The Noise Reduction is just ok. My problem with these low cost headphones is the cord comes loose pretty easily.

Usually you have to pay quite a bit more to obtain the quality that is found in these ear buds.  With such a low price I was not sure I would be pleased with the quality but with Amazons Return Policy I did not have anything to loose.  I am glad I decided to try them because both my wife and I are very pleased with the quality and performance of the ear buds.  I use them on my iPad and my wife on her Kindle Fire.  The only reason I could not give a solid 5 Stars is that the foam insert fell off once or twice.
This product does exactly what it says it does for a nice price.  It was my first time using ear buds and they are not for me.
shoulda saved the $these sound horrible & im not an audio snob.compared to $10 skull candy (that I give 4 stars), these are awful.

These ear buds fit right into your ears like fitted ear plugs; thus reducing the ambient noise.  Although the silicon tips look durable, I am not sure how long they will last, but I've started to look for the medium size replacement tips.

I was excited to get a headphones with so many reviews from here with decent ratings.... but honestly I wouldn't buy this headphones again even if it was $5.Pros: Cheap...Cons: Honestly,bad sound (I mean really bad in my experience)bad wiring (crackles if you move the cord esp. at the connector end)plastic earpiece is very thin and doesn't feel snugDon't know if I just got the bad one of the bunch but oh well, I still use it for non-music stuff (Nintendo DS) =P
summary: It's OK... still not worth it for me

reviewText: These ear buds are ok.  They sound good and I like the length on the cord (reaches from my PC on the floor to me sitting at my desk).  I just don't really car for the tips on the ear buds, they are very thin.  But they will do till I find something better.  Thanks,

With the three sizes of foam that come with the buds you will have a custom fit with one of them.  I happened to need the largest, which gave me the best fit of any buds I've ever had!  The need for "noise-reduction" is to hear the music while riding my motorcycle.  These buds do a great job killing the afterburner noise of the wind so I can hear the tunes, but they don't block out all the traffic noise I want to hear like horns and sirens ... or the putz tailgating me!  I can wear these things all day and forget they're there; very comfortable.

I got a pair for me and for my husband.  I have probably used them for a total of 75 times in the last bunch of years as I mostly swim rather than walk.  They are now mono; one ear bud gets no sound and I always had trouble with crackling in my ear.  They were comfortable and I loved the case that you either get with or can order . . . but I wish they had been sturdier.
summary: I guess I got a bunch of year's use but . . .

reviewText: feels cheap in many ways, but what can you expect from an unknown company..sound is ok, but even my radioshack brand earphones are better which costed around $13. Only good thing is that it feels really comfortable in every situation.UPDATE AFTER 5 Months of owning:I don't use it much, but today it broke, after really less usage, it started out with gaps in my music on the right bud then the bud just went.Then later on the day, the other started to gap my music, and went also.Both at the same day went bye-bye, after not much usage, owned about 5 months.My other earphones, priced cheaper, lasted a lot longer than this.It has great sounds and great comfort, but its build quality just sucks.(A lot of people commented/reviewed that JBuds Hi-Fi Noise-Reducing Ear Buds had issues of it going broken within about 3 months of average usage.)I'd say go use the $20 and get a Sony branded earphones instead of this junk.I don't know how to change the stars ratings, but it doesn't deserve a 4/5, it deserves a 3/5 stars.
summary: Updated: ok, but broke in 5 months!

reviewText: I purchased days for my godfather in order to assist him with his work out. He said that they have been great and he hasn't had any problem out of them

My grandaughter had these on her Christmas list and could not decide if she wanted blue or purple; with Amazon's great prices we got both blue and purple.  She will be delighted and I was delighted to find it so easily.

comfortable, 3 sizes of ear thingies come with it, yellow is easy to see when you have mislaid them.  I thinbk the sound quality is good, but my hearing is not, so really I am not the judge of that.  Works for me.

I bought these because I was tired of having my earphones fall out while I was jogging. I was considering buying SkullCandy earbuds, but there was no way I was going to pay $20 for some earbuds. Knowing that I could find a better price on Amazon than in brick and mortar stores, I browsed for awhile before settling on these. There were less than $15 so I was completely happy. The first day I got them, I took them out on my usual run and was pleased by how they fit, but they still seemed a little loose in my ear. Fortunately they include extra silicone tips of various sizes. I put on the largest tip in the packaging and tried them again the next day.This time they seemed to fit just right, but... I noticed that the cord was just way too long. I don't know who they had in mind when they made this cord, but it must be for someone with a really long torso. When you're running, you don't want a long black cord hanging all over the place. It looks ridiculous. Worse yet, after a couple of days the silicone tip had lost it's snug fit and the earbuds were falling out of my ear all over again. I'm irritated. They are good for anything else, but not for what I intended them for, which was RUNNING. So... beware. If you plan on using these while doing any kind of active sport, don't.
summary: Not for use with sports of any kind!!!

reviewText: I like these earbuds, they are affordable, the shipping is good, and they are comfortable with good sound quality. I would recommend this product.

Great headphones for $10, but there is zero sound isolation.  Not very good bass response.  Don't like them enough to do a warranty claim since one of the earbuds failed.  I also have the jbuds J2, i would rather get those instead.

I previously owned the Coby CVE92 earbuds, which I bought on Amazon for $5, and they did a pretty good job.  I was satisfied with them, but after about a year they broke.  This time around I decided to try the JBuds, since they were only $5 more.  As soon as I tried them out, the difference was clear.  The sound quality in the JBuds is significantly better than in the Cobys.  They also come with 3 different sizes of rubber ear pieces, which the Cobys don't.I'm very happy with the decision.  As long as Amazon is selling the JBuds for just $10, if you're trying to decide between them and the Cobys, shell out the extra $5 and get the JBuds.  They're well worth it.  Definitely a great deal.
summary: terrific earbuds, great deal, better than Coby

reviewText: These ear buds have exceeded all my expectations. I was skeptical about ordering a set of in-ear buds because the last pair I purchased were expensive and very uncomfortable (Logitech Ultimate Ears 700.) I decided to give these a shot based on the price ($8.45).Not only are these comfortable enough to wear for a long period of time, but they sound fantastic for the price. In fact, I think they sound better than my Logitech buds, which cost 15x as much. The bass level is very good and the mids and highs are nice and clear. You don't need to shove these into your ear, they sit comfortably without putting any pressure on your ear canal.They block enough ambient noise without completely shutting you out from the world. The cord is a the perfect length. I couldn't be happier with this purchase. I've already ordered 3 more pairs for friends and family.

These sound decent, have a great price but do not cancel much noise. My old pair that broke actually was much more "noise cancelling" than these. If you are looking for something that really cancels noise, I would just get a pair with big rubber grommets that fill your ear canal, they always seem to shut out more noise than anything actually advertised as noise cancelling.
This is a great value for the same cord is a lot more at the big box stores. ok ok

Besides the earbuds that are included with these earphones, I would love them.  They look cool and perform pretty nicely too.  Earbuds are exchangable so this is not a big problem and will differ from person to person, but with any earphone set like this, you need to get a good seal around your ears to get that full sound you want.  Not the most base and not the most treble out there, but great all around set.
Overall reasonably priced.  sound quality is 3 of 5; I would get this if you do not want to spend too much on headphones and yet not get an earphone of bad quality.
I didn't think there was any difference in earphones but these are sooo much better. Good sound ,easy on the ears plus good price.

These are comfortable, inexpensive earbuds. If you need to get the job done and aren't concerned with super-high quality, then these are great. It might be fitting for some to give five stars, but I can't say I love them simply because they're not superb units that an audiophile would love. I use them, they're fine and I would recommend them to someone with similar needs.

I am not an ear bud aficionado like some of the reviews. I bought these to listen to my music while I sand with a Disk Orbital Sander. I really didn't know what to expect as far as the "Noise-Reducing" feature, but here is my observation. With my sander off I can hear someone who is speaking loudly to get my attention. I can also hear them with the sander on just about the same. I don't know how or why it works, but it seems to make all external sounds monotone while my music is on. The music is clear and I do not have to turn it loud to try and compensate for the external noise. It just seems to minimize the loud sounds around me while focusing the music into my ears. As far as durability... I have had these buds yanked out of my ears to hit the floor. They have been dropped. A fan actually fell on them once. They still work as they did out of the box. The Mic thing on it, I only used once and it seemed to work well enough for the people to hear my voice, but I had to hold it near my mouth as opposed to just speaking while it was hanging there. I love these, and when I destroy them I will buy another pair. Hope this review helps you make your decision.

I ordered the ear buds because I needed a new pair and they were a great price.  Was totally surprised when I started using them.  The quality of the sound is fantastic and they do actual reduce the sounds around.  The sound is clear with no static  noted nice stereo sound as well.

My boys are always needing new headphones and I needed something with smaller ear pieces so these worked perfectly for us since you get 2 sets of gel like inserts that are different sizes and the price was good!

I like these for some things, like listening to audio books, or listening to TV shows at the computer when the wife is watching the big TV (both are in the same room).  They are OK for music too, but don't expect high performance like with NuForce - NE-6 ear buds - $39.00 here on Amazon (the extra 30 or so bucks goes a looong way).In their favor, these are one of the more comfortable buds I've owned.  They fit well and do a good job of noise isolation.Overall, I'm glad I bought them. I wear buds -for hours- every day and so these have their place, and the comfort level + price + sound quality = a great deal for modestly performing comfy ear buds.

I'm no audiophile, but I thought for the money, and compared to the junk Apple provides, these were just great. There may be some that a machine has pronounced better, for 3 times the money, but who cares? I want something that stays in (these do) and sounds good (these do) and that doesn't cost more than I paid for the darn Shuttle in the 1st place (these don't). Nuff said.

We got these for our 5 year old daughter to use in the car, but they don't stay in her ears very well. They do come with three different sized buds which was great, but none of them seem to work for her. Nothing wrong with the buds themselves, they might just not work well for younger kids.

These earphones are the best I've ever seen out of all the ones I've purchased.I had it for about two months before the left bud started non-functioning though. (I think because of the long cord I had to constantly untangle it when I stuck it in my pocket)

First and foremost, these are NOT noise cancelling headphones. To technically be noise cancelling they would have to have a small microphone on each side to block out noise. This would also mean they'd require their own power source. However...these are great headphones. I bought them because my ear buds that came with my ipod fall out of my ears...irregularly shaped ears I guess. These though are great and perfectly stay in. They also have great bass. Especially considering the price, they are definately worth it.

I will be getting my 3rd pair.  The Wiring is very thin and over time it will short.  At the moment I only get one channel.  Lifespan for me is about 18 months (Thus my low durability rating).  I really like these for the price.  The sound is excellent for NPR Podcasts.  I do not have any problems listening to music.  I listen to as I walk or shop.  You have to remember to lower the volume as you check out.  Because it is so reasonably priced, it just as easy to replace worth a new purchase.

10 dollars! great ear buds for the price. They aren't prefect and the sound quality isn't the best ever, but these are still very good. I would recommend them to anyone looking for economy ear buds. good deal!

Over the past 2 or 3 years I have purchased several pairs of the JLab JBuds, mostly to use for listening to podcasts/audiobooks while exercising. The low price meant I could easily keep a pair or two at work, in a gym bag, etc. In the past I had been pleased with the quality for price -- good fidelity and tone along with decent ambient noise reduction.About a month ago I ordered two new pairs since the plastic tubing on the old ones was getting stiff. Both pairs have inferior sound quality, quite noticeable in comparison to the old ones with the same audio source. Voices are tinny and distorted enough to make understanding a problem against background noise.Same name, same brand, same look, but very different quality based on my experience.
These ear phones are amazing! Definitely worth the $10!Crisp sound, comfortable and sleek black headphones.Need I say more?This is the best it's gonna get!
I bought them for noise reduction not  quality of sound and they dont do it. Might just as well buy the 99 cent ones

Love these little things.  Sounds good with MP3 player.  Three sizes should fit all.  Comfortable and seem durable.  Have been using them over half a year, walking, school, working out.Update: Cord jack finally gave out after a year.  For the price still not bad.  Trying out Skull Candy earbuds now - will have to see how they compare.

Excellent product! First ear buds which actually stayed in my ears without constant adjustment. They also block out almost all outside noise. Great for airplane travel. Give a major degree of base response. Seems like you have large over the ear headphones on.

Had a cheap pair of Sony (~$15) earbud-style headphones, but accidentally lost them. Bought this one thinking it'd be just as good, but was disappointed. The earbuds themselves are larger and bulkier than they need to be, and the actual covers on this are made of thicker inflexible silicone, so the earbuds fall out easily. On the bright side the covers don't come off as easily, but they're a pain to push back on if they do come off. The 3.5mm jack also isn't right-angled, which increases wear and tear on the cable. In addition, the design of the wire splitter for left and right earbuds doesn't make sense; I'd have preferred a stationary splitter positioned closer to one ear to prevent the wires from getting in the way or needing to adjust the plastic splitter piece.

The title says it all.  If you haven't tried these, you have no idea what your music can really sound like.  Compared to all of the others I've tried, Sony this and that, buds, clipped to outer ear etc, nothing compares to my JBuds!The instant, and I mean INSTANT I put these in, I had a whole new listening experience.  The frequencies these little gems carry is amazing.  I could hear bass like it was meant to be, without having to use any EQ settings.  Wonderful.  On David Beagles classic guitar solo "Joy", it was as if he was in the room with me, I could hear every pick and pluck of every string.  Fantastic.  3 seperate plugs for that perfect fit.  I use the medium and my wife tried them...she needs the small.  Once again, the perfect fit.$20??  Are you kidding me?  3 trips at Starbucks or these fantastic Jbuds you can use next time you're at Starbucks?  Quit spending 2, 3 or 4x more on junk earbuds.Only 4 stars for the fact that there is nothing to carry these extra buds in.  I'm sure they will get lost within a month.  Also like a previous reviewer indicated, only considered noise reducing because the fit and form a seal around your ear.  Nothing high-tech about that.
summary: You have no idea what you are missing in your music until you try these.

reviewText: I bought a pair for less than $7 - it worth it. As usual the cords don't look durable, the length is quite long - it has enough length to attach them to the iMac ( back of the LCD) while sitting behind it on descend distance. Low frequencies are very good if you properly place them into your ears - you can hear the low basslines on dubstep tracks.

These worked well but I haven't tried many out. They come with a few extra ear pieces so I guess that helps customize the fit. I of course didn't know which ones would work best with my ears so I'm just using the default ones and they seem to work fine. They're more comfortable than iPod earphones and I can definitely tell they do have some noise cancellation to them. I've had them for about a month and they've worked well. The chord is a bit long and I don't like that if I drop them and they're completely unwrapped, they'll hit the ground. But the long length can come in handy, like when I'm on the elliptical, it's plenty long with out getting tangled in the machine.All in all I'm very happy with these, although in all fairness I'm no expert and have only tried iPod earphones and over-the-ear noise cancellation earphones in recent years.
summary: Good earphones, but I haven't tried many to compare them to.

reviewText: I wanted this for the gym so I bought it ~$6 knowing I will probably lose it or break it soon. But music via this ear buds is so muffled that everything sounds unclear--haven't been using them at all. Thought it was because I was spoiled by ATH-M50 so I bought a pair of sony for $3 more--I wasn't spoiled! Save your $6 and buy something else--Sony MDR-EX10LP/DBL Earbud Headphones Cobalt Blue or Panasonic RPHJE120K In-Ear Headphone are both better than this.
summary: Sounds are muffled through this ear buds

reviewText: I was looking for good sound and most importantly something that was comfortable at a mid range price. The reviews on these very low cost ear buds were extremely positive so I took a chance. .So far...very acceptable sound, the comfort that I had hoped for and a great value.Unless you want exceptional sound and are willing to pay big bucks, you can't go wrong with these. At this price, if you leave them on a plane, you won't loose any sleep over having to buy another set.Received in retail packaging earlier than expected.
summary: Very good sound and comfort...especially for the low cost.

reviewText: These were beyond my expectations. no distortion. nothing else.... absolutely clean sound was heard.... even at high volume sound didn't get messed.

These are good ear buds and much better then the standard iPod ones. The noise reduction is pretty good as well. I can wear these for a few hours before my ears start getting uncomfortable. With the standard iPod ear plugs my ears would start hurting after 5 minutes.Great for people whose ear plugs keep falling out as these are soft and will stay in comfortably.Best,DG

These are apparently an older model, and therefore priced to move.  They produce decent sound, they stay in my ears, they look good and they effectively cancel out a lot of noise.  I wish the cord was maybe six inches shorter since the length makes them awkward to wear in the gym.  I would definitely buy these again.  Since I use more than one set of headphones, I can't really comment on their durability.
summary: Decent sound quality, really good value

reviewText: Nice sound for the price and much better then what came with my Sansa Clip+.  I had hoped that with 3 different sizes of doohickeys to shove in my ears at least one of them would have stayed put tho.  They stay better than the flat type, but won't stay in if I do a lot of moving around....okay for a stroll, but not for exercising and probably not for jogging.  They might work for someone with a different shaped ear canal then mine.

For under $12, I find these Buds to be very good for the price. I find them to sound as good as my iPod Buds, but more comfortable. They are not quite as good as my Sony Buds. It is a matter of preference, but I prefer these type of buds that go inside the ear. They include 3 different sized silicone tips for a comfortable fit. For the price, I'm very happy.
They sound HORRIBLE. I have several pairs of cheap Walmart / RadioShack ear buds that kick these around the block. You don't even have to wait for shipping, just go to Walmart.
summary: Go to Walmart - they have better

reviewText: Bought those for $10, they do their 10 dollar job... These buds have stronger base then highs.  In general you have to mess with the equalizer to get the sound right when the style of music changes.  Sometimes I love the sound, sometimes hate it - haven't figured out the reason why yet.Lets see how long they last...3  years later. They still work! Still cannot figure out if I like them or not.. But hey, get alive, these are $10 year buds, all right...
These buds were a great purchase for the price and I went back and bought another pair too.  Sound is good, not exceptional, but certainly justified by the low price.

Just terrible. I know it was cheap but I was expecting a little more. The sound quality is horrible, reminded me of the free headphones you get on airplanes when you purchase the in flight movie. Do not buy.

I got these earbuds as a replacement for the crappy earbuds that Apple provides with its iPods.  These earbuds feel cheap and makes an annoying sounds when you move it around in your ear.  However, it gets the job done and if you need a backup set, these are good for the price.

Ok, so this is my first purchace just for in-ear earbuds.  They are comfortable.  I have used this type of earbud before and remember my ears being in pain or tender after using them.  These are pretty comfortable for being stuck in my ear for so long.  These earbuds are good overall.  I recommend them, especially if you have some garbage earbuds now.  Sound quality is the best I've had, but I haven't heard the top of the line or anything.  That is all from me. The cord is long like a day at work with no work to do.  Ok not that long, but for earbuds they are pretty long.
summary: I bought two and wished I bought more.

reviewText: Okay sound, cheap earbuds.  If you are delicate with the earbuds they can last about a year.  This is the reserve pair when you break your everydays.
summary: Earbuds, you can never have enough.

reviewText: For the price they work good, I use a paper clip  and attach the cord to my shirt neck line. There light and have 3 pairs of rubber ear buds.

JLabs has a more expensive set of earbuds but I find that the sound is the same.  So, if money is a concern, these work just as well.  I don't listen to loud music to save my precious ears, so maybe at high volume the more expensive pair might be better.  But I'm completely happy with these.  Three different sizes of rubber covers so the small ones fit my petite body and stay in my ears.
summary: Lesser expensive pair but same sound. Petite women-small size rubber cover works!

reviewText: While they don't compare to my $600 Shure, they are a good improvement over the ones that come with most MP3 players and work well if you want to sleep with them on.

The comfort of these buds exceeded my expectations.  They come with three different sized covers to help get that perfect fit. Previously to buying these, I was needed an over-the-ear device to keep my other buds in place, especially during workouts.  I don't need to do this with the J-Buds.The wires to these buds are longer than my previous pair.  I like this as it gives me more diversity.The sound is decent. I don't hear anything buy my music. No background noises and this took me some time to get used to.I bought these in pink. I live in a household of males and this is the only way that keeps someone else from taking my stuff!!  The color is more purple than pink but it still works in warding off "borrowers".Overall a great purchase.  A new model has been released so I was able to get these for under nine dollars so I really can't complain about these buds.Excellet price point. Above average performance. Worth buying, even if it's to have an extra pair on hand.

I usually wear the "Medium" size covers for other earbuds but medium felt big for these so I switched to the small ones. I wore them on a flight I took 3 days ago and can still feel like they stretched something in my ear. It even hurts to sleep on my side at night because they did something to my ear.The sound quality is ok but nothing special and definitely not worth the discomfort.
summary: Wore them 3 days ago. My ear still hurts.

reviewText: These are great ....I use them all the time and this brand is the one I like the best. Great for the price.....
summary: Would recommend this brand if you need ear buds....

reviewText: These have been great 10 headphones.  I use them on my motorcycle.  Can keep the volume much lower and they dont fall out when putting on my helmet.  They dont reduce wind noise as much as i was hoping but it does cut it - not all bad since then i can hear traffic a bit.

What junk. The first pair I received, only 1 earbud worked. I returned it for an exchange. The second pair I received worked for about a month and now the same problem happened. Only this time I can't return them because return time ran out about a weak ago. So in conclusion, if you like earbuds that one side goes in and out with static noise, then this is for you, otherwise stay away unless you like throwing $$$ away.Update:I'm giving 50% apologies to the vendor. Although the first pair did not work 100% (even when moving the chord), the second pair (replacement)may work. I bought more headphones (earbuds) and same problem. It has to be my sansa clip 4+ mp3 player. I'm going through the process with them for a replacement.

I read through most of the reviews of this product before I bought them and almost did not buy due to some of the complaints that I read.I am so glad I didn't listen to those reviews!I am no audiophile but I do like music.  I use these with my Sandisk Sansa m250.  They work great.  I don't understand the reason behind people complaining about the sound quality?  If you really want amazing sound quality, why are you buying $20 ear buds??The sound is more than fine for me.  I use them for running both outside and at the gym.  I have had to adjust my running style outside when using these outside due to they do cancel out almost all outside noise!  not a problem when running on a hiking trail, but if running on the streets, I can't hear cars coming up behind me when I have these on.I have used them for runs that have lasted over an hour several times.  My ears have never hurt, these were comfortable from the first time I put them in my ears.  They do not fall out when I wipe sweat like my others seem to do.Overall, I am very happy with these earphones!!

I got better sound quality from a pair or earbuds that came with my Gilette razor blade refil a few years ago.  These are tinny, no bass to speak of,and none of the rubber ear pieces fit my ears right.  I'm quite disappointed.  Maybe the best things in life are free.  Back to the drawing board.

These are good quality headphones for an inexpensive price.  I dropped the device they were plugged into and broke the jack off the headphones, so I have ordered a second pair.  With the distance of the fall I don't think many headphones would have survived intact.  User error not manufactures defect.

I have had to use several different types of earphones/earplugs over the years. Both outside the ear and inside the ear canal. Muff type and very soft make fit with heat and time. I have had time that the use of a headphone /earplug for times at hours and days. This is a case of shoulda, coulda, woulda. I would have and could have and now should have bought this particular earplug a long time ago. Dang I should have bought these at least ten years before they came out. Why you ask now? I love these earplugs. Knowing what I know now. I would have paid five times as much as they are asking for them. Even at that they would have been cheap. Every once in a while when I run into something like this. I just wish I had been able to purchase these ten twenty or even five years ago. These are so good you will wish you had them at least ten seconds before you get them. Like I say you will take them anytime you can get them but the sooner the better.I can not believe they are that cheap. They have to be the best value for anyone wishing to listen to almost anything. The one thing I can not make a point to listen to is music. Even if and when I listen to music I could not give a clue as to how well they work for music. Why you may ask? I have shot so many weapons or been around so many violent explosions that I do not have that much left in the way of good hearing. Still I love these earphones.It just does not get any better than these are.dray

So if you think the IPOD ear phone is cheaply made, wait till you see this one. While the sound is alright but the plastic of the "buds" is really flimsy and the wire used is of cheap material. The so called noise reduction feature is no more than the soft rubber tips of the ear buds which block off some outside noise. also if u buy it and intend to use on running - DON'T as you will hear the clicking noise caused by the wire hitting the inside of the hollow shell of the ear phones when you run and it can be louder than your music !!
Good quality sound - especially good base frequencies - and good isolation from external noise.  Comfortable to wear.

I was a bit skeptical about the quality of sound at first, but either the sound has gotten better (through breaking in) or I have become more accustomed to it.  I really like them now, and I especially like the fact that I haven't paid a fortune for them.  They fit snugly and comfortably in my ears.  No complaints.
Not for audiophiles, but these are good earphones and good value for your money.  The extra sizes included are also a nice bonus.

The good news is that these earbuds sound pretty good.  Because they come with several different sizes of soft rubber earpieces, they are more comfortable than the buds shipped with most players.The bad news is that these buds do nothing to reduce sound.  If you are planning on using them on the bus, for instance, you will find that background noise is no different from using the usual cheap phones.Construction on these is really flimsy.  The cord is the thickness of a piece of embroidery thread.  With daily use, I don't expect them to last much more than a month.For comparison, I have previously used theShure E2c Sound Isolating EarphonesandKoss SPARKPLUG - Stereo In Ear Ear Plugsphones.  Both provided far superior noise reduction; the Shure qualify as a deluxe set of earplugs, very nice on airplanes.  The Shure provided much better sound quality, the Koss was about the same sound quality.  Both were better construction (though both were still broken within a year).  The Koss was about equally comfortable; the Shure was much more comfortable, due both to better design and a wider selection of earpieces.  Currently Amazon is listing the Koss for $13 and the Shure for about $70. Both are better buys.
The sound is fine, but these earbuds refuse to stay in my ears at all. I've used other earbuds with no problems, but these won't stay put, even when I'm not doing anything active.
This is an OK set of headphones.  Noise reduction works well, sound is mediocre with almost no bass.  Not horrible for a cheap set of headphones.
I've been happy with these since I got them. They're well-balanced and they don't really have any levels where they are weak. Great product.
These are awesome! Sound is amazing! Drowns out everthing else. And they're comfortable. You don't even know they're in!! They're nice and soft. Get em, you won't be disapointed!
plug em in mp3 player, put other end in ear, hear music, nothing fancy, cheaply made, sound quality mediocre, price ok

These are a good deal for the money. Sound is quite decent, and they're very comfortable. The cord is way too long for use w/an Ipod Nano on your arm, so be aware of that; I wrap it around the nano to keep it out of the way, but it's a bit horsey. The noise cancelling is not great with these, but it's OK. I use them in a pretty loud health club, so wish they were better at keeping out the outside noise. Nice that they come in white or black. Overall, I recommend.

I wanted a ear phone with mic. This has good price and meets the criterion. The sound is good but it seems just a tad below Panasonic RPHJE120D. Nevertheless, I believe this product gives good value. My only complaints is the in-ear design. The soft plastic cover does not extend to cover the hard plastic edge. As such, when you push this in your ear, the soft part may wrinkle to expose the hard edge, which causes discomfort when it rubs against your ear.

These headphones are so cheap and are so much better than the standard ipod headphone, better than headphones costing five times as much. Having said that, they are somewhat 'disposable.' The wiring in mine lasted for eight months before working loose. It is more expensive to send them back for warranty replacement, so I didn't bother. If you are thinking of buying, buy a couple (at $11, why not?)I did fix mine, it's not too hard if you have a scalpel, a soldering iron, some heat-shrink, and some patience.Update: I received an email from JLabs, and they are sending me a free replacement - you can't beat that customer support.
summary: Great, but weak wiring, excellent customer support

reviewText: Sound is adequate for the price and the different size ear pieces really help with smaller ears.I would not expect these to last that long but for the price you could buy several pair and have them as a good back up.
Sound quality is about the same as the original ear phone came from the MP3 player, but not as comfortable as the original one.
summary: Not as comfortable as other reviewer said

reviewText: I have used these regularly since purchasing them, and they are very comfortable. They also have good sound considering their small size.

I purchased these 'phones because of the high reviews.  They are decent, but in my opinion not worth the hype.First off, do not expect them to be "noise canceling" in any shape or fashion.  Even "noise reducing" may be a bit of a misnomer.  Noise reduction is only the result of how far you can jam them in your head.The sound quality is okay.  There is no bass to speak of and the sound is pretty tinny, but that is really to be expected in 'phones at this price point.  I hate to say it but my super cheap Sony MDR-E828LP earbuds sound better.  There is also no carrying case so you'll have to figure out some other way of storing and managing the cord.I do like that the cord is of equal length from each bud.  They are also quite comfortable.Overall I probably would not purchase them again, but I guess I should not have expected as much from such cheap earbuds.
You can here music on them and their worth the buy ;) they can definitely improve the style and appearance of the headphone and the cord feels a cheap...
These are just as good as Sony or Apple and definitely better than the Panasonic ear buds that are on here, they have good base, easy to change the ear lobes pieces; a bang for your buck.
Very bass heavy, I had to turn up the treble on the equalizer to get something approximating normal sound. Still a far shout better than stock iPod earbuds, though, and very comfortable in the ear.

I love these headphones. However they only last so long. I am able to listen to headphones while at work so I used these headphones Mon-Fri. I've purchased these headphones 4 times now in the last 2 years. So that means I have to replace them every 6 months or so. While I do cringe when they go bad, I realize the alternative of buying something at similar price at Walmart just isn't worth it. For $10, purchasing this product on Amazon is worth it. Once you plug them in, no one else can hear the music. They are a good fit and are extremely loud. This is as good as headphones get. I don't care if my next set goes out in 2 months, I will still buy another.
summary: Last about 4-5 months with every day use

reviewText: For $10, you can't beat them, however, don't be expecting GREAT sound.  While these do beat out the iPod ear buds, they aren't as good as the Skullcandy Titans (See my review there) I bought at the same time.  I figured for how cheap these were, I would give them a shot.  Might as well have an extra pair of decent buds in case I lost or broke my other ones.  The tips aren't as soft as other silicon tips I have tried, so they don't make a great seal in my ears.  Maybe with some Comply foam tips these will be better.  Even so, when I do get them sealed, their range of sound is just OK.  There isn't much on the bass end, but the mids and highs are decent.  They sound pretty good and higher volumes without a terrible amount of distortion.  Again, these are just above average sound quality, but they will beat out the ear buds that come with any MP3 player.  I can't say much of the noise reduction as these didn't seal in my ear 100%, but they did do more than traditional buds.

I just received these ear buds and I am quite disappointed. I do not expect these to last very long at all. The sound is not the problem for me, it's just that it seems to be of poor quality materials. The cord itself is very, very thin so it's already apparent that the wiring is not very well protected. When I put the plug into my iPod if I even slightly twist the plug while it is in the jack I will get a lot of static. Not worth $20.
They were ok, but they broke much to quickly. They are cheap, so I didn't have high expectations, but they broke within 2 weeks.
summary: They were ok, but they broke much to quickly ...

reviewText: I had to replace my very awesome Logitech's and decided to try these reasonably priced buds.  The sound is passable, but they provide little to no noise reduction.  I work in 'cubeville' and don't like to hear my neighbors...I could clearly hear voices and keyboard strokes with the music volume set at a comfortable level.  These will be going back...  Friend at work loaned me their Tweaked Classic earbuds - incredible sound for 19.95 via tweaked.com. Save your money folks.

These JLabs JBuds things are terrible, I'm so disappointed. I'm no audiophile but I'm afraid these are hopeless.I just wanted a pair of cheap noise-reducing buds for listening while working in the yard but I didn't want to spend a bucketload on them, my buds disappear every few months (with my 3 teenagers helping, no doubt). I didn't think they could be all that bad, they're JLabs after all, and my old cheapo JLab J2s were a favorite. Unfortunately the J2s has been discontinued, so I got these based on the price and JLab's reputation.They're tinny, buzzy, muddy, all the adjectives you can think of to trash listening gear; the cord is short and plastic, and too stiff. The throw-away buds that came with my MP3 player have better sound. I wore them for a bit trying to think of positive things to say; the only plus I can come up with is that they fit well, and sound isolation is fair.I say these are a solid "don't buy" at any price. Check out the Monoprice 109927, the Panasonic RPTCM125K, the Sony MDR-EX37B;  sure they're 2-3X the price, but you won't regret the few extra dollars once you hear these JBuds.  I feel like I just paid the idiot tax.....
These were a great deal for the price but the complaint I got from my boyfriend was that they don't stay in his ears when he's working out... I had to get him new ones in the end.

These headphone are horrible. Sounds like an old gramophone from the 80's. No bass, no clarity and clear communication.It's definitely one of those .50 cent products mass made in China with a 1000% margin on it. Stay away, invest a bit more and get the cheapest skull candy or sony instead.

Very nice quality, definitely will buy again.I use these for jogging since sweat and moisture usually kill all of my earbuds after some time.This is a very inexpensive option and they sound very nice.
summary: Great ear buds for the price!

reviewText: These headphones are horrible and poor quality. I have only had mine for 3 months, and they are already broken. I get no sound out of the left ear now. The cord is so long that it is simply impossible for it not to get tangled or become a nuisance. I had gotten these headphones precisely because the ones that came with my ipod were not working well and the left ear plug produced no sound. Now, I have the same problem with these.By contrast, I got my wife the Coby CVE92 Isolation Stereo Earphones, which is cheaper, has better sound, and still works.

I have just received this product and trashed a nearly-new Ear Bud set from Bose (at ca. USD100.) This product (at USD13.) has considerably better performance and infinitely greater comfort than its Bose counterpart. I am absolutely pleased and amazed. (N.B. A few hours of "burning in" may be required in order to reach the full audio potential, however)

I bought these for my son in mid July 2008. He was happy with the sound, saying sound was much better than from the ones that came with his Ipod. Unfortunately, the left ear bud just stopped working about a month ago(November). Many other reviewers seem to have had the same problem, so it's hard to recommend them for that reason. Otherwise, I would say the sound is pretty good for the price. They come with a one year warranty so I just emailed the manufacturer. Too soon to tell if I will get a replacement.**Update July 2009 - A couple of weeks after posting my original review, I received an email from the company apologizing for not responding to my email sooner and offering me a replacement. I received a new pair within a week orf responding to them and so far, they are still working well.

I bought these to match my metallic cover and these are NOT metallic painted as it looks in the picture. Now I have to order a different pair and it is ending up costing me twice as much due to the innaccurate photo representation. Not happy about this.

Although I was mistaken when I grabbed these and put them in my pocket, thinking they were my original Samsung headphones that came with my NOTE 2, only to realize once I put them on and the sound was like listening through a tin can that they were not the correct ones. My friend ordered these as a replacement for her iphone and quickly ordered the Original iphone ones after listening through them only to leave them sitting on the table for me to grab.  They are now in the bottom of my bag as an absolute emergency pair!
summary: They look good but sound like crap

reviewText: I tried these twice and both times I had a single ear bud that went out after 4-8 months. Great product if it worked.

I bought these expecting something decent but not spectacular, which is exactly what I got.  They are both Comfortable & have good noise reduction but there is something to be desired sound wise (particularly highs in my opinion).
Purchased three months ago.  They work well, but the insulation on the wires cracked on both earbuds and at the minijack.  Still working, but just a matter of time now until they are dead.
I thought they would be better but they weren't. Find others at the same price that are better than this one.

These headphones were recommended by Cnet not to mention several other reviews that I read on Amazon which led me to believe that these would be a viable alternative to my Zune Premium in-ear buds (which sounded PERFECT). Boy was I disappointed!! The largest ear mushrooms are barely adequate to keep the buds from falling out of my ears. And the sound is absolutely terrible! It sounds like a horrible monotone alarm clock radio. They're loud, no doubt but the sound quality is below bad. Now I'm stuck with these cheap decroded pieces of crap until my replacement Zune Premium headphones arrive. I should have ordered those in the first place but I am in Iraq and don't want to mess up a "good" pair of headphones. Stay away from Jbuds.

The Panasonic earbuds was 10x better than these poor excuse for headphones. Audio is dry. I had to throw these away immediately, I couldn't even work out with them. Every time I took them out of my ears, the rubber buds stayed stuck in my ears. Not worth your money. And if you're intent to buy these b/c of the microphone, please don't. All commands you wish to speak can be done with your fingers faster than repeating them twice. Would not recommend these at all.

After paying $80 for overrated Apple Earphones (the exterior peeled off), I ended with Jbuds as it was more durable (2nd purchase) . I didn't buy it for sound quality (needed for gym use) and the fact that we needed it cheap. I would suggest trying other brands like sony for value for money.
summary: Better than $80 Apple Earphones but Sony Earphones are the best value

reviewText: Not only does the music sound clear and crisp coming through them but for the first time my ears do not hurt.  Now when I exercise I am no longer adjusting the ear piece and switching them from ear to ear because of my discomfort.  Most importantly when I have the volume on low and the music still comes through clearly and I know I am not hurting my hearing. Whenever I wore an ear piece in the past I worried about the possible damage done to my hearing and with these, not an issue!!Highly recommend these on all levels!!!!Quality , price....  GREAT!!!!!

Love these JBuds. They fit so well and listening is a pleasure when the buds are not constantly falling out or hurting the inside of my ear.The music sounds great.The fact that they come with three different sized  ear bud covers is such a thoughtful designer touch.Very good produc for the price.
But then I was liberated of them so I can't tell you about the longevity.  They fit snug, cancel out background noise and were comfortable to wear.
summary: They worked fine on the test run

reviewText: I purchased two of these for my sons' Christmas gifts. They use them with their tablets. I can't hear anything coming from them (besides their off key singing every now and then) and they apparently can't hear me either, considering how many times I have to go tap them, lol. Works well and has held up to their roughhousing!

I read a lot of reviews concerning this product and bought one. It's good in reducing noise, but made me sick to my left ear and stopped using it. If anyone has this kind of experience please let others know.

This is my third pair of JBuds ear buds and I always have a backup pair on hand.  Although I tried and like the Coby Stero Earphones, I stand by JBuds and would recommend them.  Good price, speedy delivery, and a great product.

Bought 12/17/2009I have been using the Coby earphones ($5) for a year now and I've gotten tired of changing them every 3-6months. So after my 3rd Coby gave out, I decided to try this item out.Look : First impressions, they look  almost identical to the Coby's but they have 2 more extra earpieces (small & large). The cord is a little flimsy (no complaints here since these are cheap) but the part where the cord connects to the jack looks very vulnerable and soft. If the earpieces get snagged (which happens with me a lot of times), I feel this part would give out. THe Coby's jack is L-shaped so if the wires get snagged, it takes a little stress off the jack/cord connection.Sound : Here is where I got disappointed. While the audio quality is good, its not as good as the Coby's. I tested both earphones side by side (The Coby's Right earpiece still works) and the difference is big. Jbuds did give a clear crisp sound but lacks the Bass sound which makes the sound fuller. Coby's has good Treble & Bass ranges and you can even hear the tiniest sound (from shakers or maracas or tambourines). IN some acoustic songs, the Jbuds lost the tiny background sounds (tambourines, etc as mentioned). I'm particular of those small background instruments since they give the song "that feeling." I tested both on acoustic, hiphop, RnB, rock, dance, trance songs and the Cobys sound better hands down. Dance tracks & HIphop where the bass is more prominent sounds better with the Cobys.Bottom line : If you want better sound (and can handle changing your earbuds every 3-6 months (The last one I have lasted 6mo. and all 3 Cobys lost sound on one side only) go for the COBYs. They sound good I still keep the old ones, cut-off the non-functioning side, & use it while sleeping. :) If you want an ok sound, go with the Jbuds since I read they have a 1-year warranty (without shipping charge) so your money is safe for a year.UPDATE: 6/10/2010My earbuds finally quit working so i emailed them about it. They sent me a replacement immediately & I got it in no time. Maybe the production has improved over the months but the new ones that i got sound waaaay better than the ones I've had. I'm updating it to 4 stars for great customer service & good product!UPDATE: 12/27/2011My Jbuds finally died. The replacement they sent me lasted about 1yr. and 6 months. The replacement sounded better and I have come to love my Jbuds. For $5, I got a quality product with quality sound. I am updating it to 5 Stars!
summary: JBuds Hi-Fi Ear Buds  VS  Coby CVE92 Earphones

reviewText: It is the cheapest earphone I could find, and it suits my need of listening to audio books.  The sound quality is good to me but I am not very picky.  The volume is high, which is important to me because I listen to it while walking on streets.I don't see how "noise reduction" works.  Perhaps it means the earbuds fit so well the noise is blocked.  Anyway it is not significantly more effective than other products.Now I need to see how long will the wires last.  My previous headphones all broke because of the wires.Added 1 year later: Yes the wires break off easily as other headphones I used.  The lifetime is 6 month roughly.  But before I can find a better alternative, I am still buying it...Added in 2013: My second set of ear buds broke again after 6 months of use.  Again, cable is the problem; again, this is common to all earbud products.  .  However, the product came with a one-year warranty.  And it is surprisingly easy to claim.  Just go on to their website, click the warranty claim button, enter the serial number of the bud (printed on a card that came with the bud), type in your home address.  Two days later, a new set showed up at my door.  Great service, JLAB!

The earbuds sound good and actually fit my ears comfortably. I only wish some company would offer replacement covers since these will eventually wear out. I may just buy a cheap set and use those covers. These earbuds don't completely block noise but for me that is a good thing since I do need to be in some contact with my environment for safety reasons. I use them with my new Nano and am completely pleased with my purchase.

I bought a blue pair of the same kind which I rather liked but my hubby nicked them (like 2 years ago). So I got a pink pair a few weeks ago.I could almost swear that they are different models. The new ones give off a kind of fuzzy/cottoney sound which I just cant get used to.However, for a very cheap pair of earphones, they do the job better than most.

I bought this product months ago and one channel failed.  It was past the amazon replacement period but there was a 1 year warranty. I didn't have receipt or any other documentation. I emailed the company with my amazon receipt in the body of the email. In less then a hour I recieved an email back saying they would send me a new pair. That was on a thursday. Monday I received the new earbuds -- WOW !! I would reccomend buying the case, sold by the company, to keep your buds blooming.

Bought this for the gym to use while watching news and sports. The buds are OK. But reception is hit and miss. Lose signal completely. More frustrating than anything else. Got so bad I don't even use the radio anymore. The original phones were good, but cumbersome in the gym. Buds work better than phones,  but not these. Bought again for the price, it was a sellout at half price, and got burned once again. Save your money!
These where a cheap pair of ear buds.  They're not comfortable.  Sounds decent.  Can't really expect to much from these. They are just OK.
summary: You get what you pay for

reviewText: Opened up the package, plugged them into my SanDisk Sansa and only heard sound out of one ear bud. What I did hear sounded good and maybe that one bud gets 5 stars but the other bud gets 1 star, so I guess it averages out to 3 stars. I guess for this price you cant expect great quality control. Overall I do like how they look and fit and one bud did sound pretty good.
Very cheap ear buds means you get what you pay for.All I want is sound to go to my ears. If that's all you want, then get this now.

This is the second pair of these headphones I've purchased. The first set was decent, not perfect by any means, but ok for the price. The connector broke after a few months, but I'm willing to give them credit and assume it was due to my handling of them instead of a product fault. The replacement set I ordered, however ... complete junk. Sounded terrible. I thought they might need some burn in first but after many days of listening, no better at all. Sounds like you are down a well. I tried the different ear pieces in case that was the problem but no improvement. One good pair, one awful pair, not risking this purchase again. Much happier with a Panasonic set that even cost less.

These stay in my ears, I don't have to turn my mp3 player up as loud when I use these.  They come with 3 different size rubber covers and that has made a big difference in comfort for me.  The rubber covers weren't easy to get on but they are worth it!  I have great sound now.

I use these earphones during my workout.  I tend to really sweaty and these for the most part stay in my ear.  Though at times they do slip out from the moisture, it doesnt happen too often.  It does come with replacement buds or an alternate size bud.  I replaced the larger ones with the smaller ones after a while and its more comfortable and fits better.Con: For some reason these dont work on my iphone5s.  It worked on my iphone4.  I dont know if its the audio jack on my new phone or if they r just not compatible.
Stay away and buy something else!! These things sound like they are under water! Kids headphones are better than these things.

My first time with earbuds. Therefore I may not be knowledgable with how to use them. They come out too easily, especialy when eating something, plus I thought they would reduce outside noise a little. As I wanted them when mowing the lawn?

I was shopping for ear buds since my puppy decided the ones I had would make a great snack.  Came across these ones for seven bucks.  Thought I'd try 'em and see if they worked.  Was somewhat skeptical.  Not any more!  These things work really well, and I'm impressed.  The puppy ate my 40 dollar ear buds.  These work just as well.  Don't waste your money on those expensive ear buds unless you want to impress someone!
i bought one before this one, can't remember which, but i noticed that the sound is kinda fuzzy on this one in comparisonalso, i've had problems since day one with one sounds louder than the other
I am on my second pair of buds, my first lasting me about 6 years.  Good sound, good fit, and inexpensive.

I ordered a pair 3 months ago and they were great. They came in black plastic packaging.I recently ordered the same exact pair that came in a silver and white package. There is a difference in sound quality between the two. The one from the white package sounds muffled while the ear buds from the black packaging are clear/crisp. SEE UPDATEThere is a noticeable difference between the two pairs despite being the same color.I will do a burn in and see if that is the problem. JLab's claims process seems pretty easy so far. I'll update later on how it goes.UPDATE: Burn in has helped a bit but still a little muffled. Jlab's warranty support was great though and they sent me a free pair to replace the suspect pair within a week. The new pair sound fine.
summary: First pair was great. Second pair sound horrible

reviewText: The sound quality isn't great, but it's fair enough for the price.The construction seems a bit chintsy - plastic-y, but they've actually been fairly sturdy. Again, for the price, you can't expect too much more.At least it's not the funky cord style like the sony fontopias. Decent length, too.
It has been about 3 months since I bought this product. Now only one piece is working the other one is broken already.

I highly recommend these ear buds.  The sound quality is great! I was surprised due to the sale price because I recently purchased ear buds from Walmart for $10, they were lacking in sound performance and after about 2 months one side quit working.  I am very impressed so far, the only slight issue is, I wish they were a little more comfortable, they are the standard ear buds with the replacement sizes.

As the title states, these headphones are decent overall.For the price that you're paying, I wouldn't expect too much.I randomly got two pairs of JBuds in my JLab Grab Bags.Quite honestly, I was expecting more from JLab. I have always liked their products. However, I have purchased only some of their more expensive sets.It was interesting to listen to their cheapest offering. The JBuds aren't horrible, but they definitely won't go very far.If you're looking for a cheap pair of headphones less than $10, I may consider these.They're cheap enough to knock around and to just use as a pair of beater headphones.
summary: Decent. Won't blow you away though.

reviewText: dollar store item, cheap plastic and poor sound, even you know you are getting what you paid for, still, you would feel like you have paid too much for this cheap budnot even worth to return, my mistake to hit on a deal and fooled by the stock image
summary: very cheap and dollar item, do not waste your money even it is not alot

reviewText: I bought these and they broke a couple a months later. One of the little speakers just stopped completely. The sound was not impressive at all, you're better off buying really cheap ones for [...] bucks.

I bought these mainly to cancel out noises while I'm working out and use them also to zone out alot of noise at the bowling alley.  I was skeptical at first but after having them for the past two weeks find that they are indeed a noise-reducing product and have good quality sound.  I would recommend this for recreational music listening use.
I have tried many head phones and this one is the best of all. Very nice quality and durable. I like it and going to order one more for spare. Just go for it!!!!!

Timely delivery.  Excellent comfortable fit it the ears.  Top sound quality.  I enjoy classical music and they deliver as if I were at a live performance..  Pleased that I bought two sets.  Highly recommended.

great full sound, very comfortable. these are great earbuds, and i dont like earbuds! just love them! nice having a choice of size, for that just right fit. these donot cancel all outside noise, but for my use that is a benefit. thank you j tech for such a great product!

I've been through 2 Sony ones, 1 panasonic, 1 Denon within 2 years.They are all above $20 ranges.  Denon being $60.Personally like the Sony's sounds the best, but not durable at all.Denon, more durable but expensive and sound isn't up to par with its price.However, this JBud for a sub $10 earbud, is very durable and sound is very decent as well.Highly recommend!!!

Bought two sets because they were cheap and my kids lose them all the time.  First pair were crackly sounding and the left side stopped working completely within the hour.  The second set is working okay.  They sound surprisingly good and the inclusion of smaller rubber tips made them fit my 9 year olds ears better.  For that and the incredibly low price, I give them 3 stars.Amazon gave me an instant refund for the defective pair.  Cool.
Dead on arrival. I tried it on several different devices that otherwise functioned. (win7 PC front/rear ports, mp3 player, kindle fire) Didn't bother refunding.

I use earbuds daily: working out & studying.  Bought a few different buds from walmart and target but the selection/quality has always been a disappointment.Only had these for a few days but heres the run down.1/28/12----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Daily use:  Typical use is: 4-6 hours A DAY. (study/exercise)Comfort:  5/5  These fit really well, and surprisingly doesn't come loose when I run either (5k on a track) or when I do ballistic motions like box jumps.Quality:  4/5  These aren't some $200 3D surround sound nonsense buds, but they sound dang good.Length:  Ample. I can easily plug it into my EVO 3D and place it in my front pocket without creating tension on the wire.Comments;  I think you'll be hard-pressed to find a better bang for your buck.  Some customers had ordered these for $20 but for $9 with free 2 day shipping, how can you go wrong?

Consider the Panasonic Earbuds because these were a bunch of tweeters going off in your ear basically as I compared it to my Ipod touch earphones. My Panasonic earbuds for 6 bucks is on par with my ipod earphones but these JBuds were a bunch of tweeters. Not recommended for music but maybe for other stuff like listening to the radio or watching a movie or audiobook or something. If your looking for that head knocker if you know what I mean just don't depend on the this one to provide you with it. Im sticking with the Panasonic for Now.

I got the zen stone plus and wanted better ear buds and the sony font pods that were with my ipod were way better it had higher trebble(sp) and better base (thumping sound) the price is cheap but the pods dont do it just maybe its the zen stone but same songs on the ipod with sony font pods sounded much better. In an attempt to make it sound better the EQ does help but not much.  And you turn it up higher trying to make is sound crisper and better, but they are so so review for me...
They are slightly uncomfortable, offer you no way to regulate the volume but they are shiny. Big ones hurt my head, these are slightly better than airplane sets but not much.
summary: It goes in your ears meh

reviewText: Great quality! Great sound! Very durable and feel great in my ears. I bought then last year, I guess, and they are still in great shape. I use then everyday. Thank you!

I bought a pair of Sony Fontopia with a 3.5 star rating and loved them.  Then saw these Jbuds with an even better rating so naturally thought that they would be better.  How dissapointing!  The sound quality is very poor in comparison.  Dont waste your money even if it has been discounted.  Not sure what the other reviews were using as a benchmark when rating this item but I had a direct comparison with the equivalent Sony Fontopia.
summary: Dissapointed in the performance of these

reviewText: Got these headphones for a great price. They also block out other sounds. Buds are great headphones if you looking to listen to music and drown out the world around you.

Awesome headphones. I love these guys and have been using them for about 6 months now.  Their sound is impeccable, and are extremely comfortable, I wear them while studying I mean like 8-10 hours a day, and never really notice them.  I wouldn't say that these are actually noise cancelling via electrical interference, its more via sound muffling than anything, but don't misinterpret, with the sound at a medium volume you will kill all but the loudest ambient noise. I highly recommend these.  Flat out the best $20 I have EVER spent.
summary: Wonderful - best $20 headphones you can buy

reviewText: I do not hear any difference from these Earbuds than any prior ones I have used.  I think JBuds are over rated by the manufacturer and other buyers.
Like a tin can on a string. Very little bass response. Fortunately they were not very costly. I have had good luck with Sony earbuds.

These earbuds are the exact same as the Coby CVE92 Isolation Stereo Earphones. same design (identical), same sound, only these have a higher price. Wish I would have just paid to get a higher end nice pair. Save your money in the end these are just so so.

I like these buds for the price. Please note the price is the big factor for these buds. The sound and the isolation is not exceptional but they are better than what might be expected for the price. If your looking for great sound and great isolation keep looking. If your looking for good buds at a great price these are good buds that are comfortable, stay in your ear, are easy to sleep with and generally very comfortable.

I like these headphones for the price. The sound was pretty decent. The only thing that would make it convenient is to have some sort of way to tell which one was for the left ear and which one for the right; both are the same so something like a slight color difference or some sort of indentation to tell them apart would have been helpful. The other thing is that the adapter that plugs into the MP3 device is straight as opposed to having a 90 degree angle. This straight connector makes it snag clothing and other items in the pocket in addition to this also seems to make it more prong to be damaged. Other than that, I would buy this product again.
