summary: Good headphone & good sound. Worth the price.

reviewText: The head phone are very good you don't hear much nosie & its a nice fit. Its worth the value.

I will not even take this if it's free.  The sound of this ear buds is just like scratching an iron roof.  It will definitely hurt your ears by the sound it produced.  You will regret this if you buy it.  It's your choice.
The buds sound great for less than $10. The only problem I have is that there is no clip to prevent the buds from tangling. Did not have to use customer service so I can't really speak to that.
summary: Good sounding buds...no clip to stop them from getting tangled though

reviewText: I had tried several types of earbuds for the mp3 players that I have.  Nothing fitted well enough for me to enjoy the music.  The earbuds which came with the players were too large, wouldn't stay in my ears and hurt.  I tried several types of headphones and earphones, but nothing gave me the sound I liked, or just weren't comfortable.  When I purchased the Jbuds, I was completely satisfied, and haven't looked at any other earphones.  They fit comfortably, and the sound is really great.  Admittedly, I am not an audiophile, but what I hear with these earbuds is totally satisfying to me.  I would purchase them again and I would recommend them to others.

If you're looking to spend ten or twelve bucks, then these are a great buy for that price range.  They fit ok, very comfortable, come with three size adjustments.  Cord is adequately long (roughly 4 feet).  Noise reduction depends on how well they fit in your ear - they fit/seal very well in mine.  Durability:  they're cheap;  I don't expect them to last more than a year or two.  Sound quality is good, for a ten dollar unit.  Surprisingly decent bass; but don't expect to find the same quality of a twenty, thirty, or fifty dollar pair.
summary: You get what you pay for

reviewText: I listen to books all the time and go through ear buds.  They break or stop working.  These are rugged and of good quality.

These are by far the best headphones I have ever owned. Granted, I never spend more than $40 for a set, but these have a sound quality that was better than that of any other set I have owned or used. If you are looking for a good, cheap, pair of isolation headphones, these are the best.

I needed an extra pair of headphones for work. These are comfortable (the buds are soft), well priced, and come with extra buds (small, med, large). But the sound quality leaves something to be desired.  The bass is weak, although tolerable.  I was able to improve the sound some by boosting the 125K eq slider, but anything below that just caused distortion.If you've been using a higher quality set of earphones, you will definitely notice the difference in the lack of low-end.  If you don't care about great range, these are fine.  You get what you pay for.BTW - the 'noise reducing' feature of these headphones comes from the fact that you are sticking a soft rubber plug into your ear.  It definitely helps to block out background noise. But don't confused this noise reduction for more expensive headphones which electronically monitor ambient sound levels and adjust accordingly.
summary: comfortable, well priced, extra buds - but weak on bass

reviewText: Sound very bad, a very truly awful perfomance, don't buy it.The odd thing is that I purchased one of these in 2013 in black color and the sounds very good.So, what's the deal? the color reflects how terrible sounds?

Update 12/20/07: I have used these ear buds for 4 months now and still no problems.  They are used about five hours per day five days per week.I am not an audiophile.  So don't read this review for a professional sound review of these ear buds.  I know nothing about ear bud "burn in" and if these ear buds benefit from a burn in period, or the percent of bass versus treble sounds you are getting.I am, however, a 5 hour per day iPod Nano 2nd Gen user who wanted a slight upgrade from the standard Apple buds, and these headphones deliver that, in my opinion.  I have used the black Jbuds for one month now.PROS:1. Sound isolation: the rubber ear pieces act like pretty good ear plugs and, therefore, channel all the music right into your ears.  I can operate my iPod at a lower volume and get as much sound channeled into my ears versus the old earbuds.  Plus I can run the lawn mower and not have to blast the music as loud to hear the music over the lawn mower noise.2. Versatile: three different size rubber ear pieces to help find a comfortable fit.3. Comfortable and small: the ear buds are smaller than I expected, and light and comfortable.  I can wear them for hours without getting pain in my ears from being "stretched" open, as happened with other ear buds I have tried.4. Good bass sound: I prefer heavier bass versus treble, and these seem to tilt toward the bass side.CONS:1. Left versus right: how much more would it cost JLabs to put a tiny white or red stripe around the cord where it meets one of the ear buds to differentiate right or left?  I got tired of looking for the small L or R printed on the buds and put a dab of white-out on the right hand cord where it joins the bud.  Now I can look down and quickly pick the correct bud for left or right!2. Cord tangles easily.  Other headphones I have owned have more spring in the cord to help prevent tangling.  If you put these in your pocket they get tangled about 50% of the time, in my experience.I would recommend these ear buds for someone looking for a reasonably priced upgrade from ear buds that ship standard with MP3 players.  I've owned a Dell Pocket DJ, SanDisk Sansa M230, and iPod Nano, and in each case the JBuds are a definite upgrade for me.
summary: A non-audiophile review - comfortable sound isolating ear buds!

reviewText: Much more comfortable than the Apple ear buds. Sound quality is fine, certainly plenty good for cutting the lawn or exercising. For nine bucks with free prime shipping it's a no brainer.

I first used these ear buds about 4 years ago, and have never looked back. Bought newer ones as they came to market. Have always been happy. Sound quality is excellent. Seem to last long. Fit comfortably in the ear. Pricing was great.

I must have strange ears because these feel like they are going to fall out. They arrived promptly, they are beautiful, but they don't fit. I feel like I have to nail them in my ears to get them to stay and even so they do not. So I will be returning them. But if they do fit other people's ears, it's a great deal. They worked very nicely and boy were they pretty.

I got these for my daughter, who is an ipod addict.  The noise reduction and sound were good.  The noise reduction being almost too good as it was even harder than usual to get her attention when she had these on.  Unfortunately, one side of the two buds died after two weeks. Fortunately, they have a one year warranty.
summary: Nice Buds, if only they lasted more than two weeks

reviewText: I bought my mother in law a Kindle HD Fire for Christmas.The Kindle has great sound but she lives in a nursing homeso the others living there probably would not like her running it all the time.These have nice sound and do a good job of blocking out background sound.
summary: Really nice buds for the price

reviewText: I have bought several Jbuds over the last couple of years. They sound great but they don't last. My longest lasting Jbud worked for 6 months.
summary: You get what you pay for!

reviewText: I received my new JBuds in a matter of days, which was great! They arrived in EXCELLANT condition! I plugged them into my lap top (TOSHIBA SATELITE)pulled up my music folder and tested them out. I can't tell you enough how AWESOME these are!!!! The music sounds great, they DID reduce noice(which leaves more MUSIC to my EARS) they have a very comfortable fit and I like the color choices offered by JBud. I picked the Pink ear buds, but there is a color that will please just about everyone! They even have cases to match!  I WOULD MOST DEFININATELY RECOMMEND these to EVERYONE!JBuds Hi-Fi Noise Reducing Ear Buds (Pink)
summary: JBuds Hi-Fi Noise Reducing Ear Buds (Pink)

reviewText: These aren't the best ear buds on the market, but they may be the best for the price. The sounds quality is good for such an inexpensive ear bud, and I don't worry about losing or breaking them since they didn't cost much. They don't stay in my ears very well, but I don't don't use them while I'm active (I have another pair for that), so it doesn't matter.
I ordered these for my 11 yr. old for Christmas. He thinks the sound is good. They fit in his ear and stay in. The price was great. I would buy JBuds brand again. Fast turn around from Amazon.

These ear buds are very nice for their price.  The multiple silicone inserts ensure a perfect fit.  Sound quality was very good.  My only gripe is that the silicone inserts seem a tad flimsy.  Overall, for the low price, it's a good set.  I also bought the JLabs Earbuds case to protect these JBuds.  They are a great combo.

I should've listened to the other bad reviews.  Used for 1 month and already lost sound from one ear.  I actually think its a problem with the plug.  I will go back to my cheaper Creative ear buds that have lasted me years

I got these for my son in the summer of 2007 for his ipod nano. The sound was good.  I thought they had a bit more depth to them than the sony, and the price was great.  I'm not a big fan of the ear bud type headphones, I don't believe that they sound as good as the "ear muff" style kind, but that is what the people want.  And I have had the higher price ones too, the Esure.  Anyway, the little rubber things fall off too easy, and I have just had to replace them because the wire has a short in it right where the jack goes into the ipod, and sound only comes out of one side unless you hold the cord steady.  Who can do that?  probably my sons fault because he wraps the cord around the ipod to put into his pocket and I'm sure they probably tell you not to do that.Bottom line is, for the money they are pretty good over all, but word to the wise, don't wrap the cord around your mp3 player if you can help it or they might not last too long.
summary: ok, but cord didn't hold up

reviewText: I bought these to replace a pair of Creative EP-630s.  These were slightly more comfortable, but did not provide as good sound isolation or sound quality as the Creatives did.  However, that was not the worst part.  I received the shipment on Nov. 7, and they were dead by Dec. 24.  The wire tore just above the plug, apparently because I had wrapped them around my mp3 player.  I only paid $16, but these headphones are not worth that let alone the nearly $50 amazon is asking now.

My old iPod buds finally wore out after a year so my son got me a pair of these.  My daughter stole them from me and really liked them.  She never did like the iPod original buds.So I had to get another pair for myself.  Great sound!  Great Value!

Sound quality is very good; not spectacular, but very good. However, the noise cancellation is excellent. I can barely hear anything beyond the music at 1/2 volume. Normally, I play it at 3/4 volume to "tune" things out and relax. However, these block the outside sounds extremely well. Very happy with this purchase.

These are the best low$ earbuds you will ever own.  Great sound for a budget price.  I bought differnt colors for each of the family.  They work great on airplanes to block the roar of the engines.  I also use them when I mow the lawn.

I purchased 2, it's Okay... not too good for my iPhone, iPad.. sound is also okay not much clear and just simple sound whatever you listen... shipping good with my other stuffs. this ear Buds have microphone only that means this is without volume increase (+) or decrease (-) controller.-HP
Based on the price, the quality is good.  Can't expect it to be as good as $80 ones. I give it 4 star - think it is fair for the price.

The sound is good. Best I've heard on the in ear style head phones in this price range. I would say they are not noise reducing especially on a plane. During plane rides it is very hard to get consistent volume on these and I had adjust the volume so much it was annoying. I Will use these for everything but airplane rides. I'll get  real noise canceling headphones for that.

I am on about my 4th set of these. Why do I buy that many? Well they are the most comfortable ear buds I have found and since I use them just for audiobooks I do not care about sound quality. However I usually carry my small MP3 player in my pants pocket and when I bend over, sit or kneel in the yard it must put tension on the cord and they soon fail just near the plug. I end up with mono sound. The break occurs where it is not easily repairable so I toss them and go on to the next set. They are cheap enough that I may continue to purchase them although the last set only lasted a week until the wire failed.Edit on 5/4/2014I opened up my latest pair and noticed there was a warranty serial number and registration process. I registered the ear-buds and sure enough a few days later one of the wires broke. I went through the warranty process and discovered that it was quite simple and that I did not need to return the broken set. I had not registered previous sets because at this price point returning them would have been too much of an expense and hassle. They say the new set is in the mail. i will up my rating to 4 stars because of this good customer service.
summary: Very comfortable but wire is fragile

reviewText: These earbuds work. What else can I say, I've had no problems with them so far. They don't they fit comfortably and they don't fall off when I work out (running or on the bike). I think the only complaints I get are from people trying to talk to me when I turn up the volume!
summary: WOW they do cancel the outside noise...lol

reviewText: They are OK for the price, comfortable, decent sound.  Would have been 4 stars, as they are definitely better than most buds under $10, but one of the two pairs I ordered was DOA, one side just didn't work.
They are a comfortable headset and provide a super sound. They also include three adapters for each type of ear canal.

Excellent earbuds.  When I first rec'd them I let them play for 24 hrs before I started using them, as the instructions suggested.  Once I insert them in my ears it was total heaven.  There is absolutely zero outside noise.  The sound is crisp and clear.  The earbuds are very comfortable.  I can listen for hours. You can't beat them for the price.

These are ok, but nothing great. At this price point, I would give them 3 stars, but definitely 2 stars compared to ear buds just a bit pricier.Compared to my previous earbuds (Skullcandy Ink'd v1.0), the mids and highs are comparable, but the lower mids and low-end seem hollow and lacking, even for ear buds. Comfort wise, they are ok, but again there are earbuds for a few bucks more that are much better. My package only came with one size of rubber inserts, so the comfort issues might be resolved if you can find better sized ones from another pair of earbuds.Overall, I can't complain too much given the price, but I honestly fell I should have just spent a bit more. The sound quality between this and the next step up is quite noticeable.
Great to have as a back up pair but very muddy sound with very little dynamic. Couldn't beat price for a back up set for my back pack.
These headphones are ok, but their construction is a little flimsy.  The prce is good and they do perform adequately.  I would by them again..

There are some really expensive ear buds out there but, frankly, even after listening to many of them, I couldn't conclude the additional money gets me very much. These ear buds are excellent with solid, crisp bass, clear mid- and high-range sound. They are very light weight and nice looking. They seem to be very well made. The microphone is an added plus as I don't have to remove a bud from one ear to handle a phone call or to record a short memo to myself. Yeah, I like these. I think they're great.

As everyone knows, the earphones that come with the iPod are a joke - big & bulky, painful for all but those with the largest ear openings.  For Christmas 2008, my spouse got me a pair I'd put on my Amazon wishlist (the particular brand/style, which had cost around $19 is no longer there, too bad), which are the best earbuds I've ever had -- they had a solid-foam ear insert, that you rolled between your fingers for a few seconds to warm up (like the foam earplugs you use at a shooting range, or when diving - after you roll/warm them, you stick in your ears and they form to a custom fit), and they fit & sounded wonderful.  I used those for my iPod Shuffle, but after I discovered all the great free movies/shows on Netflix's free streaming service, I began watching a lot of stuff on my laptop...and found I needed another pair of earbuds, since that first pair was never on the same floor as my laptop.Went back to Amazon to order another pair of those pink jobbies, and couldn't find them.  So ordered these.  They're comfortable for long-term use (but not as much as the pink jobbies), but don't block outside sound unless you're listening to something through them.  And although they come with different sizes of rubber ear-fittings, be careful trying to replace them, because the rubber is extremely thin & flimsy, and rips easily.  Learned the hard way.Overall, a great value.  But not as good as those pink ones with the foam fittings.
summary: Quite comfortable but not very noise-reducing, and not durable

reviewText: I bought 2 of these earbuds to use on my iPhone 4. One only works if I constantly keep adjusting the plug into the phone. I would not buy them again.
summary: Not as good as I expected.

reviewText: I got them primarily for use under noise-control ear muffs while operating loud equiment. They sound great, but they tend to come out of the ears after a while and require frequent re-inserting.Good value for the price.

I am on the fence with these. They are cheap enough, but sound quality is really not up to my standards. The sound range lacked and the volume was not high enough for a motorcycle rider. (without boosting)Even with my equalizer, I was not able to make them sound like others at the same price range.They are straight in type, which does not give the sound quality of angled ear buds.I like low priced ear buds, as I am hard on the wires. I prefer the flat wire units.

I have been using another Jbud for almost 2 years (SAME MODEL)  and the sound quality is much better then this NEW ones. I bought 3, one for replacement and 2 for gifts and I return all 3, Sorry JLabs
An excellent replace set of earbuds for stock headphones. They fit nicely and sound great.

Cheap headphones with excellent sound quality... What could be finer? Well how about a pair that lasts more then a month.  Two separate pairs experienced the same malfunction: one earbud just dying within around 4 to 6 weeks of usage.  One breaking is acceptable for the price point but two shows this to be a problem endemic to the product.  Look at the many other reviews with the identical issue- bad headphones at a cheap price are no bargains.Edit: many pairs later and I've really come to appreciate these headphones. You simply will not find a more comfortable and well sounding pair at this price.  Since my initial problems I've gone through many, many sub-$10 and these do stand out.  Worth buying, get a couple if you're clumsy and go ahead and jam.Edit 2: I've been reading some other reviews that say this product can range up to $20... Definitely not worth it.  If you've got prime and these guys are at their usual ~$7.00 price point buy them.
summary: They won't last...(EDIT: Or will they?)

reviewText: It fits in my ears very well, as they give you 3 different size ear pieces, however the sound is mushy.  The earbuds that came with my Slacker player have much better sound, but they keep falling out of my ears.  I would look for earbuds with better sound.
I bought these cause they were cheap, as was the MP3 player I was attaching them to.I've been using both for five years now!

Bought these for my granddaughter  and they work great! She wears them when she is on her PC and her Kindle. And when she is wearing them, I don't have to listen to it! I tried cheaper ones, but they do not last very long and she tells me there is a huge difference in the sound.

I was pleasantly surprised by the quality of these ear buds.  I was skeptical because they are inexpensive compared to some of the other noise reducing ear buds on the market.  However, they are not cheaply made.  I use them at a very noisy gym and they block probably 90-95% of the noise around me...which is far better than I expected.  They also fit my ears very comfortably.  I would definitely recommend these to my friends and I would buy them again...
Wow, I wasn't expecting much at this price point but these buds sound great, stay in place (thanks to the interchangeable silicone pads) and are very comfortable. What more can you ask for?
these headphones are awful. the sound is terrible and forget listening to talk shows. save your money and buy the better quality ones. not worth the 5 bucks.

They don't reduce the noise as much as I would have liked but they do reduce it some.  They sound they do produce is great so just for listening they are very good.  For less than 10 bucks I guess you can't expect total outside noise to be cancelled out.

I'd like to start out by saying these failed on me after nine months of moderate use. I've had ear buds fail on me in the past and usually its a slow death. With these on the other hand the right ear bud died without warning.The time they did last during the nine months was solid though. The sound quality is average, but for the price its expected.Even though I gave this three stars I ordered a second pair recently. You can be the judge if nine months is possibly worth ten dollars.

I purchased these to replace the earbuds that came with my iPod Shuffle, based on the great reviews I saw here. They are soooo much better than the hard ill-fitting earbuds that came with the Shuffle. I could not keep the others in my ears.  These are much softer and fit very nicely. I am very pleased and highly recommend them! I'm getting ready to order more as gifts for my niece and nephew and brother-in-law who all received iPods for Christmas.
summary: Much better than the iPod earbuds!!

reviewText: I go through a pair of these phones every six months(the wire breaks inside at the connector and one side will fail). I've found these phones to be excellent, however I believe that the COBY CV-E92 are the same phones-availiable only in white and with only the medium sized rubber ends(which is the size I use). I order 2 or 3 at a time and enjoy them till they fail. They're like $6.00 compared to $20.00 for the J-BUDS.Try them both, that's all I can say.
summary: Coby CVE-92 are the same headphones

reviewText: Only good for sitting at your desk listening.Sound is fair.You get what you pay for remember this.Not good for running.Be careful if you stick them in your bag or pocket. The head phone broken when I was removing it from my saddle bag.While it is only 6 dollars there are other pairs of head phones for 6-8 dollars that have lasted longer or still going if I just hadn't lost them! Dang it.Would not recommend.

I purchase a lot of headphones and for the price these are just fine. I don't listen to music with them mainly for YouTube at night in bed. I have others that sound terrible. So for a month they have worked great so for durability my review isn't ready but for quality they are great so far

I sent this to my father who has an android phone so he could listen to his fm radio on the phone.  It is awesome because it also has the voice control on answering the phones.  For only eight bucks you can't beat the deal.  They fit perfect in most ears and quality is great too again.

reviewerName: JasonKCA "Love history books, really love mil...
reviewText: You always hear the saying "you get what you pay for" and in this instance I simply needed some ear buds to use at work for training modules, web meeting review and other treble type purposes. It blocks out common voice background noise very well and while it cannot handle or even let you hear bass frequencies, it's great for what I needed! My pair that was more pricey was stolen while I was on medical leave so I wasn't about to spend much. Of course for music you would want better quality.

These headphones sound great, are comfortable, and most importantly they block out a lot of outside noise. One of my pet peeves while working at a local coffee shop is all the background noise (especially the super-trendy music). I used to listen to my own music with some over-the-ear headphones, but I had to crank them up sometimes to block all the background noise. With these headphones, I can keep my music turned down nice and low while eliminating or reducing most background noise to a low murmur. It works great for what I wanted.As far as sound quality, the bass isn't too bad for a small headphone and all the mids and highs sound clean and crisp. The fidelity is so good on these headphones I can listen at very low volumes and the sound is still crisp. Still, when it comes to sound quality, there's no substitute for a big old set of ear-muff style headphones. Since I'm not going to carry those all over, this is the next best option. I would definitely recommend them.One word of warning - watch the volume on your computer. If you plug in while it's cranked up, your ears will be ringing. Sounds obvious I know, but these things sit right up against your ear drum. Caution is the word.
These fit nicely in my ears and didn't fall out easily. The sound quality seemed about average for a pair of headphones.
Sounds like I am listening thru a pillow.  The free ones fron planes sound better. Would NOT buy again. Save your money.

These are a tiny bit better than what comes with mp3 players.  I usually use the large earphones over my year, but ear buds are more convenient when travelling or in restaurants, or elsewhere in public.

Sorry but I just don't get it. Although these are indeed comfortable to wear the sound is by no means amazing or anything to get excited about. To me the sound is very muffled, I don't get the deep base or even the mid level sounds. I compared them side by side with the Sansa buds that came with my MP3 player and there is just no comparison. If comfort is all you care about then these are for you, otherwise I would look elsewhere.
summary: What is all the fuss about?

reviewText: Within a week of receiving this product,  the plastic cover on the lead wire brokeexposing the bare wires.  This was with normal use, and very little use.On the other hand, the sound quality is excellent.

These are perfect for me. All the others tend to hurt my ears. These fit perfectly. And as far as the sound quality is concerned, I'm no expert but the sound quality to me is excellent.  I would definitely recommend!
I really like these. They fit snug. Are comfortable. Don't allow too much outside noise. Are easy to keep clean. Would recommend.

It's worth spending a little more to get better frequency response. I gave four stars simply because they're only about $7. I returned but only because I needed something with a little more bass (yes I tried the different sized rubber pieces).

I bought these to replace a set of Samsung buds that came with an MP3 player. These had perfect high end and clarity but ZERO bass. I went to JLab's site and submitted an email. Their response was:"Have you been able to try the different size tips to find the best fit? A snug fit is what allows the bass to resonate inside the ear canal."Well I had already done what I thought was a break-in but they also have a break-in audio file that is full spectrum. I switched tips and did a breakin and I now have bass. I'm hoping to get some more, but these are now as good as my previous Samsung buds.They are light, fit well and when I had them on, I can't hear my coworkers. I fair value.-Edited after my customer service experience.
summary: Make sure to pick the right sized tip

reviewText: Granted these are $10 headphones, they rival headphones that are in the $20 range.  But they certainly won't blow you away with hi-fi sound.  The bass is nice, but at decent volume music seems to get muddled.  It often sounds like the lows and highs are competing to be heard, and in the end its just one big mess.  One thing I noticed is that these seem to be tuned for electronic music, which had much less distortion than rock/rap.  Of course if your budget is $10 then these are about as good as you can hope for, but if you have a few more dollars and are looking for a really pleasant listening experience then look elsewhere.

I tested the iLuv iEP322GRN vs these headphones vs the Panasonic RPHJE120G In-Ear HeadphoneThese headphones do absolutely nothing they say, they do not reduce noise, produce an extremely bad quality sound and do not even fit that well in your ear with the different ear size attachments they provide. The sound they produced had absolutely NO bass were extremely flat and the vocals sounded seriously muffled. If there is one thing I hate, its bad quality headphones and that is exactly what these are. I would highly recommend the other two headphones I tested because they were very neck and neck in the competition of cheap headphones
summary: The <$10 heasphones test. These absolutely FAILED

reviewText: These are great little headphones but when they say "noise reduction" don't be fooled into thinking these are somehow noise-canceling headphones.  If you take a napkin, wad it up and stuff it in your ears they become "noise-reducing" just like these headphones.  Don't get me wrong, you get good sound for a super cheap price but that's it.  You get what you pay for.

These ear buds put out so much sound as compared to my older but very reliable and used Sony's that I almost blasted my ear drum.  Turn your volume down before using them the first time.  Noise reduction is just from the rubberized ear pieces and not by some electronic cancelling like you see in some headphone sets.  Still I think they're a good buy.

When the first pair died after a couple months I figured I did something to cause the right ear to short. Couldn't imagine what.  I'm a 40-something female.  We're not known for being "hard" on headphones.  So I order a second pair primarily because these fit and stay in my ears.  And guess what?  The second pair died at the 90 day point also.  So it's not me.  It's them.  THEN I see these other reviews with a similar warning.  Wish I had known.  But now you do.  Stay away.  $50 total for two pairs and no headphones.
summary: These Die In Less Than 90 Days - Read On...

reviewText: I bought these in 2007, and they're still working great (but I don't use them very often, and I don't jog with them or anything). I like their sound better than the few other ear buds or vertical-in-ear headphones I've tried. They provide good low end, which is a must for me. I use them with my Sansa Clip MP3 player.

I snatched up two sets of these ear buds at their current fraction of retail price as my husband and I are both avid music lovers and are rarely seen without our Archos media players. I was very hesitant at first given the reviews stating the ear buds failed after a fairly short period of time, but I figured for $10, you really can't go wrong. We have never had premium quality ear buds and both of us have been prone to ear soreness after extended use with our traditional ear buds. My husband especially suffered from this as he is always listening to music and podcasts throughout the day and at work and often uses music to help clear his mind to fall asleep at night. I had hoped that these JBuds would be great for both of us, and so far, I have not been disappointed.The included instructions state that you have to let the JBuds play music for an extended period of time to play at their full potential. If that's true, I am in luck because right out of the box they sound amazing. The quality is very crisp and clear yet very full. With my JBuds in, I am completely immersed and it's a beautiful thing. It sounds and feels as though the music is all around me. I am no audiophile, but music is a huge part of my life and these buds have multiplied my enjoyment of my music tenfold. Even when listening to podcasts, the voices are clear and it sounds as if the person talking is right in front of me. I know this is much owed to the ultra comfortable silicone ear buds which block out a surprising amount of external sound. The weather has been horrid here lately with harsh winds and I walked outside to take my pups in the back with my JBuds in and I didn't hear the howling wind at all. I have even been using these when gaming which has also been a treat. I love my Logitech G35 7.1-Channel Surround Sound Headset, but as it requires a restart of my game, I'm not always willing (or able) to restart on the fly to plug in my headset. In those situations, I plug in my JBuds and I'm completely immersed in my gaming world.As for comfort, as that was the driving force behind this purchase, they have not let me down. It was strange, at first, being that the way the JBuds fit as compared to standard ear buds is very different. The JBuds slide further into the ear than I am used to and it felt odd for the first five minutes or so. After that, I hardly noticed they were in. The soft silicone is fantastic for holding the buds gently in place but not putting any pressure whatsoever on the ear itself which was always our biggest problem. Standard ear buds have to be wedged into the ear and rely on that to stay in place, which not only leads to a less secure fit but soreness over time. The silicone ear buds fix both issues.My husband and I are both very pleased with this purchase and they have met and exceeded all my expectations for the price I paid. (I got two pairs for less than the half the price of one pair at retail!). I don't know if my review would be as glowing had I paid retail price. In truth, I probably would not have paid retail price for these just because I don't feel this type of product is worth that kind of money, but for what I paid, I am extremely happy and I'm even thinking about buying a few more sets for my nieces and nephew who aren't seen without their iPods. For this price, the quality is unsurpassed. You won't be disappointed!!
summary: Simply amazing for the current price

reviewText: I got for my 8 year old sister because her other headphones were a piece of c word! These are so good for her and the music quality it plays is magnificint! Also the vibrant colors make it attractive to young children. You should get these for kids!!
These headphones broke within a week of buying them.  I would not purchase them again, we had to return them for a credit.

These are ok for the price and work. But they seem to fall out of my ears often and it's frustrating when exercising to keep putting them back in. Maybe my ears are too small or something but other than that they work well!
Seeing as I go thru headphones like candy, these do just fine by me. While not as good as the Sony brand, these are a good set of earbuds. Earbuds seem to work better for me than regular headhpones.

reviewerName: Jeri J. Steele "Jeri J Steele, Pioneer Inform...
reviewText: I have to use my tablet for conference calls. These ear buds and microphone combination has worked well. The sound quality for listening to music was good for the price. I love that I got to pick some color instead of all white or all black.

reviewerName: Jeri Zerr "formerly a Road Warrior of the Nth...
reviewText: Hi-Fi Noise-reducing ear buds - cause sore ears within short order despite trying every size pad. The sound is okay with the cobalt magnet, but not the best audio quality.The Panasonic ear buds fit better than the JLab, they also sound better since they have the much better quality neodymium magnet. I much prefer the Moshi ear buds, they are just FAR more comfortable.  The Mochi Mythros (neodymium magnet) include a built in microphone for skyping (they are sold for the Kindle but I use them both for my Kindle as well as for my Sony Walkman MP3 player because they are by far the most comfortable ear buds I have EVER used.At this price for the JLab JBuds I had planned to buy several pair so I could leave a pair in the bag I take to the fitness center, but after the concerns over sore inner ears, I will not be using these but as a backup pair and will not be buying another pair after all.
summary: Sore inner ears after a half hour of wearing.  I prefer the Moshi Mythros though they include a microphone (useful for skype!)

reviewText: got these for my daughter,because she liked the look,but the quality is great as well.very happy with purchase.she is rough on these things lets see how long they last.

You can spend a lot more money and get a much more high end product but if you are on a budget, these are much better than the pair that comes with the players.  Used min for the first time on a transcontential round trip on a plan and found them to be very effective.  Great deal.

Being unable to wear over-the-ear headphones leaves me at a significant disadvantage, or so I thought before my husband gave me these little beauties.  They are far better than any of the other ear buds I've ever tried.  I'm very impressed with these little guys; and as someone with ridiculously sensitive skin and tender ears I'm happily surprised at how comfortable these are.  They come with several sizes of soft-squishy material so you can find the right fit for your ears.  I use them primarily for playing Skyrim and listening to Pandora, both of which require a certain sensitivity and clarity of sound to get the most out of and these ear buds deliver on all counts.
The sound is not bad. Based on the price, it is not bad. It is worth to buy especially it has a micro-phone on it.

Buying headphones is always iffy, so I was worried when I bought these because the price was so low. These are by far the best earbuds I've ever had. They're even better than the ones that came with my iPod, which were great until they wore out from heavy use. I highly recommend these -- they're a great bargain, and great headphones.

I had been using the v-moda Bass Freq earphones for a while, then switched to some Sennheiser earbuds. Both were pretty decent, but i have to say the v-modas had a better punch for rock/rap which i listen to. I tend to break earphones a lot getting them snagged on things in the gym, so after my last incident i decided to try these. I guess the sound is clear enough, the mid to high range is pretty decent, but there is NO bass whatsoever. None. If you like bass, steer clear of these.Seriously for a few bucks more you can get the v-modas and you will be much happier.

These had great sound, fit, and balance for running ... until the left ear bud went dead 6 miles into a half-marathon. Something went wrong in the connection between wires and the base of the headphone plug.Admittedly, I didn't try to warranty them; I'm sure I have lost the packaging and receipts.Good for sound, not up for active use.UPDATE: The customer service email was very courteous and sent me a replacement set of J-Buds. I didn't even have to return the broken set! I'm impressed.
Love the color! The price is perfect for someone who seems to loss ear bids daily. Thanks!
Bought as a present for my husband. He claims they are so comfortable, good sound, and he can wear for hours without earpain. Worth the 20.00 better than the 40.00 Ipod ones.
These Ear buds work well on our smart phones. Have not had any issues with it at all. No static, crackling, or unusual sounds. Very nice & recommend.
Got the job done for about 4 days then stopped working. Not sure why. I have to go purchase a different set now.
Got these for my grandson to use on his kindle HD.  He loves them and that's good enough for me.

I guess I should have realized that when it said "noise reducing" and not "noise canceling" it really means they do neither. The "noise reducing" part of these head phones is the rubber shield, although I have a hunch it works better to keep the ear buds in your ear than it does to actually reduce any noise. You cannot compare these on the same day as any actual noise canceling head phones. They work, adequately, but if you want top notch sound and noise cancellation, look for something with active noise cancellation.
summary: Inexpensive, you get what you pay for

reviewText: I am quite disappointed with this purchase. I feel like I guess I really did get my money's worth. I bought them because they were cheap on the side and they do not work as noise reduction at all. I am unhappy with the purchase. Do not recommend them if you're looking for noise reduction headphones. Otherwise they work "alright" as normal headphones.

I purchased a black set of these in the past and, though pretty inexpensive, they have been a solid performing set of ear buds with great bass and have lasted through even being accidentally thrown in the washer a few times.  When I was looking for another set to have as a spare I figured it was a sure bet to just purchase another pair since they are so reasonably priced.  I got the blue ones this time but have been dissapointed with the difference in sound quality.  The plastic shell seems slightly different now than the first pair I got about 2 years ago and there is noticeably less bass in the newer pair.
summary: newer version of these has noticeably less bass

reviewText: Comfortable with adjustable ear pads. Does a good job of noise reduction when I'm riding my motorcycles. Cord is slightly too long allowing it to catch on things. Came with 5 free downloads.

For $6 you can't find much better... but save up and spend $12 and you'll be so much happier. Just a little friendly advice from someone who used to own these until they died and is happy to own something different.
summary: The price is their best point.

reviewText: Ok, here's my 2 cents. My first in-ear phones aside from the ipod phones were the Sony Fontopia and they broke within the first couple of weeks. The cord on those were the flimsiest ever. I took a chance on Jbuds because of the price, initially, compared to the $40 I spent on the Sony's which turned out to be a disappointment and seriously damaged my faith in the Sony brand. Overall, I love the Jbuds and will purchase them again and have given several as gifts. The sound quality is great and is a definite value as an everyday pair of earphones for working out and such. I am no audiophile but even compared to my other pair of expensive Shure earphones, these are excellent. The only criticism I have is that I wish the cords were thicker and sturdier. On my last pair, one earphone no longer works and it is due to stress on the cord, I'm sure. At $20 a pair maybe I shouldn't expect too much perhaps. Honestly, with as great as these are in all other aspects, I don't think it is too much to ask for a stronger and thicker cord. Bravo to JLab for such a great overall value. Now let's just make them a little more rugged for us active types.

I've had many in-ear, silicone-style earphones before, and I know proper insertion can be a challenge to keep the piece in your ear securely.  I have even learned to pull the fleshy part of my ear up and out with one hand, while inserting with the other, to "straighten out" the ear canal for a snug fit far enough into the outer ear canal that they don't pop out.  However, these puppies never seem able to stay in for any length of time.  Maddeningly, even during cold winters when i have a ski hat over my ears, these earphones seem to figure out a way to squirm out.  Tried them in all three of the silicone sizes, none work.  I've never had this problem with in-ear headphones before.  They *look* nice, with the silicone insertion part flush with the blue molded plastic, and they sound perfectly good — until they start coming out and you lose all bass response, then volume, again and again... I wonder if they were ever tested on human ears prior to release.  If you want in-ear phones that go in and STAY in (and sound very good, the way in-ear headphones typically do), I recommend the Panasonic RPHJE120V.  Not only does this Panasonic model stay in, but it features an innovative diagonal design that requires only one hand to insert securely.
summary: They refuse to stay in my ear

reviewText: I bought two of these for regular laptop use and you get what you paid for.Pros:1.Cheap2.Light weight3.Sounds not that bad when use with 16bit 192000Hz - Studio quality. I am mostly using it with Win7 Machine listening  Trance.Cons:1.Does not fit properly medium size usually slides down. Large is too large and small is too small. I have a pair of Sony, i have not found a perfect fit like Sony.2.I know its not noise reduction type and but it does not do not even 2% of it.3.Cord could have been a little longer.Overall it perform as it suppose to for much you paid for it. If you love sound and want to enjoy what you listen then find something more expensive. These head phones are not cut out for it.

I had only every use old fashioned headphones.  Cans they are called.  I never believed that good sound production could be had by "earbuds" and therefore never tried them.I was buying these for my wife.  It turns out that even the smallest rubber "buds" that came with these headphones were too big for her hears.  If you have small ear holes, these may not be for you.  I have very large ear holes and I had to use the smallest "buds" on the phones.I plugged them into my PDA MP3 player.  With my old headphones, the volume had to be up around 9-10.  I put the buds in my ears and hit "Play."  Whoa!  The volume was more than loud, it was extremely loud.  So, I turned the volume down to about 2-3.  Now I use the earbuds to play music when I am mowing the lawn.  The JBuds DO reduce the noise of the lawnmower and I was able to hear the music clearly OVER the lawnmower.  It was a great experience to actually be able to hear the music while mowing the lawn.Needless to say that even though I bought these for my wife and they do not fit her, I am glad to have bought these earbuds.  I recommend them wholeheartedly to anyone who needs some noise reducing earbuds.They have faithful bass response and the highs are not muddy.  Of course they don't compare with $200 earbuds, but the good thing is that they don't cost $200.For the money, these are awesome headpho...er, earbuds.(So old, can't stop calling them head phones, albums, cool daddio...)

I received the item on time and it comes inside a bag like if you are buying candy. It came in a good package since I bought this headphones when I also bought something of a bigger size so they just placed it inside together in a big box. ONE PROBLEM that seems REALLY WEIRD when I opened the box and took out the things they put inside so the items dont get damage, it had DROPS OF WATER INSIDE. I checked if the box had any signs of water damage but the box was clean and dry. Hopefully the seller makes sure next time to send it dry. The sound of the headphones is not that great but they feel comfortable for the price.
summary: Package came with drops of water inside.

reviewText: For $10 these are hard to beat as an upgrade to the earphones that come with most MP3 players.I consider these to serve two main purposes:1.  Inexpensively upgrades your current OEM earphones.2.  Introduces you to the difference better earphones/buds can make.I'm not going to say these sound as good as my Audio-Technica ATH-CK7's but they didn't cost near as much either.  If I loose or break these I can easily buy another pair and for $10 I don't expect them to last forever.I mainly use these at night when I set the sleep timer on my Sansa Clip+.  In this case the long cord comes in very handy and they are comfortable enough that I almost always fall asleep with them on, then wake up later and take them off.  Even with my ear resting on a pillow I have found these comfortable to wear.As with all earbuds two things make a big difference in sound quality: the position you have these in your ears and the break-in period (JLab's website explains this in detail).  I'm pleased enough with JLab's entry level earbud that my next set will most likely be their J3's.These do carry a one year warranty if you register them within 30 days from date of purchase on the JLab's website.

I use my iPod mostly to listen to podcasts and audiobooks, so it doesn't much matter... but the sound from these earbuds is very muffled, a bit like listening under-water.  If you care about sound, look elsewhere.  If you're looking for noise-reducing earbuds for spoken word only, these are acceptable, though just barely.
summary: They sound crappy, but what do you expect for $10?

reviewText: Comes with multiple size rubber ear inserts. None of them seem to fit real well or stay put for heavy exercise.

I suppose everyone's ears are different but these won't stay in my ear. The slightest tug and out they come. Almost useless. Too bad because they were comfortable and the sound quality seemed pretty good. But if they fall out, What's the point?
The buds fit my ears well, and the mic picks up voices around me. My hearing is below par, and I bought these to use with an iPod Touch and hearing aid apps. Great combo.

The product is a gift for someone for christmas so i can't tell about the quality but the shipping was unbelievably fast. I hard ordered them the night before with the free two day shipping option and it arrived the next morning. I wasn't suppose to get it till 2 days later. I was really surprised by this. It was pretty much over night shipment for free.

I purchased these for the price. I get these for my kids because I don't necessarily want to listen to their how-to videos about Minecraft. They kids like them, they come with S, M, L sized ear buds, and they have survived the abuse from the kids for now.

Hi, these ear buds actually stayed in my ears most of the time! Great product!! I have a problem getting most ear buds to stay in, but these stayed in all while seeded our lawn, for 2 hours! So I was very pleased!Thank you!
VERY NICE EAR BUDS - SOFT FIT NICE AND LOOK CUT.  LOVE THE COLOR.  CAME VERY QUICKLY AND WORK GREAT
I like these as they are not "borrowed" by my husband all the time.  They are mine and the sound is great

I use my Mp3 player only to listen to audio books, and purchased these earphones to replace the ones that originally came with the player. The attributes I look for in earphones for audio books are obviously different than those who listen only to music with their players. Most importantly, I want clarity of sound and these headphones deliver. I found the buds to be a bit large for my ears and not as comfortable as I'd like, but I have yet to put on the optional sized plugs that comes with the ear buds, which may improve the size problem. Otherwise, these ear buds are an excellent accompaniment to my belovedSanDisk Sansa Fuse Mp3 Player.
summary: Excellent earphones for the audio book listener

reviewText: After reading the reviews, I went ahead and bought them. I know ear buds in general are not the best in the bass department but these things have no bass at all. There are different rubber tips included and none of them fit properly (I am a 5'11" male). The medium ones are too large, the small ones feel like they will pull off inside my ear, the large ones are also too large. If you intend to keep these in your backpack, the rubber picks up crumbs, fuzzies, ect which sounds like an ear infection waiting to happen.At $6, you are better off just using a pair of dollar store buds.

hey o, was excited to have some head phones that controlled my iPhone. the sound was bad but to be expected for cheap head phones not the deal breaker, while making calls the remote would hang up my calls repeatedly... lame had to buy new ones, getting panasonic the cheapest ones with remote as the non moted ones are supercomfy and sound good. good luck y'all
summary: Sound bad and remote went crazy first day

reviewText: Pros: Excellent upgrade over stock ear buds.  They will not fall out of you ear.Cons: Cheap construction and cord length could be longer.Conclusion: Excellent spare ear buds for work or the gym.
these buds don't hurt your ear and i have had mine in for hours on end. they come with different sized ear plugs in case. great sound quality and don't distort as they get very loud. great buy

I bought these based on good reviews I had seen here on amazon and I am SO disappointed! Not only in the headphones but in the reviewers because they couldn't have gotten this any more wrong.These:Fall out of your earsSound terribleAre fairly unattractiveAnd the worst part is NOBODY CAN HEAR ME WHEN I USE THEM!SAVE YOUR MONEY BUY SOMETHING ELSE.

I bought two of these. They're a great replacement and believe me, I'm an audiophile. I've been a professional musician for 33 years. Earbuds don't last. These will last as long as very expensive brands and are very well balanced. Sure, they're not Bose, but they're not far less quality for far less money and they will last as long. I've idiotically spent $160 on Bose and they broke, as all things do. Don't waste your money on more expensive products -- buy these. They are not the best, but they are excellent. Most people won't know the difference. I do know, but I also know that I can buy 10 of these for a Bose ear bud.

Got them at the sale price. At this price I have absolutely no complaints. Here my comments based on my comparison with my other buds.1) Noise reducing. Yes they are. I'm typing as I listening to them and they do cut down on the clicks compared with my other ones.2) Ear size, there are 3 sizes of pads, small, medium and large. Both the small and medium fit my ears but I've noticed that the medium pads really increases the bass. It really makes a difference compared to the small pads and my other buds. I haven't compared the bass with the big pads but I won't since they are too big to fit comfortable in my ears and I won't be wearing them.3) Sound quality, The deep bass with the medium pads, I'm not too worried about that because I can use the equalizer on my MP3 to adjust that.4) Yeah, they come in a cheap Ziploc bag but as long as the price is good I'm fine with that!Overall very pleased with them.
Disappointed, the one that came free with my Sansa 240 sound better.  poor Sensitivity also
summary: jbuds not as good as expected

reviewText: I've bought a few pairs of these headphones.  I really like the sound.  I especially like that there is an L-shaped arm on the end that you insert into the mp3 player, so that the cord doesn't stick directly out.  My first pair of these eventually went bad at that L-shaped arm, though, losing sound unless you held the cord a certain way.  Now I know not to wrap the headphones tightly around the mp3 player so as to not damage the connection at the L-shaped arm.  My second pair is holding up very well.
summary: Nice sound, good for the price

reviewText: Paid only $9.99 for ear buds ... perform as well as one's purchased for $49 to $79.  Am anxioous to see how long they last, but others only have a 3 to 6 month life with my use.
The earbuds that came with the Ipod are extremely uncomfortable.  These were inexpensive and, although I have to turn the volume up a little, their sound is very good.
These do not compare with ear muffs for really loud tools (like a router table). However for distracting noises like sanders they work great. I can listen to the radio while sanding.

I have actually purchased several pairs since last fall,all of which are still functioning well. The sound,(assuminga proper fit) is quite full and well balanced/natural.After trying several other brands, I still keep coming back tothese to hear how the original "track" was mastered. Many other budsare bass-heavy, or very bright. These provide some isolation,without being totally disconnected from your environment.
There is to much base for my liking. Even with full trebel and reduced base output it is still a bit much for me.

As soon as I write this review I am arranging to return these Jbuds to Amazon. This is the 3rd or so pair of Jbuds I have owned, purchased from Amazon. I like the value, I like the sound quality. But when it comes to durability, they are disappointing.I have used these for literally less than one week, light usage, really; they have already become useless in the same way every other pair of these I have had previously have become useless: the wire has shorted-out where the wire connects to the plug. If I manipulate the wire I can momentarily hear the sound in the Left earbud, then it shorts-out again.Why cannot I find some earbuds that sound good, last awhile without shorting-out, without costing an arm & a leg?
summary: Can Someone Please Recommend Some Good-Sounding Earbuds that Have a Cord That Doesn't Short-Out by the Plug?

reviewText: Recently my nephew broke his pair of ear buds and needed a new pair. I thought this would be a great choice since I already own a pair of these and they work great. I own the yellow pair of the JBuds Hi-Fi noise-reducing ear buds that I picked up at a local electronic store. I have had them for a little over 6 months and they work phenomanal. My cousin has a really expensive pair of b*** ear buds and says these are not the exact same but are somewhat comparable which I think says a lot over some of the other brands out there. They are extremely loud if you want them to be, once in your ears you can barely hear any surronding noise, and the bass on these work great they don't sound like those choppy stock speakers you hear in cars' all the time. The colors are also great. They come in an almost two tone color with yellow and black, blue and black, and red and black which look great. I will definitely be a repeat customer for these ear buds if I need another pair in the future.
summary: Performance rich ear buds for less than half the performance rich price.

reviewText: A great set of ear buds for a great price.  Sound quality is very good, constrauction appears durable.

decent for the price, let the buds burn in by leaving your music player on for several days straight and the sound quality improves dramatically. connection points are good , what more do you want at this price point.

It would be a mistake to compare these ear buds to other products without first taking into consideration the price.  I mean a Lexus is better than a Kia, but one costs 5x as much.  Same deal w/ these ear buds.  They work (I hear music from them), they haven't broken for me yet (had them over 6 months)... and to be perfectly honest if you are not an audiophile, you probably can't tell the difference between these and ones that cost 3-4 times as much.  5 stars from me

If you're looking for your basic on-the-go earbuds and you're not an audiophile, then perhaps these earbuds are for you. I bought these in May 2011 to replace my 3rd pair of ipod earbuds and my free pair of sound reducing earbuds that worked great in dampening outside noise. I figured the buds on these ones would do a similar job at reducing noise while keeping the crisp sound of the ipod ones. They do reduce some external noise, but not enough to appreciate the lack of sound quality they produce.The mids and highs do not have much clarity in that range. They get the job done but if you're looking to listen to symphonies like Bach G Major these are not your earphones to do that. If you're going to the gym and using them, then these are it. I give it 3 stars in comparison to better/expensive earbuds and 5 stars for typical everyday buds that I can use and not worry about losing or breaking them.

The price is really good for the quality of this ear buds. They are not really high quality but I only use them in the gym so quality is not something I am looking for in that environment. They provide good enough audio.
Very good fit, very good sound for a small headphones and incredible price, almost 100% noise reduction with a little high volume. For this price the product is excellent.
summary: Excellent sound for a low price

reviewText: I'm sending these back, I don't care for how cheaply they are made. The cord is 36" from plug to where it splits to go to your ears, The plug is straight, cheap looking, and cheap feeling. The cord is also very cheap, and fragile. The sound is OK, but lacking low frequency response in a very big way.  My first impression when I got them was "What the heck, did i buy these cheap ear buds?"Yes i did, and it was because of all the good feedback I found here on Amazon. For the cost, maybe you can take a chance with them, your opinion might be different.
summary: How cheap can ear buds be made, these are in top running for cheap.

reviewText: Works just fine. Very inexpensive. Seems to dampen sound going out and coming in from outside what I'm trying to listen to. Happy with them for sure!

When I got these I was thrilled, they sounded great with none of the static from the line that other earbuds had produced.  Although I read a few reviews about the connections going out, I assumed the users were excessively rough on them.  Since the connections had gone out on my last pair (different brand, $20 range), I was very careful with these.  I got them on 10/14/08 and I lost the right sound yesterday (11/19/08).  I'm going to try and get them fixed under warranty but even cheap earbuds should last longer than a month.  Hopefully the J2's will hold up better.Update:  The manufacturer has replaced these under warranty with no cost to me.  They are a company that truly stands behind their products.
summary: great while they worked, see update below

reviewText: SEE UPDATE AT BOTTOM:  3 STARS ONLYThat pretty much sums it up.  Four words.  These are really a great value at this price.  I think the price has even dropped again since I purchased these 2 months ago.  I purchased these for my wife because she claims the standard iPod headphones hurt her ears.  With the varying size rubber tips, these are a much better and more snug option.  While I purchased them for her, she doesn't use them that often, so I ended up keeping them for myself.  I'd always had a difficult time watching movies on the subway with the background noise.  No longer with these.  These fit so snugly that they work almost as well as any battery operated, noise cancellation headphones.  The extra long cord is good too.  Simply a great product at a very reasonable price.UPDATE 12/20/2008:I wrap my cord around my iPod when not in use.What seems to have happened is a disconnection in the "plug", which has one earphone "cutting out" or simply not working.  It will work if I jiggle the cord, but I don't want to buy a new pair of ear buds every 2 months.  I expect more durability at this price level.I'm going to try another brand new pair that I purchased and see how long it holds up.  Watch for an update in 2 months.

The sound won't blow you away -- the bass is pretty weak -- but these inexpensive earbuds perform better than I expected for their low price. I've used them with an iPod while walking, waiting at airports, sitting at a desk, etc. They're also good for watching movies on a MacBook.

I got these after my co-worker told me my earphones let out too much noise.  I don't think he can hear or complain about it anymore now that I have these.  He will probably still find something to complain about, but it won't be my earphones!

I use my earphones fairly often I would say about 5 days a week. They come in handy for my walk to and from work every day, as music makes my trip faster.So I am fairly picky about my head phones.However when I received these I was pleasantly surprised. They fit comfortably into my ears and the sound was very nice.I am very happy with my purchase and I am looking forward to see how they fair in my cold weather area but so far I would recommend these to friends and family.

I bought these as an upgrade to the ear buds that came with the MP3 player I got my son.  He isn't so impressed with them.  He likes the ones that came with his player better. I beleive it has to do with how they feel in his ears.  Not the sound quality.

too bad some customer images have angled connectors on these.....they arrived  with a straight connector.  i think (have no proof) that angled connectors work better and last longer if your player has the jack port on the side...less wire turning back and forth at the junction.  lasted about five months...the wires are very thin and not reinforced anywhere.  they at least IMO sounded fairly decent for the price and were very comfortable and come with 3 sizes of pads and had no prob getting them to fit me.  I was happy until one bud quit working and I found that basically electrical connectivity was lost where the wire joins to the jack...I am a sansa clip user and exercise and do alot of yard work, etc., and wear ear buds several hours a day.....I tell you, I have worn out many headphones and earbuds(many brands) and always it is where the jack is attached to the wire, so I guess that Jlabs is not really too different from anybody else in the cheap earbud market.
summary: good value while they lasted...warranty honored though

reviewText: Some reviewers have mentioned that the sound quality is not that great, but I have to say that they produce the best sound of anything I own, including my THX-rated Logitech 5.1 speakers that cost $300, and a pair of $60 over-the-ear headphones. I suppose there may be other ear buds that have better sound, but in this price-range these are top-of-the-line.On a side note, they are a bit fragile-feeling like all ear buds - I am on my second set, but I don't hold that against them in my case, as they got sucked into a vacuum cleaner - poor little guys didn't stand a chance. :)  That is a great reason to get these over some in a higher price-range - they will probably not be your last.
They work good they just have a very cheap sound to them if you are just looking for throw aways or you lose them often you might like them but they are loud but like I said just cheap sound quality
i've bought these ear buds for about 1 week and half and its already wearing down.. i have to tweak the plug to make the right ear bud to put out sound..

I'm would describe myself as more of a careful shopper than an audiophile... I got these for a highly reduced price of about $10 and I'm very happy with them. I go through earphones quickly because of frequent travelling and use of them.I don't have anything negative to say about these at all. I think the sound is good (at least better than the other ones I've used... I'm currently listening to iheartradio on my computer and it sounds great.)They fit me fine. I am using the ear buds that came attached, but it came with two other pairs of ear buds (one larger, one smaller).Some other points that may only interest me but are positives:- The plug part is a bit thicker than most of the ear phones I've used before and feels well constructed.- Also the plug part is square. This is not really a big deal, but it's different and sets these JBLs apart.- The wire is also thicker and seems to tangle less than others I've had. A definite plus with the way that I use them.- The earphone pieces themselves have a nice comfortable tapered shape.I'm not a person who wants to spend a lot of money on earphones, but getting these for a good price has definitely made me appreciate the better design and construction of quality earphones.
summary: Good Things to Say About These Earphones

reviewText: I love the Jbuds, particularly the fit in the ear. I cannot get standard ear buds to stay in my ears and these fit comfortably inside the ear, providing great quality sound. The soft and pliable material of the unique flange design really helps with fit and comfort. The low profile form factor of the buds outside the ear also allow me to wear these when I lie down or sleep. Also note the in-the-ear design of these ear buds do eliminate a significant amount of outside noise, which for me is a plus. This allows them to double as ear plugs, keeping the sound of my snoring spouse and dog out when I turn my player off.
I did not like the sound at all. I guess I got what I paid for. I have them as a backup now, but I would not use them for anything else.
Excellent Sound and comfort, but the quality of cable feels rigid and fragile. The old version of the cable and audio connector feels better.
summary: Excellent Sound and comfort, but poor quality of audio cable.

reviewText: this ear buds are very nice and sound great for the price i paid this is a great deal wooow
My cat ate most of it, but before he did they worked fine, but I could tell they would not last a long time, hey you get what you pay for.  Not good for everyday long time wear.
Perfect for the price.  I really like these and would buy them again if necessary.  They are a really good idea for a present too.

I know there are much more costly earbuds out there and that the audiophile wouldn't give these a second look.  These fit my list of needs to the tea.  They do a great job subduing the noise from my husbands soccer game on tv which must always be played at full volume.  When I listen to one of my relaxation tracks I could almost swear I am near the ocean instead of the middle of a cornfield.  Plus the squishy silicone makes them incredibly comfortable.  As a previous reviewer stated all the kids and grand kids will be getting a pair.
These are much more comfortable than standard ear buds.  They are worth the price and the different sizes of silicon noise blockers meant that my kids could enjoy them too!

After I got my apple earpods stolen, I've been looking for the right ear buds. I just bought these for fun and they honestly sounded pretty bad. too flat in my opinion. But great for the price range. I'm just bought new sony earbuds lets see how that turns up
summary: its great for the price range.

reviewText: Simple: you get what you pay for.  These lil buds get the job done.  Do not exspect Bose quality for ten bucks.  You will always be disappointed.

I use this earphone with a portable radio when biking to work. There is a lot of wind noise on road. This earphone is really loud and clear, much better than the previous Sony earphone that comes with an MP3 player.

I use them with my sangean portable radio every day for the past two years and those jlabs in-ear speakers never failed me: not one minute, not one hour ,not one day. I would say that for the occasional, everyday walking those are more than perfect, good sound quality, good noise reduction, no noise interference, not to speak the awesome price. Some say they break easily well, I would say maybe your player connection is not proper. I can say that I do abuse them, carrying them in my bag everyday, pulling on them sometimes. Got them back in 2006 , it is now October 2008 and they are still working. I am ordering a second pair just to be sure I have a spare pair .. because everything good in life don't last forever.Update: more than three years now, one pair died, the wire connection at one of the buds broke, and now ordered two more pairs. I have compared them with another set of earbuds, more expensive, by another company and I have to tell: The jlabs buds have no compairson: the price and the sound quality blows all others away. What do they have done better? the wires are not blowing my movements noises in my ears while walking, jogging, exercising like other buds do. BIG DIFFERENCE. Small price worth every penny and beyond.They do break after a while but I will keep buying them over and over. Ten bucks every two-three years is the best deal. Thank you, JLabs!
summary: listening with them for 2 years now -every day

reviewText: Bought this back in late september of 2009 and in august of 2011 i noticed the reception on the right bud is a little sketchy.  I wear these sorta backwards (right bud in left year and vice versa) because somehow it seems to fit my earholes better, so theoretically the weak bud is actually the left bud, but whatever.i've been using them almost 2 full years now and it just now started to give, which isn't too bad.  i don't use them heavily however.  for a few months i almost rarely pull it out but there are also periods that i use it often.  i also toss them about a lot (including tossing into my purse and getting it forever tangled up with my keys or work badge) so maybe if i took care of it more it wouldn't be dying.but for $10 buds and lasted me for 2 years, not bad.  i wasn't expecting exceptional sound out of them or anything.  noise canceling's virtually non existent (well, it's a bit more than a reaaaaaaally cheap generic bud i guess, but with them on i can still hear people in the next cube over talking, though it turns into general gibberish).if you need cheap buds and isn't looking for super specific high end quality, these are pretty good!

Sound quality is not as good as the original Samsung headphones that came with my phone.  No volume control or mic mute buttons on the head phones (unlike the Samsung original).  Finally the samsung original headphones are available for $3 less.So overall very disappoint in the product.
summary: Disappointed with sound quality and feature set

reviewText: These headphones are great. When I am using them, they are great at blocking out outside noise. I can listen to my music at a non-deafening volume and not worry about hearing everything else in the room. Came with replacement plastic tips - I haven't had to use them yet, but it is really nice to know that if I need them, I have them!
I like the great bass sound from these ear buds, and the noise reducing capabilities.  I plan to buy another set for my wife.

I ordered these ear buds to use with my Creative Zen Nano MP3 Player. Prior to this, I have been using the ear buds that came with my player. I cannot say enough good things about these JBuds. I have a very small ear canal, apparently, and the small size cap that came with the JBuds fit in my ear perfectly and doesn't keep falling out the way the Creative Zen bud did. The sound quality seems great to me. Enough said!

The earbuds that came with theSanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)sound about the same as these ones do, but the JBuds fit in my ears much better, and because I can push them in deeper, I can get better volume.

This is my second time purchasing these headphones because I want to have sets at home, my purse and the office. So comfortable, great sound quality and good blocking outside noise. Perfect earphones!
summary: I Keep coming back for more!

reviewText: These work pretty good I bought two my son alway looses them or brakes them they sound good and don't cost a lot

I've always had problems losing the little rubber ear tips that go on the Sony Fontopias and have found that I can order them separately online - they seem for fall off very easily for me but since my ear canals are smallish, they always fit well. The JBuds also fit very well, but *for me* the ear tips/rubber ear caps seem just a touch stiffer or slightly thicker than those on the Fontopias. The Fontopias were slightly more comfortable, but the JBuds are pretty darn close.I did but these because they were well priced and white, but Fontopias also come in white.Mmm, there is a noticeable difference. First, the cables are a bit stiffer and not as "relaxed" as the Fontopias - meaning, if you coil them up up crinkle them up in your bag andx then pull them out to wear, they retain that crinkled shape for a while where the Fontopias don't seem to do that. However, what I didn't like about the Fontopias was that the cables were coated with a sort of tackiness/stickiness that made untangling a challenge at times (if you didn't use the cord case that came with the ear buds).There is a nooticeable difference in sound. I get deeper sounds with the Fontopias, more bass. With the JBuds I hear crisper, lighter tones. I guess it depends on what you're listening to and what your preferences are. I like the JBuds now but that was after a couple of weeks of breaking into the new sound change.I had a problem with the white plastic coating pulling away from the ear bud at the base and exposing the wires. I think the Fontopias are probably built better overall.The jack that plugs into whatever device you're plugging into doesn't bend at a 90 degree angle like the Fontopias, where the bent part ends up parallel to the jack surface. It's bent more like 110 degrees so when you plug it in, the bent part isn't parallel to the device but sticks up a bit. Hasn't been a problem so far.No case.
Love these little buds. They work really good and have a good sound for the money. Very satisfied.

I purchased these to replace the "V-Moda bass ear buds" I lost recently.  I guess I was seduced by the lower price tag.  Ten bucks isn't a lot, but it adds up, so I went for the savings. It was a mistake.  The sound just isn't up to snuff...it lacks bass and clarity. They were comfortable though, and my mom was complaining about her ear buds not staying in and being uncomfortable, so I gave these to her.  Now I'm off to purchase the V-moda's I should have got in the first place.

I was really excited that I ordered these earphones because they seemed very good. I received them within 2 days after ordering. The packaging was nice and the earphones had a very nice design. Although it gave me a good impression, the earphones itself is horrible. The sound quality is bad. It's definitely not worth the $15 I spent and I wouldn't recommend this to anyone.

These ear buds work great. Not sure if its just me but these headphones seem not to tangle up as easy as other ones that I have owned. The sound is good and the fit is good. Comes with 3 different size rubber pieces for different size ears.

I am very happy to have bought these headphones cause I was looking everywhere for the right size. My problem is that I have small ears and regular headphones hurt them. They have pretty good sound though don't isolate much noise.
summary: They fit in my small ears!

reviewText: This pair was pretty good quality in terms of design and audio quality. The price was good as well for this product.

HOT Pink looks great & sounds great.The value/quality ratio is excellent.Much more comfy than some others that I've tried.Nothing has broken with daily use for 6+ months.Leary at 1st with the MSRP at 4x the current selling price,but that just adds to the great buy that they truly are...

I bought these for my 14 year old son who has an Ipod video.  He liked them so much that I bought them for my shuffle & my wife for her nano.  The sound is good & the various sized earpieces was useful.  However, my son's earphones died after about 6 months of use.  I know that he is hard on things but this is a bit quick.  Now I had to give him my set & I am back to the original headphones.  Next time I will look for something more durable.

I bought two pairs of the (black) ear buds but had to go on Amazon chat because I didn't get the extra ear bud pieces that come with them.
