The Amazon customer representative sent me another pair (blue) which arrived within a couple of days.My girlfriend has been using her ear buds only at night when we talk but one side of the ear buds has already stopped working. It's only been about a month (got them on ~2013 October 23). I've only used one of the two pairs of black ear buds that I ordered but the pair I've been using seems to be okay. They were pretty cheap ($7.51 for each) and I only use them when I'm walking to class on campus and at night when I talk to my girlfriend.
These work great.  I use them with my ipod touch and my laptop and they are holding up great.  Plus you cant beat the sound for this price.
1. Quality sound.2. Nice bass and treble.3. Quality made.4. Comfortable.5. Convenient.Excellent purchase.  5-stars.  A+++Would purchase again.
summary: Worth every penny and then some.

reviewText: Sept 2008 editAfter my first set of earbuds failed I contacted the company and explained that one earbud quit working. From the looks of it the 3.5 mm jack housing is constructed at a 45degree angle different than typical L looking jacks. This appears to be a serious design flaw. I'm not going to even ask for another pair and will look somewhere else.Do not recommend. At all.--------------------------------------------For their price range and use a B gradeThese Jlab headphones work well for the price. I purchased these due to my iPod's headphones wearing out. To my layman's eyes I believe the `noise canceling' act of these headphones is the fact that the ear grips completely seal your ear canal. I cannot hear any conversation our outside noise aside from yells or extreme noise.  I prefer my Audio Technica QuietPoint ATH-ANC7Audio-Technica ATH-ANC7 QuietPoint Active Noise-Cancelling Headphonesover these but I got them for their small size.The ear buds are extremely prone to popping out of your ear canal if the cord is at all moved; which was not my case with the stock iPod ear buds. The input connector of the headphones seems to be the weakest hardware aspect as I found them to be scratchy if the body behind the jack is bent in anyway.Sound levels of the headphones feel muted and dull. I tried changing EQ on my iPod to various levels and I never felt the quality matched the AudioTechnica's. But then again they are not the most advanced and I knew that when I bough them.Pros: Completely blocks out all outside sounds. Small. Gold connector jack, PriceCons: Ear buds pop out extremely easily, muted sounds not much high treble or bass feeling,
summary: For their price range and use a decent buy.

reviewText: Bought these over a year ago and there still bangin, can only imagine what the more expensive JLAB's are like.
summary: OVER A YEAR OLD, STILL JAMMIN

reviewText: Good earplugs.  Perform as well as the $300 noise cancelling ones.  However, they are not as bulky and expensive for similar performance.  Teenagers will like this.
summary: What's not to love about it

reviewText: They're comfortable, but not reliable.  Sometimes I get sound out of both ears, sometimes I don't.  I've only had them a few weeks and expected much more.

I got these to use when riding my motorcycle.  They fit well in my ears and as long as I point them in the right direction they feel good and don't rub my ear with my helmet on.  I can hear my mp3 player even on windy days. These buds are a winner.

Better than I expected for the price ($10). It doesn't block out sound amazingly, but it gets the job done - call clarity is excellent with the microphone, which also has a button that will mute during calls, pause songs with one click, and skip to the next song with a double click. Feels pretty reliable. I've been a long time user of the cheap knock off samsung/whatever brand earphones sold on Amazon, but I think this set is well worth the premium. The cord is also longer than I was expecting, which was nice.

First off, I haven't spent hundreds of dollars on earbud headphones, but others have, so read their reviews too.  However, I do own a pair of BOSE noise canceling ones so I'll use those and the standard iPod earbuds as comparisons.The fit is nice, comes with three sets of soft rubber ear pieces.  Much more comfortable than the iPod buds.Sound quality is decent, but lacks some deep bass.  I didn't expect them to have BOSE like sound quality, but was slightly disappointed. Also, noise reducing is a little misleading, these are NOT noise canceling.  They merely reduce outside noise by sealing in your ears, but they do a pretty good job of it.Price is good for what you get.The bottom line: If you're looking for a low-cost replacement for the earbuds that came standard with your MP3 player, the JLab JBuds are a good alternative.

There are thousands of ear plugs that all claim their the best for one reason or another.  Some companies even have the gaul to advertise the frequency range for their ear plugs and brag about how theirs are better because they have a wider frequency range than their competitors but their frequency range is outside of a humans capability only dogs can hear them.  Any way my wife said these are the best she has ever used and she has had over 40 pair and these are good quality at a fair price.
Although this set is slighly bigger for my ears, I still could use it.  No complaints about it.  This may be due to size of my ears.

I can't complain about the sound quality as it's pretty incredible for the price and it gets an A+ for comfortability. I just can't find any earbuds that feel as comfortable in my ears as these. I seriously forget I'm wearing them, they're that comfortable. But I will say that the durability needs improvement. No matter how I care for them, one ear always dies within 2 or 3 months and it's an absolute pain. I wish the quality of the overall product could be improved. I wouldn't even mind paying an extra few bucks if they could just fix the durability so that I could keep them longer! I have earbuds with worse sound quality and they last twice as long so I'm sure it can be resolved. Either way, product is decent and deserves a 4 star rating.
It sounds okay. It works. It was pretty cheap as far headphones go. The only complaint I have is I keep losing the ear buds. Good thing they give you a bunch
Husband radio geek! Always has it on! Likes classical!! VERY particular about quality of earbuds!! Says these are excellent quality!! Amazon price is good! Free well packaged ship!
summary: Fussy Classical Music Fan Says Thumbs Up!

reviewText: Just got these today and was looking forward to great sound quality. It is absolutely awful!! I can't understand anyone saying that the sound was great for even a moment. I knew the sound was inferior immediately; I compared it several times to other standard earphones and they all sounded better than the JBUDS. I would rather have the more uncomfortable earbuds with a more superior sound. I really hate giving a negative review but I can find no redeeming quality except that the JBUDS are more comfortable in my ears. I will keep searching for earbuds with a great price but ones that do not fall short on QUALITY!! I enjoy listening to music too much to settle for such terrible sound. These buds deserve ZERO stars!!2/24----UPDATE!!! I was WRONG...these earbuds are great!!I just used these by chance and realized that I was just placing them in my ear instead of securing them in my ear canal!! By securing them properly in my ear canal the sound is FANTASTIC. Just what I was looking for and I am very pleased and satisfied!! The bass is wonderful and the sound is very clear and crisp. The Jbuds compare favorably to a very good set of Samsung earbuds. The Jbuds are infinitely more comfortable! Happy Listening!!
summary: REVISED: Great ear buds!! Deserve 5 stars!!

reviewText: PRO'sI was initially worried about purchasing the jbuds because of the different mixed comments, but I went ahead and took a leap of faith. And thus far I am not regretting it the sound is crisp the base sounds good.Comfort in the ear is remarkable and the idea of giving extra and interchangeable rubber was well appreciatedPrice is niceCON'sThe only thing that i find a problem is the fact that there is no fixture to prevent the wiring from tearing down the middle. but with careful use this is not a problem i assure u.Ears needs to be really clean cause buds fit in the ear comfortably and picks up on the wax. ewwwIf I had to do it again I would buy it in a heart beat.Would be keeping you in the know of how it is working.

These were a great buy for the price and quality.  I love the softness of the bud that rests in your ears.  I originally thought I may have a problem with them falling out of my ear, but not the case and I wear them at the gym on the treadmill.  These have been the best earplugs and I plan to keep a pair handy.

I'm going to be very honest about what I look for in earbuds. I'm not an audiophile. I run marathons and simply want something that's sounds decent and is comfortable to wear for a four hour run. These fit the bill at a low price. My first pair lasted about two years before one side stopped working. That actually worked out great since I usually only wear one earbud (for safety reasons). I chug off the dead earbud so I no longer have to find a place to tuck it. Regardless, the three sizes of ear pieces make thm comfortable for ears of all sizes, and they don't fall out while exercising. If you're looking for a simple pair of in ear headphones, you won't be disappointed.
summary: Good enough I bought a second pair

reviewText: They are not the best ear buds that I have had but they are ok.  One comes through louder than the other. I wouldn't recommend these to anyone!
Perhaps they're not equal to the $100 variety, but these were just fine for a knock-around pair. I bought three sets, as I've got a propensity for running these through the washing machine.

I use these to listen to audiobooks in the gym, so they need to endure a certain amount of abuse. I order them in pairs for this reason. I reordered these ear buds because they're good at blocking out ambient noise like the bad music my gym plays, and nearby conversations, but I'm not going to reorder again. I expect them to wear out relatively quickly, but in something more like 6 months. These last about 2 months on average. Then the jack starts to wear out and either one bud cuts out, or the sound wobbles back and forth, etc. There are other cheap earbuds that last longer.
summary: Work fine, good price, but flimsy

reviewText: I use these with my ipod when I can't sleep, and they stay in my ears without hurting. Great job.

These are a decent pair of earphones, for the money. They are definitely better than the cheap $5 earphones you pick up at your local Target or T.J. Maxx. I'm interested to see how they will hold up after daily use for a while. Honestly I'm going to have to tell you to go pick up either the RPHJE120's, or the Monoprice 8320's, all within the same price range.Bottom line; they're good, but they're not the best within a $10 price limit.
Just like every other set of earbuds I've ever bought, these weren't working by day 3. I hate earbuds completely.

My needs are pretty simple.  I want to use my laptop while my wife has the TV on.  The Jbuds provide enough noise reduction so that I can comfortably hear my computer but I can still hear what is going on around me.I added a dab of red permanent marker to the right earbud because it is otherwise almost impossible to tell one from the other. With that modification they meet my needs nicely.

Caution if you need to use the mic - study further. The mic does not work with Sansa players or 'regular laptops'. My four stars is strictly for the sound.  With burn-in of 5 hours, these have the best sound  and comfort (small ear channels) of the less than $20 buds I have used.

Had it for 3 day and so far I'm extremely impressed, I usually don't like these type of earphones I like the regular ear buds or earpods like apple, but these are phenomenal, I'll keep posting after I've had them for longer :)

reviewerName: Leiah "So, I Read This Book Today . . ."
reviewText: Just as advertised, very comfy, noise reducing, and love the pink. The only complaint is that one of the ear bud covers was missing off the earbuds and wasn't in the package, but 4 more were included so no big shakes. I only seem to lose one at a time anyway, due to dragging around my Zune everywhere I go, they get rubbed off the tip and I have to replace. I will probably rip up the cord before I need all of the covers, so I can deal. These are just so comfortable, and the sound is great. The price can't be beat, so I am a happy camper.

I wasn't expecting much for $6. Sadly, I got less than I expected.The earbuds arrived in the same box as something else I ordered. I didn't recognize it for what it was at first. The packaging looked like a small packet of snack. No big deal, I'd rather not pay for extra packaging, and it is easy to open - just tear the bag open.3 sizes of sleeve is provided. They seemed smaller than sleeves from other headphones (Sennheiser, Klipsch) both in diameter and length. It doesn't feel very secure in the ear because it doesn't go in as far as the other earbuds, and thus doesn't block outside noise as well as other earbuds. I swapped out the earbuds for another set I happened to have around, spares from another earbud. Feels much better now.The sound from the earbuds are not great, but considering the price, I'd rate it decent. A bit weak on the higher frequencies and strong on the bass. Not crisp.The cord is about medium thickness, and smooth (nice - doesn't get tangled easily). The cord doesn't straighten itself, however - it stays "crumpled" looking.Now despite all this, I'd still rate it 4 stars for being a great value. It would be great for having in the gym bag, and the sound is still better than what comes bundled with most MP3 players. But the fatal flaw for me is that the volume from left and right earpiece is uneven. It's not my ears (I swapped sides to test) and not the material (I plugged in different earbuds to test). It's not the connection. Just poor quality, and likely very little quality control. From the average review rating of 3.5 stars, I'm assuming most units don't have this problem. I'm rating it based on the one I received.
summary: Uneven volume from left and right earpiece

reviewText: I was looking for a set of ear buds that would stay in place and not have too stiff of a wire and one with a moderately long cord. I found it. I read a few reviews about this and that made my mind up to try them. For the price, they have great highs & lows. Bass response is moderate. I like the fact that they came with 3 sizes of inserts to fit what you need. I've had them a few weeks now so I'll see how long they last. I have not contacted customer service for this product.

Bought this ear buds because of so many good reviews, just got it today and I did a comparison with a headphone then I realized right away the big difference: for the ear buds, the music base is nearly gone. Good part is wearing is more comfortable than many other ear plugs. Would not have bought this had I known all this. Amazon delivery, like always, is great.
summary: Why so many people like this thing ?

reviewText: UPDATE: I contacted customer service and they IMMEDIATELY shipped me another model. The service rep was awesome and didnt hesitate to say -quote- throw them away if they give you a headache. i will send you another right away. then contact me if they still bother you. -end quote-AWESOME!! The new headphones work just fine. i dont put them in my ear as deep, so that could be it - maybe my ears are sensitive to that. either way, they work swell. (i wish i could update the star rating, but im not sure how. i give it 4 stars).-----OLD REVIEW------PROS: extremely loud - volume on the lowest setting - clear, quality sound when playing music; great fit; awesome look; cord doesn't tangleCONS: wanna-be noise canceling blows; gives me a headache!I was so looking forward to these Jbuds after reading good reviews here. But when no music is playing they have a slight hiss - I take it it's the noise-canceling feature - that just bothers me. When music is playing it's less discernible, but i think my ears still are annoyed. I have slightly sensitive hearing - as in, I can tell when a tv is on and the audio is on mute (it still emits a sound). So this slight hiss really bothers me. I think these headphones look fantastic, and they fit well. It could be that maybe I just can't have earbuds, so then I'll just have to stick with classic headphones (over the head).I really like these if it weren't for the headache. It totally blows. I'd get these if they didn't have that wannabe noise-canceling hiss.I'm gonna give it another week. I'll try it with a different laptop, and at different times of the day. Then I'll return it if it doesn't redeem itself. *crossing fingers*
summary: UPDATE: NEW ONES WORK FINE (old review) Disappointed - gives me a headache!

reviewText: Sound is fine for my old ears. Choice of 3 size ear inserts let me get a good fit so they don't keep falling out like the standard iPod headphones.
I have been using these headphones for over a year and they are sturdy with good sound quality. I am buying a second pair to keep in my gym bag.

I purchase this Ear Buds to use them with my Ipod shuffle. My Ipod's Ear Buds where fine but they let to much outside noise in. So at the Gym that cause me a problem. In order to listen to my music I have to turn up the volume and even by doing that I keep listening to a mix of my music and the Gym music. What makes me buy this where the Noise-Reducing part but sadly this Ear Buds are so cheaply made that none of the advertise features actually work. Every part of this Ear Buds seems cheap and flimsy. I have a Sony walkman cellphone that came with a pair of Ear Buds and those are great in every sense. Even the Noise-Reducing feature works awesome I barely get any external noise even at low volume.
summary: You get what you pay for.... A pair of cheap Ear Buds

reviewText: When I ordered these ear buds, I never thought they'd be too big for my ears, but they are.  I'll have to purchase some other type of ear phones.
These ear buds work very well for around the house or for light exercise such as walking or biking. They have a long cord.

My ears a very sensitive, most earbuds are uncomfortable...and after awhile downright painful. These came with two extra tips, each is a different size. I found them extremely comfortable. I can wear them for long rides on the motorcycle. I will buy a couple more pairs.As for noise reducing, for earbuds they are very good. Earbuds have to be entered correctly into the ear to get the full effect. When entered correctly, these work well.I also like the fact that they do not bother others around me. In fact, my son didn't even realize I had them in one day... And he was sitting next to me on the couch. Now he wants a set too.
summary: Comfortable to use, sound is great.

reviewText: I love everything about these ear buds with one exception.  The cord is way to long and results in catching it on things which pops them out of my ears.

I used to go through ear buds ridiculously since I usually listen to music to lull me to sleep and by the morning the thin wired versions were quickly broken.  The sound quality in these is great--not very noise reducing though so I wouldn't't depend on them to act as noise cancellers but they last forever, sound good and take all sorts of abuse and don't break.  For this price can't be beat.
love these little ear buds , they have a wonderful sound and when your puppy chews them up you can replace them without having to cry
summary: the best  ever and great price

reviewText: The original earbuds that came with my 5th generation iPod were starting to irritate my ears--making them itchy and scaly. I had also purchased some noise-cancelling in-ear buds from Apple that were $40. Those worked well for cancelling outside noise, but keeping them in my ears was a big pain. I would have to fiddle with them for 15 minutes to get them to stay in for half an hour. I saw so many positive reviews for these earbuds and the price was half of the Apple earbuds, so I decided to order them.I don't know why, but these stay in my ears without any fiddling with them. It is almost as if they have glue on them but they don't. As some have pointed out, they do not have the best quality for sound, but I listen to podcasts and audiobooks mostly and they are perfectly fine for that. They are not 100% noise-cancelling. I can still hear outer sounds, but they muffle the outer noise much more than the regular earbuds. I haven't tried these on an airplane yet but I think they will work all right. If not, I will have my other two sets of earbuds handy. Bottom line: I am using these earbuds more often than the others now.

I love these earbuds! I had to buy new earbuds because the standard ones that come with the iPhone and iPod are just too big for my ridiculously small ears. When these arrived, they had three different sizes of tips. I used the smallest size and they were perfect. They conform to my ear and I can barely hear anything around me when I use them. I usually have to put just one in so I can still hear my kids if they're home with me. The sounds quality is also awesome. I can hear things that I didn't even know were there without the earbuds.

I really like these earbuds, I love the blue color they match everything that I intend on using them with. When JBuds said noise reducing they really meant it, I don't hear anything but what's coming through the earbuds. Compared to my expensive set of earbuds these seem to have a louder sound come through them which is great when I'm traveling and in other loud environments. The sound quality is awesome, I wasn't expecting a lot from these earbuds because of the low price but I was surprised by the quality and clarity of the sound. I had originally purchased these to be my back-up earbuds for the just incase my expensive pair were lost or broken but these have now become my go-to earbuds that I use with everything and my other ones have retired to be my back-up pair. They're very comfortable and you can wear them for hours without your ears feeling sore. For the price of these earbuds you can't go wrong, they're worth so much more because of the quality and clarity of sound you receive from them. I would refer everyone I know who loves their music to purchase these earbuds because they're awesome and you can't beat the price.
These are exactly what I wanted and work great.  Comfortable and well made.  Nice colors and good sound quality. Recommended.
The headphones worked great but they broke within about 4 weeks.  Oh well--glad they were too much money.  More like disposable.

I thought I was getting a FANTASTIC deal paying just $9.95 for a pair of ear buds that normally were $49.95, and maybe they are a fantastic deal to other people, but I would've paid more for better sounding ear buds. I have a pair of Skullcandy ear buds that I think are great. I lost one of the bud covers so I was looking around on Amazon for a replacement. I came across this deal and I bought the JBuds. To me, the JBuds are not nearly as clear sounding as my Skullcandy buds. I like that crisp, clear sound to music and the JBuds have a muffled sound to them. Needless to say, I was disappointed but it wasn't worth it to me to send them back. They sit in my bedside table drawer.

They look nice while matching the color of my Sansa Clip very well. The sound is also very good. I am not a big fan of therubber pieces that go in your ear. I have another brand that came with memory foam "marshmallow" and I put them on these earbuds instead and now they are more comfortable.Very Good for the price I paid - I think they were only 5.99 at the time

I was not impressed with these ear buds. The sound quality is not what I thought it would be. None of the rubber pieces seem to fit comfortably. They hurt my ears after using them for an hour or more. It's all right for a child or young adult. I will look into Skull candy next time. My teen son swears by them. LOL!
Not as good as I hope they would be, kind of sound muffled but okay.  Not worth sending back and I am using them.
works great really like them they do block out all of the sound from the traffic while walking thank u

The best ear buds headphone. very clear sound absolutely amazing headphones, I've tried more the 50 pairs of different headphones but these blow my mind for headphones under $10 they sound like they would cost $100. Try them you won't regret it. I give them 10 out of 10.

I simply refuse to pay more than ten dollars for a pair of earphones, because as soon as you step on them, hook them on the doorknob, slam them in the car door, etc., their history. So imagine paying seventy five or a hundred dollars for a pair of earbuds only to have that happen to them. The only problem with that attitude is that you end up sacrificing high quality sound from your phone or mobile/portable device for price. Well, not with JBuds! These are remarkable sounding earphones for a reasonable price. I caught these on sale at Amazon for less than ten dollars a piece, needless to say, I stocked up on them, and they come in all sorts of fashionable colors. Grab a couple of pairs for yourself, you can't go wrong, especially for the price.
summary: You can't go wrong with JBuds

reviewText: I bought this ear buds by reading a lot of reviews, I was dissapointed, the bass sucks and I can't go high volume levels comfortably, I bought the Apple ones again, I don't care if they brake easily, the sound can't be compared at all.2/10

I really like theses ear buds. They have good sound quality and are very comfortable in my ear. They come with 3 different sets of the cushions that go in your ear. Each set is a different size for people's varying comfort levels. I keep them around in case one comes loose and I need to replace it.  I had a pair for several years and left them behind on vacation. This is my second set!

Earbuds are unpredictable until you actually stick them in your ear. Which I suppose applies to a lot of things.These are comfortable and even come with some extra silicone ends if the set it comes with don't quite fit. The sound is really excellent and it does a pretty good job of fitting securely enough to block out some noise.I lose earbuds like most people: All the time. These work as well as some I have bought for 5 times as much and it will be a lot less painful when I lose them.In fact, maybe I should order a couple more pair...

I thoroughly enjoy these ear buds for the sound quality ranges:-quiet crispness of Rain Forest relaxation sounds-nuances of Classical Chamber Music-soulful vocals of Corinne Bailey Rae-speaking voices for audible books-movie dialog and soundtrack*Can't speak to rocking out or gaming since I don't do either.There's a selection of ear bud tips for a comfortable fit.Take the time to "burn them in" according to the directions supplied, it makes a positive difference.Last but not least, you can't beat the price for all the pleasure you'll receive. Happy Listening :)
summary: Good Value, Sound and Noise Reduction

reviewText: As a music enthusiast, I wanted see how these in-ear canal headphones do. Well, they were very dissapointing. There seems to be a new standard in headphones that provide a "SAFE" volume level that is incapable of damaging your ears. The sound was all there, mind you. Bass, treble, mid. But it lacks pop, oomph. There just clearly isnt enough air for good vibrations to occur in these headphonesPROS: Definately good for keeping outside noise to a minumum, great for planes, loud settings.CONS: Just get better headphones, they dont even stay in your ears if you give the cord a tug.

i may have received a defective product or whatever but that thing i returned sure doesn't have a noise-reducing feature. it instead has screeching noise whenever i tried to listen to a song on my computer. giving 2 stars since i was allowed to return it.
summary: not noise-reducing at all, has screeching noise

reviewText: I got these after reading promising reviews. First I'm comparing these to mySony MDR-E828LP Fontopia Earbuds with Winding Caseused with my iPod Nano. The J-Buds have little or no bass compared to the Sony's. The Sony's are clear, comfortable and inexpensive for $9. The JBuds sound muddy and and drone in the midbass. They do, however, block out peripheral noise better than the Sonys.They're not worth the hassle of sending back so I'll likely just use them as a spare pair.Try a set of the Sonys from a local discount store before you get these and you may find yourself with a good set of $9 earbuds.
summary: Save yourself $10 and get a pair of Sony's

reviewText: I didn't buy these expecting much; I just bought them to listen to music or lectures on my computer to not bother my room mates. They work great, have a good feel and were really cheap.

Good: It's cheap and very confortable (specially because it comes with 3 different sizes rubber covers).  Since you can choose the rubber which better adapts to your ears, besides being confortable it also provides some isolation.Bad: It's really nothing more than that.  It's 19 bucks headphone and this is exactly what you get, nothing more.  It's very fragile, the sound is regular (nothing really special) and the "Noise Reducing" is solely due to mechanical isolation.
summary: Fair - You get what you pay for

reviewText: I run a lot and these buds just don't stay in my ears.  Maybe my ears are just shaped odd, but I even tried the different size adapters that came with it and nothing worked.  They would stay in less than a quarter mile when I run.  For a normal lifting session with weights, they are fine and you get good sound through them because they seal into your ear.  But the constant jolting of a jog, just breaks them loose.  Now they hang in my truck and I use them for when I'm driving.  They are good quality and comfortable, but only for less active use.

I was skeptical, but these ear buds really do work.  I have a new mp3 player, and I used it in a crowded, noisy waiting room, and I had no problem hearing my music, in fact I was able to turn the sound down.  Well worth the money.
very good for the price; would recommend easily for those on a budget. So far durable and the kids love them for their comfort

Recently purchased a pair of J-Bud noise reducer headphones for my iTouch.  The price was so right I just couldn't pass them up.  They make the standard headphones sound terrible.  I wanted to go to BOSE or another product, but these serve the purpose so well and were so reasonably priced why look any farther!!  PastorJSLamb
Yes, there are plenty of better earphones out there but for the price and quality and can not go wrong!
These ear buds don't tangle as much as some I have ordered.  The sounds quality is good, and the color is nice.

I guess I have a small ear canal, because my iPod earphones keep slipping out and even if they stay in, they are not deep enough for me to hear the music well.  So I bought these Jbuds since they have the various size ear pieces and were rated highly and weren't that expensive.  I've used them once.  No matter which ear piece I use, they still won't stay in my ears and the sound isn't great out of them anyway.  Instead, I've found that by turning my Ipod earbuds sideways and putting them in that way, they stay in well and provide great sound.
summary: OK, but not what I needed

reviewText: The buds broke in about 2 weeks. Cheap and broke. All I can say, maybe its just the ones I got but I wouldnt buy again

These earbuds were part of an incentive package for a Sansa c250 I purchased.  They adequately cancel some background noise, and are superior to standard earbuds.  I do not find them comfortable to use for long periods of time (greater than 15-20 minutes).  I find that I tend to prefer the full ear cover headphones for the best noise canceling, however, these are lightweight and easy to carry, and they don't have the bulk associated with the full ear cover designs.
I AM WEARING THEM AS I TYPE THIS, IT IS VERY LATE, AND I AM BLASTING MUSIC IN MY EARS FROM THEM RIGHT NOW!
TheJBuds work very well and sound great. I would recommend these to anyone who listens to music or the radio on a portable device.

We have used our Sony ear buds for years with our portable DVD player and I wanted to get something for each of our lap top computers. I order these JBuds as they were on sale at a super price and after comparing them with the Sonys I ordered two more pairs with travel cases and retired the Sonys. In our opinion the JBuds have a much clearer sound. I would high recommend them.

The connection to 3.5 mm jacks is faulty at best. On my phone, laptop, or plugging into the jack on the speakers at my office, the crappy connection causes the stereo to cut in and out.Also, you have to jam these halfway down your skull to hear any kind of bass response. I wouldn't mind this as much if I could actually hear out of both sides of my head.I'd return these but really not worth the trouble of the $4 I paid.I guess you get what you pay for, ....
summary: These are some of the worst headphones I've ever owned.

reviewText: These headphones provide better sound quality than the headphones that came with your mp3 player, but there's still lots of room for improvement. Perhaps one of the greatest weaknesses is that the bass is weak unless you put these further down into the ear canal, where they start sounding a whole lot better. Unfortunately, that results in the stick and wire coming out at a 90 degree angle to the head - quite funny looking, and not good at all if you want to put on hearing protection over them.Then comes my worst complaint - they don't stay in if you sweat. I two miles two to three times a week, and these won't stay in over four minutes while running and sweating. If I turn my head to look both ways before crossing a street, they fall out. If I put my head down, they fall out. I became very frustrated with this after a while and went looking for another solution.I ended up going with some sennheiser sport earphones with a behind the neck strap. Perhaps those will be better.I find these have few redeeming qualities for me besides sounding a bit better than stock earphones.

I only use these to talk on the phone or listen to an occasional podcast so I cannot speak to how they make music sound. but they work just fine for me. I wish the speaker button also had volume but so far people seem to hear me ok and I can hear others just fine so I like it

These are good earphones, sound quality is acceptable, not bad at all, and for the price they are fantastic. The bass is decent and the treble is a bit better than with the earphones I've been using the past few years (theezGear SX50 ezEars SX50 earphones 2007 White.) The J-Buds are slightly less comfortable than the ezEars but I wouldn't go so far as to say the are uncomfortable -- I've worn them for as much as 11 hours straight and for many of those hours I forgot they were there. For the price you can't beat them.

I bought a pair of these headphones in January and I love them! I use these for my Ipod Nano for when I listen to podcasts and audiobooks when I go running. They're great. They fit my ears perfectly and drown out the outside noise. The sound is a lot more full than the sound on the headphones that came with the Ipod Nano, and these headphones have made my runs a lot more pleasant, since before, with my old headphones, the background noise was a bit distracting.Unfortunately, a week and a half ago, the sound went out on the left headphone, and would go on and off intermittently depending on the position of the cord. I e-mailed customer service and they sent me a brand new pair right away (as the product carries a one year warranty). I e-mailed them on Monday and got the new pair on Saturday. The customer service was GREAT!!In short, I love the headphones, the one year warranty, and the customer service. I recommend these headphones, and will certainly buy these again once!
summary: Great Value. Awesome Customer Service. Will Buy From Again.

reviewText: I bought this item due to great reviews here and needed noise reducing headphones for my daily commute. When I tried it, it did not reduce noise at all, despite trying all the earbud attachment sizes.  All background noise was unaffected.  Even the faintest background noise (such as the sound of water from the faucet) could still be heard 100%.  My wife tried these earphones and had the same conclusion.  I am returning this product.  The only advantage is the price and nice L-shaped connection jack.

i went from another pair of $20 sony ear buds to these, HUGE difference.  i put these on for the first time and was blown away:-there is much more volume, i never had any problems hearing my music over loud sounds-great bass, if you're looking for bass in cheap ear buds this is it-stayed in the ears pretty well, i doubt they would stay in while doing anything like running though-extremely comfortable, i never even felt them in.  they were perfect for sleeping until the wire torethe problem is the wires connected to the ear bud were torn out and now one ear bud died.  this was after only two months.  outside of sleeping with them on, i took good care of them.  it had to have happened when i was sleeping, but that is still disappointing.  i wore those sony ear buds in my sleep for 2 years and it never happened with those.in conclusion these are excellent if you're looking for cheap good quality ear buds and wont be sleeping with them on.

Package arrived quickly and was well packaged. Ear buds performed well out of the box irregardless of suggested break in period. Great sound quality (I have to keep sound almost all the way down or they're too loud). Too early to tell about durability. Silicone tips fit well and are comfortable. Would buy again and could see no real reason to purchase more expensive model (I'm a casual listener and use them with my Droid Eris phone).
I like the style and the sound is good but they keep falling off even when I changed the ear plug pieces that they give you.

Pros: the silicone ear pieces fit comfortably and snugly in your ears.Cons: I was extremely disappointed with these headphones given that the reviews are so high.  In fact, the earbuds that came free with my cell phone have a far better quality sound, as are my standard ipod headphones, and frankly, many other earbuds that don't have nearly the high reviews these have.  It all comes down to price; people like me have bought these thinking they'd get good quality for a low price, but in fact I'd have paid a little more to get better-sounding headphones.  Beware of a $10 price tag!
summary: Very Disappointing, Given the STRANGELY High Reviews

reviewText: I bought a couple of earbuds for my new Coby MP3 and liked these better, although I'm not sure about the noise reducing feature...

MY HUSBAND COMPLAIN ABOUT HIS EAR BUDS FALLING OUT HIS EAR, SO I GOT ON AMAZON AND SEARCHED FOR THE BEST REVIEWS AND THE CUSTOMERS WERE RIGHT. THEY COME WITH DIFFRENT SIZE ATTACHMENT BECAUSE NOBODY EARS ARE THE SAME HE LOVES THEM, HE SAYS THEIR BETTER THEN THE ONES THAT CAME WITH HIS MP3 PLAYER GREAT SOUND!!!!

These are very comfortable headphones. However, I've never had a pair that did not break within a year. Fortunately, JLab offers a 1 year warranty and will cover a replacement. These headphones are great on sound quality and comfort, unfortunately, the quality isn't that great.
summary: Good Sound, Very Comfortable but Semi-Decent Quality

reviewText: I bought these to replace my Fontopia earbuds that died out and disconnected after less than six months. I researched exhaustively and decided that the JBuds were worth a try, with the added bonus that they don't cost a fortune.I listen to a wide variety of music, and from the softest folky-pop to my favorite percussion-laden Blue Man Group, these earbuds have delivered excellent sound all around. They actually get better after about a month.I haven't noticed any distortion or significant loss of high or low frequencies. I'm not super critical about hearing every note or reverb, but I still know good sound quality when I hear it. The JBuds work very well with my iPod Nano.The earbuds themselves are a little harder than the Fontopias and therefore are not as comfortable. Even the smaller size buds seem a little big for my ears, but I can still wear them for long periods of time without much trouble. I'm very pleased with my purchase, even months after the fact. So far, the JBuds are showing better durability that the more expensive Sony's they replaced.

Not the best. But for five dollars these are outstanding. Decent noise cancelation and good average sound. I use these when I work out and they are pretty durable. Looking for good cheap and durable. These are it.

I go through headphones like crazy!!! I use them out in the field for work. I'm either losing them or they get snagged on something and break. These work great! My only problem is I was out in the rain and the microphone part got wet and died. The earphone parts work great still. I've bought 3 and I'm down to my last one.
There is a constant static background noise and the sound quality is very mediocre. You get what you pay for.
I am just trying to get used to this and i think it has been working good and the sound quality is great

These are great for the price.  I have some JVC ear buds that just wore out but the cables had some kind of coating on them and they never tangled in my gym bag.  It isn't a show stopper but I wish these had that coating.

Bought these thinking there would be better than the ones with my new SanDisk Sansa Clip MP3 player. But whereas they fit reasonably well, the sound is no better than those that came with the player.  I am still using them off and on but would not necessary purchase again. Price was very reasonable which made the purchase seem like a smart one.
?Works well with cell phones if you can use bluetooths.
summary: ? Works well with cell phones if you can ...

reviewText: these are good for the people who have hearing loss.  they fit inside the ear.  they have different sizes for all types of ears.
I like that these buds are loud, but the focus is on the bass which drowns out the highs. I had to mess with my equalizer to get a good balance out of them.

Sound Quality:  Sony MDR-AS20J[by a long margin][almost tied]Panasonic Slimz RP-HJE350K, JBuds original, iLuv City Lights EP322[not so good] SkullCandy ink'd S2INCB, Ult Ear 100Loudest[bars on Sansa]:  iLuv [3-], ink'd [3], Sony[3+], Panasonic [4-], JBuds [4], Ultimate Ears 100[4+]Recommendation:  JBud originals, and save $ for Sennheiser 300Bs or Klipsh S4sThe Sonys were the only earbuds that sounded close to a home stereo with headphones!  They are super comfortable.  On the down side, they don't seal out noise and the wires seem fragile and will tangle frequently.Coltrane's saxophone on "Moments Notice" was the hardest to reproduce.  The Sonys were excellent, the iLuvs were decent, the JBuds and Ult Ear 100s sounded poor, the rest were terrible.The Panasonics sound would still rate second, well behind the Sonys with all the music.  The Panasonic wires tangle.  The iLuvs sound was close to the Panasonics and the wires were manageable.  The iLuvs would extend playing time because they need the least volume.  But, the buds are large, seemed to want to fall out, and may not be super comfortable.The JBuds were the least expensive and sounded OK, but the bass is weak.  These are very comfortable buds.  Wires were manageable, but had a straight plug.  The Ultimate ears sound was poor.  The wires were so stiff they would pull the buds out.The Skullcandy ink'd were disappointing.  [EZ, SC fans!]  "Eruption" was electric, better than my home stereo headphones.  They are efficient and reproduce deep bass notes you don't even hear with the others.  But, the saxophone on "Moments Notice" was unnatural and the other tracks sound hollow and distant.  The ink'd were new, they may improve with break in.  Setting the Sansa EQ to HipHop helped the horn, but overall still no match for the Sonys or the Panasonics.  The wires are a little too stiff and the plug is straight.Tested these earbuds by pausing mid-song and changing buds on a Sansa Clip Zip.  Compared, by pairs, to determine the subjective quality of each against the others.  Tracks used:  "Take Five," Dave Brubeck;  "Belong," R.E.M.; "Bring Me To Life," Evanescense; "Atomic Dog," George Clinton; "Wild Thing," Tone-LOC; "Eruption," Van Halen; all ripped from personal CDs with Windows Media Player[320kb/s] and "Moments Notice," John Coltrane from Amazon MP3.
summary: Low price earbuds using a consumer grade source.

reviewText: not too bad of ear phones. Alright sound for the price. couldn't expect more for the price. If you wand quality sound, you will have to spend a lot more.

I have plenty of pairs of headphones, earbuds, etc. What I was looking for was a low-cost, comfortable pair that didn't fall out of my ears every time I moved an inch. That is what I got with this product. It also does a fine job of noise reduction, though not perfectly. The smallest of the sizes of the provided plastic "covers" fit me perfectly. I barely know they're in my ears, and they stay put. As others have noted, the treble hiss can be a little high, but if you're an audiophile 100% of the time then you'd likely purchase a high-end product in the first place.Update: July 2012:Just last week they started to fail (the left earbud started to sputter out randomly) and in short order it just died. The right side is still working but they do now need to be replaced. I got three full years of regular (sometimes daily) use out of them so that has more than made them worth the money.
summary: Slightly Tinny But A Good Value

reviewText: Literally the worst sounding earbuds I've ever heard, these things are overpriced at a paltry $8. Even if someone offered to pay me to use them, I still wouldn't use them over whatever stock junk came with my smartphone.The audio quality from these things is hard to explain, given how terrible it is. Imagine how an mp3 file sounds when it's been way over-compressed (say, 64kbps). Now imaging listening to it through pair of cans connected with string. That's still better than how these things sound.Yes - they're really that bad. Do NOT buy for any reason.
summary: Literally the worst sounding earbuds I've ever heard

reviewText: Great sound quality.  If you are looking for ear buds for your ipod, especially during a workout routine, these are fantastic.  The best thing for me is that they do not fall easily out of my ears, like so many others do.  Some stereo geek may have something other to say...they are not Bose...and they are not, but they also aren't $100.00+.  I find them to be perfect.

fits the ear, the mic works and the earbuds seal well. Fits my ear better than the Apple originals (which fall out). Very happy with high quality sound.  Earbuds fit either ear so no looking to see which is left/right.

I've been listening to books on my commute and found that I couldn't get some of the audio books loud enough to even hear them.  Plus I couldn't get the typical ear buds to stay in sometimes.  These have solved both of those problems.  I can get as much volume as I want and they don't fall out of my ears.  The sound is clear and understandable.  And they were much cheaper than some of the "high end" ear buds.

I used this pair 5 days a week for 16 months before they fell apart. In the positive category, the quality of sound and comfort. On the negative side they were loose, I could never use these during any physical activity or they would fall out. Overall if you like this style of earbud and have small ears it will cost you less then a $1 a month. I on the other hand will be replacing them with something else.
Exactly as described. Came in on time and the sound is exceptional. Would definitely recommend this product to anyone wanting high quality at a low price.
these do a great job for the money. they sound good, fit in my ear well and don't feel uncomfortable.
summary: I really enjoy not hearing my co-workers!

reviewText: The sound wasn't bad considering the price point, but one of the ear buds went out not even three weeks after purchase.edit: Ended up getting another pair since they're so cheap in the hopes that they would be better. Again, good quality sound, and the second pair lasted much longer, but only just over three months of regular use.

I have small ears and I've never been able to use regular ear buds.  They always slipped out.  After getting an iPod for Christmas and not being able to listen to my music without old-fashioned "headphones," I purchased these.These little buds have 3 sizes, and the smallest fit my ears perfectly.  They don't slip a bit, and they are soft and rubbery and fit all the way around, so not only are they super comfortable, my music sounds great.  The sound quality is better than the ear buds that came with the iPod (I'm not an expert, so I don't know if that's saying much).  But for the super low price, the comfort and the sound quality.. these just can't be beat.

I bought a set of these several months ago.  I'm not the type who pays that much attention to varieties of sound (highs, lows, etc) so that wasn't an issue with me.  The issue for me was comfort.  I had surgery years ago that left one ear shaped just a tad different from the other.  It also left the sound going into that ear a bit tinny (thus my disregard for sound quality).  At the time I purchased these, I also purchased several other types of headphones from different companies, looking for a comfortable fit.  These were a perfect fit.  And the sound quality was so good on them that I didn't notice the tinny sound in the damaged ear.I just bought two more pairs.  One to keep for use at home, reserving the pair I already own for use on my mp3 player, and leaving one as a spare in case anything happens to one set.I highly recommend these to anyone who has a problem with other earphones or headphones that just don't fit right.

they hurt my ears, although I know everyone's ears are different.  I can't keep them in so I took off the outer rubber thingy.  But the sound quality is so poor I am not using them.  I will keep them in the car only if I need a back up some day.
Purchased for my wife and her arm radio. She uses on walks and really like the ear buds, they do not bother her ears, and claims they work really well.
Amazingly good reproduction for their size and cost. The variety of sizes of buds makes it perfect for easy insertion to the earways for good listening.

The JLAB JBuds are excellent in-ear headphones, with great bass, clarity, and noise reduction... when they work...I bought this product about 5-6 months ago. When I got them out of the plastic package, I loved them. Then they died 5 months later. Now, I can only get sound if I hold it in one precise position.Many times, I only have sound in the right ear. I cannot move without having no sound.I do admit I have been a bit ruff with these headphones (wrapping them around my iPod mini when not in use), but I do not think good headphones should do this...But since they're only $20, I am getting another pair.
summary: Great sound for 6 months, then no sound...

reviewText: The big selling factor for me is that these come with rubber tips (in various sizes) that are far more comfortable than the ear buds that came with my ipod nano.  I agree with other reviewers that calling them noise reducing is a bit much, but for the price, they do the job.  The rubber tips also help to keep the ear bud in your ear when you are running or moving around a lot; something the Apple ear buds don't do.The one negative for me was that the audio jack for the ear buds isn't compatabile with the plastic case I bought to protect my ipod.  The ear buds that came with the ipod have a narrow audio jack, while these have a much wider one.  This probably isn't a big concern for most people, but it may cause problems if you have other ipod accessories.Overall, if you don't want to pay alot and just want a everyday, "knock-around" set of ear buds, this is the product for you.  If you are looking for super high-quality sound and performance (and don't mind paying $80-$100), then you should look elsewhere.
summary: Good Ear Buds for the Price

reviewText: After reading a ton of reviews and seeing that this is one of the most purchased ear buds on Amazon, I thought, "Why not? I'll buy 'em" — What a mistake!The sound from these ear buds are so flat without any bass whatsoever. I have a pair of cheapo plastic earbuds that aren't even "in-ear" and they sound like a pair of Sennheiser's compared to these. It literally sounds like I stuck a cotton ball in between my ear drum and the ear buds... that's how flat these are.

I bougt this item to be a good ear bud with some noise reducing ability, and that is what it does.  Not the best sound quality, but then its not one of the more expensive ear buds.  The sound is good, not great, but it does deliever on the noise reduction. It's a good buy for the money, if you want really good sound , this probably is not what your looking for.
The sound is really good on these ear buds for the price.  I would recommend ordering these to anyone that wants to save some $$.

As I pulled this up to re-order another pair (not because my old ones don't work, there are still working in A+ condition, I just need a 2nd pair for 2nd ipod), I noticed that it was back in November 2006 that I ordered that first pair.  Those still work great.  Before buying this I remember trying several different earbuds, including that dreaded apple pair that comes with the ipods, and they were all so uncomfortable in my ears.  Hated them.  These are very comfortable to wear for an extended period of time.  The sound that comes out of these little buds is amazing.  The only other type of headphones I have tried that I would even consider buying over these would be the Bose over the ear (if I ever get the courage to spend $200 on a headphone set).  Besides the Bose, nothing else compares when you look at price ($10 a set!), sound and comfort in one earbud.  Very happy with the first pair over 2 years ago, so I am now a happy re-peat buyer!  Worth the $10, and then some!
These buds fit as horribly as the cheap white ones you get with your iphone.  They do not fit and I have to shove them in my ear every 15 seconds or so.  Very annoying.
summary: These buds do not fit in your ears.

reviewText: I really like this product. I find that it stays in my ear well and it's not uncomfortable. I had stayed away from ear buds because of  size and fit. The little stems make placing and removing this product a breeze.

I paid $15, relatively low in terms of Hi-Fi earbuds. If Coby can sell "Super Bass" models on Amazon at around $5 or $6 which perform quite well, I don't see why this earbud should have been such a weak performer. These earbuds are some of the most poorly performing I have seen (at the price). Bass output is way down from that of the actual recorded music I am listening to.
summary: Weak bass, highs ok but not impressive - not worth money paid.

reviewText: The fact that the full price on these headphones is $20 is absurd. I paid around $6, which is more reasonable. These headphones sound decent, but they do not contain the sound at ALL. My roommate said he couldn't sleep cause he could hear my music from across the room. Granted, a college dorm room isn't huge, but my volume wasn't even all the way up. More importantly, though, the construction of the headphones is not good at all. Right under the bud the wire is extremely flimsy, and became exposed within days of using it. They still functioned, but they were close to ripping off entirely. There are some better $5 headphones out there (cough cough Panasonic cough cough) Although in my long quest for cheap headphones i've realized that i should just stop being a cheapass and invest in more expensive headphones..i'm almost positive all the cheap headphones i've gone through over the years has costed me a fortune. If you aren't careful with your headphones and use them alot, avoid this one.
summary: Bought for $5, still returned it anyway

reviewText: While these JBUDS did not, in a side by side comparison, provide as much surrounding, warm sound as my Sennheiser 212 headphones, they provided excellent clarity, especially on KJAZZ radio. Talk formats are also excellent. The comfort is surprisingly good for an in-ear bud. For 20 dollars, this is a great substitute for the cheaper buds that come with most MP3 players.Update on 12-21-06: I've come to be more impressed with my JBuds over the last two weeks, marvelling at the bright, crisp, and yes, warm sound that comes out of these inexpensive buds. Perhaps, as I've read in some of the headphone information that is out there, that there is a "breaking in" period, which has something to do with loosening the tranducer. In any event, I'd have to give these JBuds another star.Second Update 10-8-07: My only complaint about the JBuds is that sleeping with them at night I will sometimes wake up and the bud will have fallen off. I can't secure the buds to my satisfaction; however, the JBuds are so comfortable I deal with this problem.Third Update 1-7-08: The sound is not quite as good as the slightly more expensive V-Moda; however, the JBuds are easier on my ears for long-term (I sleep with them on) listening. Also the JBuds have a longer extension and don't pull out of the radio or iPod headphone jack as easily as the V-Modas, so again on balance the JBuds are better.
summary: Good Value at This Price Point

reviewText: UPDATE: Original review below. I purchased a second set of earbuds after I lost sound in my first set. I figured for the price it was okay if I only got a few months use out of them. However the second set lost sound in one ear within a few weeks. I put up with it because I usually wear these while riding a bike, so most of the time I only have one bud in to allow me to hear road noise and approaching cars. A couple weeks later I lost sound in the other ear. Needless to say, I won't be buying these again. At this rate I might as well buy a set of the Apple earbuds that will last me significantly longer and have better features.ORIGINAL REVIEW: Decent sound. No volume control on the cord, which is frustrating when the phone is in your pocket. Lasted 3-4 months before I lost sound in one earbud. They are what I expected for the price.

These JBuds ear buds does not cancel noise, but does reduce them due to their firm fit while wearing.  The music quality is good--clear highs, and suprisingly, you can hear the bass.  I would buy another set of these if the ones I have now stops working.
summary: These JBuds ear buds just plain works.

reviewText: Good sound, comfortable.  A great backup for my much more expensive Etymotic earbuds, with only a little loss of quality.
I needed new headphones for my iPod and these are doing a good job of that for now.  I use them at the gym.

These fit my ears well.  They cancel the outside noise well.  I like the freq. response, although I have a Philips pair that have better bass and more extended highs.  However the sound is clean with these earbuds.  You can't go wrong with them.  I have a couple of pair - and a Y adapter.

reviewerName: Modern Blue Argonaut "No I do not have a shoe...
reviewText: The list price on these ear buds is very unrealistic. I bought both the black and the white ear buds as replacement sets for my children's mp3 players. My son kind of likes them. They're well made and the sound quality is a bit better than the ones he had. Surprisingly, they seemed pretty much on par with the set that came with my daughter'sBarbie Girls 1GB MP3 Player - Green - Store 240 Songs!.I would have liked them better if they included acarrying case. When the kids put their mp3 player into their backpacks the headphones can get damaged by books and getting caught on binders. Considering the list price, I was expecting a small protective case. But, for ten bucks, you truly get what you pay for and this is a good set for that price.
summary: You get what you pay for

reviewText: It's ok, but the quality is just a notch better than the ear buds you buy at the dollar store for $1!
summary: No worth the trouble of ordering online

reviewText: Unfortunately, the product compatibility grid is incorrect. The plastic molding on the 3.5mm plug is too large and too far down the shank of the plug to engage with an iPhone. Because I purchased this for use with an iPhone it does not do what I need it to do. I would rather not rate the item, as I am simply unable to use it, but Amazon won't allow a review without a rating. Therefore, I must give it a single star, since it does not do what it needs to do... I am finding out what JLabs support is like, having submitted a support request.

I was looking for good quality at a good price and I found it with these ear buds, I needed them for a replacement at the plane and these did great. I will be getting a new pair soon just in case I need them.
bought this ear buds for my office computer. works great.very nice sound sound. like the option for different colors. very comfortable in ear.
These are cheap and good phones. Good bass quality (a little too much sometimes). Can't beat them for the price.

When I first got the phones, I replaced the attached inserts with the smallest ones that were included in the box.  It was easy and once done, I was able to use my phones with perfect comfort.  The sound is very good. I as most happy with the very low cost of these phones.  I can't use ear buds that came with my Zen. So I am glad to finally have phones that fit well and sound superb.

These are the best ear buds that can be had for less than $100. I haven't tried more expensive ear buds, so that's all I can comment on. They blow those crappy, overpriced skull candy ear buds out of the water. When you get a good seal on these buds, they produce really tasty sounds from very low to very high. The bass response is very deep and tight. The highs are very crisp. The mids are very true. The instructions tell you to play them loudly for a day or so for them to break in. Follow the instructions, because the bass really opens up after you break them in. I plugged them into my home stereo and cranked them much louder than I would be able to stand them in my ears. I put the ear bud ends in a shoe box and closed it so I wouldn't hear them all over the room. After the break in, I was floored by the sound.
I did not expect these ear phones to be that great judging by the price but I was wrong. They sound great for ear phones this size.

I purchased these last week at an unbelievable $9.95 one time purchase price.  Today I am ordering two more.  They sound great.  I am not a pro when it comes to headphones, but I have had many pairs of headphones.  For earbuds, these headphones are able to pick up ranges from the deepest of bass to high treble.  They are not tinny sounding like other earbuds and I am definitely surprised how great they sound for the price.  These are better then my apple ipod white brand.  The package also comes with three sized of ear buds, small, medium and large for whatever size ear hole you have.  Highly recommend.
summary: Very Surprised.  Nice Quality.  Sounds very clear.

reviewText: I don't know what I was expecting; hope springs eternal, I suppose. This is a lousy unit and if you want a set for music, find a better unit. We have flushing toilets with better sound.
I needed an extra pair of ear buds, so I decided to try these.  The sound clarity is good, but the buds sometimes slip out of my ear, especially when I am working out.
These are pretty good, and sound almost as good as the Sennheiser ones I bought that cost ~40. A good value.
Sounds like listening to audio through balls of cotton or wadded up something.  Sound is muted, far away, muffled, muddy. JUST AWFUL. I'm returning these
summary: I wish i could give less than 1 star

reviewText: Love them, very comfortable, which is what i was looking for and not easily tangled. Would buy again, I also bought a case for them.

These are FAKE! I ordered 2 (black/blue and black/black). Received them yesterday. They are incredibly cheaply made, and I'm sure these are fake. I have original JLabs to compare them with. The buds are a cheap shiny plastic, and the microphone has NO VOLUME or ON/OFF control, unlike what you see in the photo.I'm sending both sets back. Luckily I only opened one; hope that Amazon will refund me for both.
the earbuds are not amazing but is ok! i like the color, i get one purple and one blue! they sound good...

If you are a person like me who has ear wax (which means many of you are like me), you will end up finding a good chunk of ear wax on the earbuds since they go right inside your ear. I just received my earphones today and that is the main issue I have with them, since if my friends ever want to listen to my iPod Touch I'll have to secretly wipe away my "ear trash".However, these earphones have excellent sound since they go right in the ear with a good amount of bass. Like it says in its title, these ear phones are noise-reducing, but not completely of course. Overall, the sound is slightly louder than the iPod's original headphones and have deeper sound. The wire is about 50% long than the iPod's which is a good thing if you are playing sports and need some more flexibility. Another concern of mine is that I am worried that the exchangable ear buds might come off in my pocket because they are kind of easy to put on and take off.

These are a lot more comfortable than standard ear buds but my ear still gets a little tired after a long trip with them (3-4 hours).  They seem to be made well; I have knocked them around a little in the month I had them and they are still working well.  They didn't work well when I tried running while using them; they pick up the bumps from my feet (this is probably the case with all ear buds).I noticed the bass does get better after a few days but I mainly listen to talk so I have no sound complaints.
summary: More comfortable than standard ear buds

reviewText: I use this earphone mostly for workout and its great. It's a nice fit with great sound. I've had it for almost a Year and it still in good condition.

This speakers offers great sound for my money, being the cheapest one that I could find here are amazing.I really love the adapters because my ear caveat is really small and I should use the little one of these adapters.Now I have my music on the road...again.

actually  i expected  less  from this but  what  a good surprise  they  are great  good bass and  treble  ..the cord is long enough  to do everything  without to bother at all  they came well packed  and protectedand trust me once you put them in yours ears you wont be able to hear almost anything even if the sound is off  ..nice  noise reducingnot complains...
although they sound good, i don't feel they are different from others, and don't feel the noise reduction, the cord started getting rigid and is about to break
Good sound quality, might wanna tinker with the size of the buds if you have small ears.  My girl had some trouble getting them to stay in for long periods of time with the 2 larger size covers.

I love these earbuds. They weren't expensive but the sound quality is fabulous. They really are noise reducing. They come in several colors and of course I picked pink they are adorable. Would buy this item again.

Wishing I wasted my money somewhere else. Was at school yesterday and wen I clicked the mic to change songs the top part of it fell off and was lost, exposing the button and 2 wires, pos and neg.Covered it in electric tape and now just can't use the mic/button. Headphones are crappy but that was expected. As a college student, this is all I could afford.
My son was looking for some good ear phones, we got it today and that exactly what he wanted. Thank you for this product.

I bought these for work 2 months ago (I have a normal desk job) and so far, so good. They're durable. I manage to roll over the cord with my chair a lot.The sound is great.Best cheap headphones I've tried.
i didnt even look at the picture probably and i hate this types of headphones. only lasted a month before one of the ears stopped working, i am not buying this again.

For cheap earbuds these are fantastic. Good sound, fit well and are pretty durable. I ordered multiple pairs and have been very pleased with them. Audiophiles might not like them but for most people these are great.

As advertised, comes with three different size ear cushions. Plug is straight which is good for a player in a pocket. Sound is very good and price is excellent. Would order again if I needed another set.
not bad not very good, don't think you will get much from it sound is good but not as good as you expect from large headsets.

Wasn't expecting much because of the low price. All I wanted was an improvement over the sound of the apple buds that came with my iPhone. These are a drastic improvement. I could have paid $100-$200 for some really fantastic sounding earbuds, but I'd almost certainly lose them. These are so inexpensive I bought one set for work and one set for my gym bag.

I bought the JBuds Hi-Fi Noise-Reducing Ear Buds (Black) in June 2008. I used them daily at work (8 hrs a day).  I really liked the way they sound; not the best, but good for the price.  They were actually more comfortable than the Bose ear buds they replaced and didn't constantly fall out of my ears.  I am really disappointed because today the left bud stopped working.  If I would wiggle or lightly push on the cable the left bud would work again.  This is the identical issue I had with the Bose buds, but at least I'm only out $20 bucks vs the $100 I paid for the Bose ear buds. The search for buds that will last at least a year continues...
summary: Initally quite pleased, but today not so much...

reviewText: I have had the buds for a while. I have trouble  keeping the ear bud style in my ears and these are no different. I use them under ear muffs and they work fine that way.

These ear buds were pretty good. Good sound, comfortable, did a decent job at noise cancellation, up until they break down. I had two pairs that broke down on me, some kind of problem with the connection near the jack. I'm switching.

I purchased a pair through amazon about 10 months go.  They got occasional to moderate use. One earbud no longer produces any sound. It took five days of emails and daily phone calls (straight to voicemail each time) to receive any response. It was actually the email that mentioned the awful review I had put up on Amazon that finally got a response and a new pair was shipped out that week.
summary: One bud failed - iffy customer support

reviewText: Straight and simple, these are the best headphones under $20.00.  I have tried nearly every headphone with my various Ipod devices.  Most recently I tried the Coby headphones which I thought were fairly decent at the $5.00 price point.  As I am prone to losing headphones or having my children destroy them, I am simply unable to spend $60.00 a set like some of my friends.  These fit the bill and deliver more than the price indicates.Comfort is incredible.  You actually forget they are in since the design does not require you to force the bud into your ear. JBuds supplies a total of 3 sets of silicone ear buds to fit your ear.  Out of the box, they fit mine perfectly.  They hang down perfectly in the ear providing additional stability.Sound is impressive.  There was definately a break in period of about 5 hours (everyone reports different times).  I am not an audiophile but I could easily tell the difference between these and all the others.  Clarity is great and tones seem dead on.  But once again, I am not an audiophile and there are people who demand the absolute best in sound that would surely disagree. Note that some reviewers report distorted bass and compare the buds to Sennheiser's sold at $27.00 plus.  I did not find such distortion but do not have Sennheiser's to compare.From my perspective, there is no reason to buy any other headphone unless you are truly into the very best sound, which will send you to the $60.00 plus range.  However, it is important to remember that earbuds are simply that- earbuds.If you get these at the $10.00 price point, it is too good of an opportunity to pass up.  If you have kids needing headphones, get these.  I plan on stocking up.

I love the look of these, and they are also very comfortable. I'm funny about wearing things in my ears or on my face, so for me, a comfortable ear bud is hard to come by. These fit the bill. Love 'em. And at $10, you can't beat them.I bought some for my daughter too, and she also thinks they're the cat's meow as ear buds go.

im not sure if the pair i purchased is a fluke since there are thousands of 5 stars  or these buds are typically sound this terrible. i honestly feel that a $15 pair of junk skullcandies at your local drug store will have at least 2x as much bass (as in 200% more) and 25% more highs than these earbuds. for comparison, these buds sound WORSE than your $1.00 or free airline over-the-ear phones for watching movies - WHILE THE PLANE is flying.CONS: highs are tinny or cut off, midrange is muddy while lows are non-existent.PROS: both voice coils seem to be working. i like the vacuum sealed bag that the buds came in.i bought these to keep in the car when i have to go shopping, stand in line, wait for someone and not be worried if it got tore up.there are some earbuds that need a small "burn-in" time to bring out the highs or lows. im not sure if burning these in will make a difference.can someone please offer some advice? criticism or suggestions appreciated. if my expectations are too high feel free to let me know.im not expecting any combination of great highs + midrange + lows from this price bracket but please at least give me one of the three decently.
summary: worst earbuds i have ever worn

reviewText: Using these on my new Sansa Clip. Good, cheap combo for working out and active stuff. Still haven't fully "broken in" these buds, but been listening for a few hours while walking and working out and the sound is improving. A bit muddy at first but improving. I know good sound and I'm not expecting audiophile quality from these. They are fun to listen to, with enough oomph and definition to enjoy. I can hear the difference between lossless and mp3, they are good enough to tell that. They work well as earplugs too, block most sound but you can still talk to people if you need to. Great for workouts, the buds stay in place, and there are three sizes of silicone to try for your fit.Good enough sound so far, waaaay better than ipod earbuds and most other cheap headphones. Definitely a bargain at $10, not cr@ppy and worth picking up.
These work for me, sound good, and feel comfortable, and as far as I can tell, the noise-reducing feature does help with extraneous sounds.

There is a lot to be positively said for this pair of ear buds; they fit, the sound is clear and of great fidelity, and they are cheap. The cord is long (approx 56"), much longer than the standard 3 1/2 to 4 ft of other cords. What this means is that I can mount my iPod on a waist band and it will reach my ears while I'm on a  treadmill without any short cord problems. These buds worked perfectly ... for almost 3 months. Then the sound quit out of one bud and became intermittent. Upon examining the cord I discovered that it was thin and overly flexible, and that it was only a matter of time before the plastic encased wire connection would break. It did.UPDATE: Who Knew? Apparently some companies actually pay attention to these comments on Amazon. See the attached comment from JLab Audio. A replacement for my non-working earbuds is on the way to me. Kudos to JLab.

I initially reviewed this item very unfairly.  I did not have the ear buds inserted all the way.  I have been used to using the headphones that come with an IPod and did not realize the importance of the fit for performance.  The headphones come with three different sizes of the silicone ear pieces and these make the world of difference.  At first I was not using the correct size which made the difference in sound quality.  If the fit is not correct the sound is very empty with no base.  With the correct fit they do produce a nice full sound.  I am considering the J3's to just experience the full potential.
based on so many good reviews, i wanted to give these ear buds a try. what a disappointment :(  the sound quality is $*it!!!! I would not recommend them to anyone  :(
I use these all the time.  Have worked great and still do. Use them and enjoy the tunes.  Recommend this and the seller.
i love my j buds, they are no beats by dre, but definitely just as good as any other set.
Good earbuds for the money.  Very comfortable with changeable ear inserts.  Good value for the price.
Good and cheap headphones. It has worked well and held up OK.  There's not much else to say about them.

I purchased these headphones from Amazon a little more than a year ago.  For the price, these headphones are great - they sounds great and the earbuds have different sizes to fit in your ear.  My complaint is that I purchased these headphones and it is now broken - only one earbud works and the sound in the other earbud is going in and out.  This is actually the second time that I purchased these earphones and the same thing happened to my previous earphones.  This is not a major issue since I have had the earphones for a little more than a year and for the price, you cannot ask for too much.  However, this is a deciding factor in my rating of 4 instead of 5.  Otherwsie, the headphones sound great - I wear it to workout/run and it stays in the ear.
summary: Solid headphones - lasted for a little more than a year

reviewText: Gets the job done, no questions asked. When it comes to noise reduction, it's not the best piece around; for the price paid, its OK. The mic works decently. Do not expect to purchase amazing earphones with these; do expect, however, something that works reliably and consistently, with a bad to moderate performance when it comes to sound quality. If quality of sound is what you're looking for, do not buy this product!

I just got a pair of these and I'll keep this short and to the point! Search for SkullCandy Ink'd and buy a pair of those instead. Depending on the color you choose those can also be picked up for [...]. These JBuds are OK, and probably worth 10 bucks, but the Skull Candy Ink'd model sound much, much better. The highs are higher and more crisp and the lows have a lot more bass as well. (The Jbuds have more of a muffled sound to them.) I also own a pair of Skull Candy Full Metal Jackets and those are incredible as well. Those will set you back 70 dollars or so but very much worth it if you are serious about your music.
