BTW I bought 6 pair of the Ink'd buds at Christmas for everyone in my family and all of them are still working just beautifully!I have read that these JBuds need a little "breaking in" so if things improve I'll stop back by and edit this review.

These earbuds look good, are low-priced, comfortable, and they do a pretty good job of staying in my ears whereas many other brands fall out. They also eliminate most outside noise and  have very good sound quality. I'd easily buy them again and at $20 they can't be beat.

The noise reduction was not as much as I expected, but still very good, especially for the money and the convenience.They were effective and helped me tolerate an airplane flight with a screaming child.

None of the inserts fit me perfectly, but the small ones are fine and rarely fall out.  The sound quality started out good, but I'm not an audiophile so I really didn't think much of it.  Now that I've been using them for a couple weeks, however, I am finding myself stunned by the quality of what I am hearing.  When I listen, I feel like THIS is what the artist and sound engineers meant for me to hear!All this at a very low price point.  I don't think you could buy BAD headphones at this price in a box store.  These are outstanding.Con:  The cord can be too long for mobile listening, it hangs down almost to my knees so I have to stuff the excess in a pocket.  But it means I can use these for other audio sources comfortably, so it can also be a good thing.

I go to sleep listening to my favorite radio news show. These earbuds sit pretty flat in my ear and don't hurt if I lie on my side. The sound quality is pretty good, even at this price point. Best of all, if the dog eats this pair as she has eaten so many before, including two $100.00 pair, I won't cry.

JLab Jbuds fit perfectly and are very comfortable. I was also surprised they came with additional ear pieces. Overall great value and very good for the price. Perfect for riding with Amtrak.Not sure what all the bad reviews are for. These are $8 on Amazon, if you are looking for stunning quality, get Bose. These are for your basic use. Sound is slightly high but I can always adjust the audio from my phone. Mic is key and works with any phone. I think this is a great product and I will continue to purchase these to replace older ones!

I bought these because no other earphones worked for my dog. She likes to listen to music, but I get really tired of hearing Massenet all day. Honestly, after a while you'd think she would branch out.Anyway, I purchases these thinking, since they're noise canceling, she can listen to this as loud as she wants and it still won't bother me. Plus they're cheap, perfect for a dog, right? WRONG! These are not good at all. They won't even stay in my dog's ears. None of the sizes works right. Even when I can eventually get them to stay in, they seem to bother her because she tries to pull them out. Plus the cord drags all through the mud, and is way to long. No matter where I attach my dog's ipod, the cord still drags. None of the other reviews mention this! We are both very upset with the quality of this product. I don't know what I shall do. I guess I can still try them on my cat...

Just what the doctor ordered so that everyone does not have to listen to my stuff!!  They fit so well, and there are THREE extra  sets of ear thingmes in the pack and the carrying case is neat and small so I am happy with this product!!  Oh by the way-- the sound quality and clarity is excellent!!

Tried these according to the reviews on the internet. They are great for the price but the quality is adequate but not as I expected. These are good but they are somewhat hollow in sound quality. You get what you pay for.
These earphones aren't that great. For the money i'd get JVC Xtreme Xplosivs. But these didn't break so thats good.
My laptop speaker output sucks (don't they all?)... so these pods come in handy for movies, youtube, and whatever without having to lug around external speakers.

reviewerName: Pierre El Capitan de Castanets Enimigo
reviewText: Sometimes you need a little peace and want to listen to some tunes.  Well these guys get the job done.  After a while fitting hurts my ears.  I wouldn't say it's a design flaw; I haven't used/owned an ear bud that is comfortable for multi-hour or consecutive day use.
summary: Sound good but hurt my ears after a while

reviewText: The Jbuds have very good sound, but certainly little or no noise reduction except by the normal blockage of the ear canal. If the objective is noise reduction, look elsewhere; if the objective is a good and inexpensive earphone, consider these earphones.

I have gone through A TON of earphones. Let me say that these are amazing....They do have some cons though. At first, they are hard to plant in your ears, and then after a while, your ear may become slightly sore. The bass is outstanding though and you cannot hear anything at all when they are in use! Definitely buy the J2 ones if not these!

These were purchased for my 5 year old son to play his 3DSXL on our trip to Hawaii.  The OEM ones that came with his console were to big for his ears.  The sound quality is marginally better thatn the OEM set.

When I purchase a new piece of sound equipment, one marker of its sound quality is how frequently I revisit old favorites just to see how they sound.  Suffice to say, I've been glued to my iPod for several days.I've spend three times this price on far-inferior ear buds.  They're comfortable (coming with three different sized rubber tips), they do a better than decent job of eliminating outside noise, and most importantly, the sound is impressive.  Even before doing the burn-in recommended by the instructions, they sound great.  For around $10, this is an unbeatable value.  For those concerned about use during exercise, they've stayed in just fine for me, and the instructions come with an additional helpful hint:  simply loop the generous cable over the top of your ear.  It's still comfortable, but adds an additional layer of security.You'd be hard-pressed to find better sounding ear-buds in this price range.  If you need a replacement set or are simply looking to upgrade the cheapies that came with your MP3 player, stop shopping:  You've found what you're looking for.
summary: Believe the hype:  Unparalleled Value Here

reviewText: I have been using the Sony earbuds for a few years of cycling and thought I'd try something else. So, I decided to try these earbuds.The Good:1 - Sound Quality is Excellent.2 - The Fit is Excellent. Three different sizes.The Bad:1 - When Cycling, the earbuds whistle so loud that they interfere with the sound.Maybe it's just me, but that's the problem I have with them. They are still useful to me for walking, just not cycling. I think the replaceable earpieces are what cause the whistling sound, so, I just thought I'd share this information for anyone interested. YMMV.
For what they are they sound good and I don't worry about loosing them or breaking them. Can't beat the sound to price ratio.
Love them. They go in and conform to my ear perfectly and last a very long time. I like them a lot. They are very soft.
I love the color, the perfect  fit to the ears and they are snazzy to look at. . Would highly recommend to all. Distinctive look.
summary: good quality . Very happy with them

reviewText: Sounds good, nice light weight cord. Fit in the ears just right. Great deal for the price.
I have had better ear buds, but I have also had worse. They slide out of my ears far too easy, but when in my ear, they give a quality sound.

I've been using this same model for several years; abused several pieces by using them when jogging; I still prefer this brand and can say this latest model is vastly improved from their previous ones. Great sound quality also.I highly recommend JBuds, as I'm a returning customer.
summary: Love the product - keep improving regularly

reviewText: They sound a bit strange, not bad by any means, flat? Could be that I just need to use them for a bit and get used to the response. I fiddle with the equalizer and probably straighten em out. They are VERY comfortable cant even feel them in really, for that they are the best I can remember. Well worth the price. Lets see how long they last. ;)
I like these ear buds, they sound very nice,comfortable and above all with the right size foam type insert they stay in your ears. I would buy these again and I do recommend them.

They sound pretty good ok I call myself purchasing some better than my sons ear buds he has skullcandy titan and I must say his does sound better but a while ago I purchase some sony ear buds and they sound better than both of these I did not purchase them again because a little expensive I should have Oh while good luck
The product arrived in a timely fashion. The sound was good for the price point, BUT, one ear bud has failed within a 4 month time frame. You get what you pay for.

I purchased a few of these and they all work great.  There are others that have better sound, but all of their cords are too short for my applications.  These have a little extra length on the cord, and the sound is pretty decent.  I bought many others and all of short cords, so I ended up getting a few more of these as backups.
summary: I like the longer cord length on this

reviewText: These Ear Buds only lasted me 3 weeks before they started having problems.STAY AWAY FROM THIS MODEL! That is all I have to say regarding these.

These sound terrible, and the noise reduction is minimal. Right now as I type here at the coffee shop, I took out the JBuds because I could hear the people talking next to me, and put in the Koss Plug headphones in my bag...the Plugs are WORLDS better...just sucks to have to squeeze them to put in ears, but now worth it, compared to the bad sound and noise reduction of the Jbuds.  If you love bass as I do, and full-sounding music, then stay far away from these. For about the same price, I'd recommend the Sony MDR-EX51LP Fontopia or the Koss Plug headphones...better bang for the buck in my opinion.
I had to change the ear bud pad to the smallest ones. Now it fits great and the sound is good.
summary: Works great better then what came with mp3 player

reviewText: I like the quality of sound from these Hi-Fi noise reducing ear buds.  They fit well and they sound great.
inexpensive but you get what you pay for. I just use them as an extra set for my iPad at work.

I had a couple higher priced versions of this product.  I like to listen to music or videos or presentations in the evening while keeping one eye on the kids while they play their video games (these are for my laptop pc)These work really well, AND the insulation does not peel off like it did from the overpriced SONY version of this product.GREAT!  I still have them and use them after a year. No problem
summary: Better than the high priced Sony version

reviewText: I have hard to fit ears - the Apple earphones pop right out and refuse to provide a good fit. These fit well, are sturdy, and provide good sound quality. I also bought a pair of similarly-priced, all white Coby earphones and these are better: the gray rubber earpieces are much more comfortable than the Cobys.High-end audiophiles look elsewhere, but for the casual user looking for a little sound isolation and maybe wearing these for listening in bed or on the bus, these are fine.
summary: Very nice buds for the price

reviewText: These earbuds are great for my daughter, who tends to go through them (losing them, falling asleep with them and wearing out the wires) too fast to justify buying a more expensive set. The sound quality and build quality is good for the price.
I needed a longer cord to hook up to my computer at work.  These give me plenty of room to move around.  Very comfortable too.

I've been listenig to my I-pod for a Couple of weeks now using these JBuds and the sound is really pretty decent.Not great but pretty good for the price. Lows are good mids and highs seem a Little dull.They are comfortable for extended periods of time.
summary: Good sounding earbuds for the price

reviewText: I use these with my Droid X and their OK. I guess I knew they weren't going to be Bose headphones, but the $10 headphones that I usually buy from Target sound WAY better than these.

reviewText: They sound good, they stay in my ears, they're comfortable. You could hardly go wrong with these. Just buy 'em and stick 'em in your ears.

I bought these for my daughter who thought she'd hate them based on the fact that they look different from the original buds that came with her iPod nano, but once she tried them she found they were comfortable and sounded very good!

Gave these to my son for Christmas.  He liked them, they seemed nice.  Well 2 weeks later the black ear piece on one separated in 2 at the seam.  They were not used hard or harmed in any way by us, they just broke apart.  Anyway I would just like a replacement for them and then I will just as easily re-review this item in a more positive way.

You can change the size to fit your ear!!  I think these buds are a fantastic product, especially for the price.  Would purchase again!

reviewText: Overall, a very good pair of earbuds, but for the price ($10) they are outstanding! I usually think earbuds with rubber tips feel strange in my ear after a few minutes, but with the different sized cups that come with the j-buds, you should be able to find the right fit. These buds definitely cancel some outside noise, I'd say I noticed about a 50% drop in ambient noise, which is fantastic for a bus or subway where you don't want to listen to the crazy homeless guy talk to himself but still need to hear the next stop announced. Pretty good sound fidelity, especially for dialogue (I was listening to a movie once and never had to put my ipod above 20% volume). Some may complain about the quality in music, but I found the base and higher notes on Jay-Z's new album sounded great to me.Overall a great value, and perfect for a set of earbuds while traveling.
summary: Does what it says, and saves you some $$$

reviewText: These produce great sound. Cheaper and nicer than my Sony's or Nike's.Ear pieces stay on unlike my Sony's.

They really work great. I use them in the pc's at the office listening to music and sometimes at home in different electronic devices. It would really be great if the case was somehow included with the earbuds, you know one price for the both. I wish the cord was a bit longer too.

PROS:-Affordable price-An easy find-Gets you by if you're going on vacation for a week-Well it's good at noise canceling, there's one thingCONS:-Sound quality is unfortunately weak; most of the songs have a muffled sound to them, which is a personal pet peeve of mine.-The cord is VERY cheap. It was starting to lose the rubber coating after a week.-Also, the rubber tips come off very easily. One time it got stuck in my ear.-Be warned, their replacement policy is a pain too. The second pair I got was just like the previous,Cons aside it's still not bad, but there are worthier buds out there, and I guess this was alright for its price.

reviewText: These are not the best ear buds. They won't create the sound you would get from sony's ear buds, but they work well. I use them all the time in my office but I have had better ones.
I would recommend buying more than one set. Finding they can be used on my computor and portable radio. Really enhances sound when  outside. Feels comfortable in ears. Strongly recommend.

The sound on these had plenty of bass but very muted mids and highs, so music sounded like it was underwater and phone calls required extra attention to comprehend.  It may have just been the pair I got, but I'm sending these ones back.Otherwise mic seems to work fine, button pauses and plays on iPhone, and they are comfortable.  The sound just sucks.

You get what you pay for here.  Price vs quality.  They sound flat, and the highs aren't crisp.  Will work for my main use at the gym. Most earbuds last a month or two so I go cheap.  These will do the job, but I will not get these again.

reviewText: This is a great pair of headphones.  sound quality and noise-reduction are perfect.  I can not believe for the price that this was a great deal.

Buy Sennheiser CX300-B Earbuds instead! Bass is terrible and noise reduction is not that great. Should be a lot cheaper since quality is inferior to competitors.

Looking for a good headset to use for your 3DS or PS Vita then this is a good choice as both comfort and audio quality are pretty good.  The headset buds fit snugly without feeling of them being loose and the audio sound is clear and sharp with no humming or crackling noises coming through.

reviewText: Hey, the price is great...  So I thought I would try them.The Sound is good... not great, but for the price... can't beat it.The earbuds are extremely comfortable.....much better than most.However, to prove the maxim you get what you pay for... these earbuds are poorly manufactured and not reliable.  After a month of very gentle use... the right side earbud just dies.  After checking the reviews, it is clear this is a common problem.  Spend a bit more for the durability (for me, I now prefer the Altec Lansing UHP336 Snugfit In-ear Earphone, better sound, comfortable and they are built to last).
summary: Good Comfort, Good Sound, Loses Sound On Right Side After One Month

reviewText: Plenty of other folks have mentioned these are great earbuds.The squidgy silicon caps are incredibly comfortable for most of us, but it is quite understandable that they simply don't work for others. Luckily, they're cheap enough (for most of us) that it is worthwhile to purchase a pair to check out the comfort and fit.But what I was especially pleased by was the packaging.Earbuds wear out--at least for me, they do. I sometimes put 'em in a pocket and that wears out the connection right next to the plug, so I'm happy if they last six months. I just purchased to inexpensive pairs of earbuds here, theseJBuds Hi-Fi Noise-Reducing Ear Buds (Black)and someSony MDR-ED21LP Fontopia In-The-Ear Headphones.The JBuds came in a small zip-lock bag with a single piece of folded paperboard packaging. (Their text: "JLab believes in being eco-friendly. This minimalistic packaging reduces waste.") Small enough that Amazon shipped it in a bubble-wrap envelope.The Sonys, in contrast, are in a hard blister pack--not quite as nasty as the impossible-to-cut plastic, but of the same ilk. The plastic is glued to paperboard backing, so the latter cannot be cleanly separated for recycling. Inside is more packaging paperboard and some inserts, as well as an astonishingly superfluous vinyl drawstring carrying case for the earbuds. I've already got two or three of those sitting in a drawer somewhere; I've never met anyone that takes off their earbuds and stows them in one of these things. I'd be quite interested to hear if anyone does--if you do, add a comment to my review. But I'm pretty sure that Sony is just being mindlessly wasteful, which isn't much of a surprise.But what really galled was that Sony's packaging was big enough that Amazon couldn't use a bubblepack envelope, and so shipped in a box, which was almost as big as a shoebox and mostly wasted space full of packaging material. Why Amazon couldn't combine the two packages I don't know, but Sony is still on the hook here for their sins.It helps that the JBuds are one-third cheaper than the Sonys, but both seem to change prices intermittently.So: if you're just grabbing a pair of work-a-day earbuds and all else turned out to be pretty much equal, go for the JBuds. The company is more sensible about their packaging and deserves the business.

Purchased these JBuds as a replacement for my son's Sansa Clip 2gb headphones. The Sansa's headphones had a great sound but one side died after a couple of weeks so I bought these as a replacement.  The Jbuds fit comfortably in his small ears (he's 13) and the sound is clear enough but it doesn't block external noise and there is almost no bass at all.  There are adapters for larger or smaller ears (it comes with 3 sets of soft plastic adapters.) The mini jack is at a right angle which makes it a nice fit on the Sansa Clip.  The wire is 5' long and splits to about 2' before you hit the stopper.I purchased a set of inexpensive Skull Candy ear buds and they are much better at blocking noise with outstanding bass performance and clarity.  I would not buy these JBuds again and do not recommend them.
summary: Not so great at noise reduction, no bass

reviewText: The item was OK for the price, however it does not work too well for reducing background noises.  It does come with three ear buds sizes to choose from in a little zip lock bag which was kind of nice.  As far as the item goes I'm pretty neutral, I would probably buy a different pair if I could do it over again.
These good quality ear buds allow me to listen to a movie on my iPad, without disturbing my wife, while we are watching a baseball game on TV.

I bought a pair of these for me and my wife. Hers is a backup pair to the ones she is using now while walking on the beach. I use mine while outdoors fishing, gun range and working in the garage on little projects. They are perfect for listening to music while doing these type of activities. I use them at the gun range to dampen the noise and they seem to work just as well as the foam ear plugs you would normally use. Its great to have an extra pair in the car or home just so you don't bother other people while playing with your gadgets. Yes I will order more set of these when the ones we have are lost or broken.

After reviewing in amazon several comments about ear buds, I was planning to buy Bose ear buds. Concerned about quality, sound, noise cancellation, I decided Bose is not the best option. JBuds were very cheaply made, cord came out of earpiece after the very first day. will never buy from JLAB again.

reviewText: Not the best money can buy, but great for the money. These are solidly made ear buds that take a lot of punishment. I listen to audiobooks with my buds, and these are perfect for that. I tend to catch my cords on drawer pulls and that's how I've destroyed many pairs. These are cheap, but hardy.

I immediately replaced the horrible ear buds that came with my new iPod.  I have been using these for several weeks and am very satisfied with them.  The sound quality is good and they are comfortable to wear. Given their price, I think these are a great value.

I bought 2 of them, the first one I took care of carefully and it still works great. The second one I gave to my younger brother, and he broke in 3 weeks. If you're very active and careless with them, they won't last long. If you are careful with how you store them, then they'll work just fine.

I know some audiophiles are freaks about their headphones and hating on earbuds, but there are many situations (running, walking, sitting on campus, riding the bus/train/plane, etc) where the only option is an earbud, and JLAB makes the best earbuds around. They make a few models higher than this one, for a few different price points, and each of their products is the highest quality at that price point. Decide how much you want to spend, and get the JLAB model in that range, and I guarantee you will be satisfied.The headphones you get from Apple to use on iPhone, iPod, and iPad are about a 2/5 based on quality of sound, comfort, and durability. These JLAD Jbuds are 5/5 all around, and the higher models from JLAB are just amazing.
summary: The best earbuds for the money, period.

reviewerName: Rodney A. Zemke "Retired.  Have been listenin...
reviewText: Pros:  Long cord, good sound, ear bud blocks external noise.Cons:  Even with 3 sizes, you have to push the bud back into your ear on occasion.
They sound better than the ipod ones, and you can get them for a pretty low price.Will edit if something goes wrong with them.

Back in 2007, when I bought these, I was looking for a better alternative to Apple's stock ear buds. I had used them for years, never venturing from the name brand, but after my second pair I realized I plain hated them. For some reason I was attached to the Apple name, but music was very important to me, and Apple's pricing was starting to get to me, so I was determined to find better ear buds at a fraction of the cost.At the time, these were the most popular. You can find better alternatives, but for the price these suited me just fine. I ordered these as well as some Sennheisers for home use, and my listening experience matured drastically.The quality was great and truly knocked out surrounding noises without those around you hearing what you're jamming to. The pads were okay, but certainly not the most comfortable for long periods.A few months later they were dead. They had cost me just over $6, and I used them nearly every day, so I can understand why they turned over. My second pair lasted about a year before giving in, and then I switched brands.Nothing wrong with these, just don't expect to have them for more than a year.
summary: Great for the price, but don't expect them to last long.

reviewText: great separation and tonal quality.  Also appreciate the extra soft buds included.  Loved the noice cancelling feature and good choice to replace my on-ear bulky headphone

Sound quality is mediocre, noise-reduction is laughable. That being said, I got them for 10$ (normal msrp is 49.95$) so I got what I paid for but had I paid full retail I would have returned them. Panasonic makes a set of ear buds similar to these for around 30$ that are a thousand times better and available at most electronics retailers, just get those.

These sound much better than my iPod earbuds, much better... However, the JBuds constantly fall out of my left ear when I run (no matter which size insert I use -- I guess I have a weird left ear). So basically, if they won't stay in my ears when I run, they are useless. Too bad there's not a way to test ear buds before buying. Back to my crappy old iPod earbuds -- at least they don't fall out every 30 seconds.

I had before purchased the more expensive version of Jbuds, and had seen some reviews that it wasnt really worth the extra price from these versions, so when it came time to replace I got these. MISTAKE! Most of the reviews basically said the sound quality was the same, (ok fine) but didnt talk about the size or fit difference between the two! I have VERY small ear canals, and the more expensive set comes with 4 sized caps. I used the smallest and they were perfect. This set only comes with 3 and the smallest one is too big for me. Luckily I had the smaller set of caps from my previous buds. Also, the base of the bud that the cap attaches to is too wide and large (for me), and can be painful if I try to push the bud any further in my ear. Now I realize this is probably not an issue for most people, but I wish I had known this before purchasing. It is worth the extra money for the more expensive set; not for the sound quality, but for the better fit capability. Also, the more expensive buds have a clip and this set does not. Not that big of a deal but a nice and convenient feature.
summary: Good basic headphones - less customized fit capability

reviewText: I ride a very noisy train everyday to work which lasts for one hour.  I use a Zune HD toprovide music to block it.  Initially I had Zune earbuds which sounded great but only lastsa few months with heavy daily use and weren't cheap.  I then tried Skullcandy earbuds and theyfilled the bill. They had great volume range and very solid reliability.  However, weren't greatat noise isolation w/o increased volume.  So I tried the JBuds and ran into the following issues.(1) I could not find an earpad which fit comfortably in my ear. (2) The volume sounded subduedas compared to my skullcandy's (3) Zero noise isolation since I could never get a comfortable fit.So, my search continues.
Very hard to change the cushion on buds!

I bought several pairs of these for family members for Christmas. They all loved them. I'm still hearing comments about how cool these are.Everyone who received them was thrilled with the sound quality. They were used with iPods and video games. I see reviews here grumbling about the sound quality, but I bought 4 pairs and they all worked exceptionally well.These are very comfortable. My 8 year old loves his nintendo DS noises that the rest of us hate. He usually won't wear earbuds because they hurt his ears. These were different though. They were so comfortable for him, he wears them without being asked. We love that because we don't have to listen to the dumb DS.My daughter also uses them to listen to videos and lessons on her computer. She says the sound quality is as good for voices and videos as it is for music.They fit well. I've heard no complaints about them staying in and I haven't seen any fall out. One family member uses hers while jogging.In summary, these are an awesome buy for the price. High sound quality and very comfortable with a secure fit.
There work good for me. Feels comfortable in my ears. Quality is good and the price is right. Buy it and you won't be sorry.
Good price but they really don't reduce any external noise anymore than most other ear buds would do.  Good quality sound.

reviewText: I will not claim that the sound quality is just as good as the apple earphones, but it certainly has its own merits. First, it blocks out much of the background noise and thus you can use it as a low volume for a very long time without getting tired buzzing eardrums. Second, it comes with 3 ear-bud covers that can be good for you in case you want a slightly different "depth". And finally, this is the best price you can think of for a quality earphone. You could easy pay $50$100 and get something very much the same.
Pretty good bass,pretty good noise cancelation,only complain is, i get the feeling like my ears are totally blocked when i have them on.pretty good in all aspects

reviewText: This Earbuds fit well in my ear but the sound quality is poor. If you are not expecting good bass and rich sound then this is good for the money. Beats what local stores sale for around the same price. I use these to run in. One thing that I really liked was the cord length! The sound quality is decent.The packaging was kind of odd. I know they wanted to save on the packaging, just was expecting better packaging. Also would of been nice if the ear pieces were a bit more stiffer. Other than these minimal things, its a great pair of ear buds for everyday use/exercising.
Most of these ear buds break after a few weeks. These lasted several months until someone took them. I would buy again if I could find them at the price of this set cost.
This is too good for the price...deep sound which fills your ears with wonderful music..I used and one and ordered one more for my wife..needs a couple od days burn in time

I use these with my netbook and sony media pda all the time.If I lose my pair I probably will not hesitate to buy from them again.

I'm giving these a "two" because of one feature: they fit in my ears better than most buds, and stay in during exercise better than most.I bought a pair of these a while back; they performed well enough. Not great, but I'd have given them a three, maybe even a four.I lost 'em.Now, I've bought three new pairs, as part of package deal with MP3 players (Sansas ... which we like a lot) and they're awful.The sound is simply muddy. Not exactly "bassy;" that would entail some degree of defined bass sound. No, these are simply muffled sounding. First off, I would like to congratulate JLab audio for realizing their goal of providing world-class customer care. I am certainly enticed to purchase further products from this company.In the beginning, I was just looking for a pair of cheap earbuds for on the go. Found this set, but after a few weeks of use, my pair was defective like many others and I forgot about it. A few months later, I was just browsing this page to see how frequently this occurs. Turns out, many people have this defect and have gotten replacements.So I decided to give it a try and send JLab audio an email. I was promptly replied with an automatic email within 10 minutes of sending. After less than 24 hours, I was given a reply. With no arguing or any of that annoying stuff, I got a replacement set.Time spent to get a replacement: <3 minutes (haha, if you get it)100/100 for the great price and customer support.Even better, the replacements come with a one year warranty :D
Worked good, airplane noise was still heard but was not to bad. Liked the color and fit. Would recommend to get.

Purchased my JBuds in 10/2009 from Amazon and by 2/2010 I was randomly losing sound on the right earbud due to a cable problem at the 3.5 mm connector jack. Only way I can get the sound to work is by bending the cable above the jack slightly in one direction, but once I release the cable the sound cuts out once more on the right side.  I'd consider my usage of these earbuds up to the point when this problem occurred to be frequent but with no abuse.  I've always disconnected the earbuds by holding and pulling out the jack...not by pulling on the speaker cable or the flexible rubber piece that joins the cable to the 3.5 mm jack.  To sum it up, I like the audio quality of the JBuds very much...but based on my experience the product doesn't appear to be durable.  Was considering whether to buy the JBuds J2 or J3 as a replacement, but I'm not sure if switching to a different JBud model would result in improved durability with the same or better audio quality.
summary: Sound great but the durability is not good at all

this product far surpasses my expectations, I like the sound this item produces, this is a grate product for the poriceagain i thank the maker of these ear buds.

HelloI just purchased these headphones, and I'm thankful that I have Amazon Prime. If I didn't have Amazon Prime, I'd be paying for shipping, and my purchase would be of even less value.These earbuds are relatively comfortable (just a bit more comfortable than standard iPhone earbuds). They are snug, they come with three sizes of inner-ear fitting cones, and they are light. They also look pretty nice.As for sound quality, these phones do not operate as advertised. The sound is reduced, flat, and "tinny", and there is no noise reduction to speak of. In fact, the stock earbuds that came with my iPod offer better sound.I learned the hard way that "Noise Reduction" and "Noise Cancellation" are totally different things. These phones claim th reduce noise by using a silicone ear-bud that "seals" in your ears, blocking outside noise.That simply is not true. No external noise is blocked, whatsoever.These were a waste of time. Maybe I'll give them to my 5-year-old nephew for his little tape deck.
summary: Noise Reducing IS NOT the same as Noise Canceling!!

I can hear my music clearly - much better than with the last buds I had, and they really do reduce outside noise. When I have both buds in my ears I am completely deaf to the outside world and I can only hear my music. What more can I say? They are great. Well worth the money.
Very comfortable,great price,long cord, love the pink Color, went perfect.with my case I bought with it. Both for twenty dollars cant beat it
The cord is very long: in a good way. The buds stay in the ear without falling out. The sound quality is a bit lacking. But for $5.99 these were a great and easy buy.

I work in a new era of cube farms with walls so low there really isn't any there and have to deal with some really noisy people that get rather annoying from time to time. I was pretty eager to get these and put them in to drown out their constant chatter that goes on for minutes at a time. I have to say I am pretty impressed with how well they work. While I can still hear the loudest of the offenders (I am not sure there is a headphone on the market for him) it does make it less annoying and I can enjoy my time at work.

I have now bought two sets of these earbuds (I lost the first set). These have an amazing sound for the price. I tried another pair of earbuds I had just to see if I could tell the difference, and there was no comparison. These blew my other ones away (not that the other ones where expensive at all). The difference to me was that these have a pretty good bass sound which I didn't expect for the price ($10 at the time of this writing). They are also very comfortable. I don't think you can go wrong with these considering the price.

reviewText: it was nice while it lasted, about a week.  then the little clicker that you press to pause and play music, broke off.  it wasn't pried off, and get caught on anything, i went to pause my music, clicked it, and out of the corner of my eye, i saw something hit the floor, it was the little black cover.  i was able to snap it back on, but it only stays there till you move it, then it falls off again.it did work great on my android phone though, it paused and played music, answered phone calls, and people could hear me fine, i liked it a lot, but then it broke.wouldn't recommend.
far, far superior to buds that come with things.  that said..........I hate having things in my ears, no matter how good they sound.  And yes, I'm over 30.  Way over.
summary: soft in ear, sounds really good

reviewText: One problem I have with ear buds is there tendency to fall off the end and get lost.  These do not fall off.  And they are very comfortable and provide great sound.
summary: these are very comfortable and the sound is great

reviewText: Music i listen to is far too psychotic for work, but i always need it, so i always wear these.Pros-comfortable, doesnt slip easily, good for hours of wearing, a little running too.-cord's long enough. some aren't.-LOUD. nearly blew my ears out, left something turned up. careful!-decent quality. i'm not missing anything in the music, and for the first time i can tell the difference between 128kbps mp3s and good ones. reripped my entire cd collection to variable bitrate.-They feel tough. I'll report back in a year to confirm.Cons-sound's a bit muddy on the high end, i goose up the 1khz-14khz range a few db and problem solved.-passive sound cancellation is not that hot compared to other budsThey're decent and do the job, but they leave me wanting more.UPDATE:I've had these for a few years and these are the worst-sounding earbuds i own, hands down, vs philips, skullcandy, koss, klipsch. They sound like dollar store headphones and the general construction is in line with that. If you want cheap headphones, skullcandy is better.
summary: OK but the sound is awful

reviewText: inexpensive and will do the job but the sound is lo-fi not hi-fi.  My Sony earbuds although slightly more expensive are noticeably better.  Good pair to have as a backup.

The jbuds are comfortable but the rubber pieces constantly fall off.  The wires are too long and get tangled.  The wiring frayed after only 2 months of use so now I can only get sound out of one earpiece.  I do NOT recommend this product.

I purchased these headphones because they were well reviewed and were what I was looking for.  The reviews, and the price tag, aided in their selection.  I liked that so much that I bought a second pair when I thought the first was lost.

The ear buds work great! I bought them awhile ago.  They are still working great!  Worth the money and I would buy them again.  Also, the color is cute if you like pink.  The sound quality is good and stays in my ears while running and in loud rooms it drowns out the sounds, so you can enjoy your music.

After reading reviews about JBuds, I finally decided to buy them for my Ipod.  It comes along with three sizes of earbuds to best fit your ears.  The sound quality is pretty good for the price and does well for most genres of music. The bass response could be better for hip-hop and electronic music. Overall, a good buy for the price.

Great on planes.  Don't expect it to completely drown out babies that sit right next to you, but it was very effective on my flight when a toddler threw a tantrum a few rows away.  With a little speed metal on medium volume, I couldn't hear the little bugger at all.

I bought this product without knowing other in-ear earphones in the "world(?)". When I bought this product, I was getting more into JLab products.Anyway, the sound quality is great enough for me. I usually use it with my iPod I bought last year! The cord length is longer than Apple's cord length.Cord... I don't know what happened, but it "broke" within few weeks. When I asked for warranty replacement, they just asked for the proof of purchase through E-Mail. The procedure was simpler than I thought: Just forward the "Confirmation" E-Mail you received from Amazon for the proof of purchase. I just wait few days, and then the package came.For some reason, "Upgraded version" came as a replacement. I was very happy about that!Overall, I'm satisfied with this product. I ordered "upgraded version" of this product because of its service and "usefulness".
summary: Great Product with Great Warranty Replacement!

reviewText: I was looking for something that fit my ears and wouldn't fall out when I moved around. These fit the bill. I have a small ear canal so the junk that comes with mp3 players just doesn't work. These have good quality sound and are not irritating to your ears like the foam buds. They are NOT noise cancelling, they are noise reducing so you can still hear if someone tries to talk to you or the phone rings. No complaints.
these work ok, too much base and noise reduction not to good. I would not buy these again. pay a lil more and get the quality.

This is my second set of Jbuds and I really like them. I use these primarily with my Nook HD, so ear buds are almost mandatory, since the Nook produces what has got to be the crappiest audio from a built in speaker of any device I've ever heard. I've tried a few other brands of ear buds, but none of them seem to have any where near the depth of sound that these do. I do sort of wish these were available with a 90 connector, since I damaged the cord on my first pair right at the straight mini plug connection, but even so, if it happens again I will definitely be buying another pair of these Jbuds.
summary: JLab JBuds Hi-Fi Noise-Reducing Ear Buds (Black)

reviewText: Finally ear buds that will stay in my ears when I hike. Plenty of choices when it comes to tips. I did the 48 hour break-in and they sound phenomenal. I bought a second pair for my wife.

THE PRODUCT CAME WITH TWO DIFFERENT EAR BUD REPLACEMENTS. NICE IDEA. I LIKE THE BUDS THAT ARE PICTURED HERE, THEY FIT GOOD AND ARE COMFORTABLE AFTER LONG USE.QUALITY SOUNDING. EXCELLENT NAME. YOU C AN'T GO WRONG ON THIS PRODUCT,
summary: FOR A COMFORTABLE AND ENJOYABLE EXPERIENCE IN SOUND.

reviewText: can't beat these for the price.  they sound good and are very comfortable.  my only complaint is that the wire size is small (thin & fragile).

Not the best I've had when it comes to sound and blocking outside noise, but still pretty good for their price, though after a while my ears start to hurt, even with the smallest earbud pieces.Havn't tried to work out with them in yet, but I'm still pretty active and so far I havn't had any problems with them falling out
These buds are just ok. They're basically worth the $6 we paid for them. In other words, not worth returning them but will work if in a bind.

pretty good for the price. they aren't going to blow your mind but if you want better earphones, spend more money. if you aren't looking to spend a ton of money and want decent sound, get em. pretty simple.
I got this in a deal for around 10 bucks... no doubt that this is a very gud value for money ... no cons till now

I bought a set of these last year and was quite happy with them. I am not that big on gadgets and music, so spending more than $10 on earphones was just not going to happen. The earphones fit well, with three pairs of adjustable pads to choose from to insert in your ears. Sound is good, and noise is considerably reduced, even on planes, which was my main reason for buying them. They do not reduce noise as much as higher cost earphones (I tested them against a pair from Sennheiser) nor do they reproduce sound as faithfully, but for my purposes, the difference was not worth the extra expense. Those who are more demanding on sound quality or noise cancellation may want to try one of the higher end JLab models.About two weeks ago the left channel gave out. When I emailed JLab Audio about it, they had me check the earphones on a couple of different pieces of equipment and run a track test on them (which is only fair). When this confirmed there was something wrong with the earphones, they immediately mailed out a replacement, which arrived within a week of my first email to them. If that were not enough, the replacement also carries a one year warranty! All for ten bucks.Although I was content with the earphones before, now I am a fan for good. It is just not that easy to find such outstanding customer service. Even if I were to upgrade, I would pick another JLab product and have the confidence that the company will stand behind it.
summary: Can't beat it for the price + AWESOME customer service

reviewText: I have used these for several months and they have a good overall sound, especially for the inexpensive price paid......
Ear bids work great! Sound quality and comfortable level are good as well. Been using it over 7 months and still working like brand new since the days I got it, overall great ear buds

Prior to this one, I'd been using a $7 earbud. Prior to that, I was using the given Apple ipod earbuds (which I didn't like b/c it didn't fit well).  I haven't seen a major difference with the JBuds, other than the boost in the bass; however, it seems to come at the expense of the higher freq. sounds, which isn't good for the type of music I listen to.  Since I didn't pay that much for the JBuds, I really don't mind; however, it seems that the difference in earbuds on the lower end (<$50) don't seem worth paying more if you can avoid it.  That said, I've tried the expensive ones at stores and they don't seem to make a great difference either!
cheap muffled sound really even with consideration to price it is not usableorder 6 different brands of "inexpensive" ear-buds. this came last

For the price, these are good headphones. The sound quality is decent and definitely not bad to listen to music through. These things have lasted years for me and have drowned out the endless droning of many, MANY coworkers.

What can I say, this is your basic set of earbuds. They don't do anything spectacular and they don't suck in any way.I say 5 stars because they are exactly what I wanted at exactly the price point I was happy to pay. If I could actually remember to bring them with me when I need them, that would be really awesome.

I have been just buying the regular ear buds that you can get any where and I was told about these. I bought 3 of them and all of us really like them especially when everyone wants to hear their own stuff in a moving car. We are all enjoying them. I would not buy any more ear buds but these.
summary: The buds are wonderful to use.

reviewText: I can hear the music fine, they stay in my ear and are comfortable plus the price was real right. Quick delivery.

For ten bucks you can't go wrong with this comfortable pair of ear buds. I bought mine to use mostly with a small Sony radio that I listen to every night before falling asleep. I've gone through countless pairs of earphones that lasted from a month to a year before being replaced. Most sets of ear buds I've used before have been uncomfortable but produced acceptable sound.The Jbuds are the most comfortable set I've worn to date. They fit my ears perfectly and fit deeply enough into the ear canal to stay put. Included with the buds are two additonal sets of rubber tips of different sizes for those who desire them.What about sound? I am by no means an audiophile so for my needs these earphones far exceed any requirements I may have.Just to test them out I hooked up the Jbuds into the Bose speakers hooked up to my computer. The sound reproduction is terrific and is as good or better than the sound from my Maxell headphones. Using the Jbuds I've noticed subtle background instrumentation that I hadn't detected before.No, these aren't state of the art sound reproducers, but for someone with modest needs and expectations the jbuds are a good choice.Durability - I use these buds every night. Sometimes they fall on the floor, or get tangled in knots, or get lost in the blankets, or even get pawed by Evie the bichon who tries to move them out of her way. They've lasted several months now unscathed and still sound as good as ever.One more thing - The directions in the little booklet that comes with the buds says that they need to be broken in, perhaps played continuously for a day.  Being a skeptic, I didn't believe that for a second. Yet, over time the sound through these buds does seem to have improved. The first time I tried them, the musical instruments sounded clear and crisp but the vocals sounded muted and distant. Now all is fine. Explaining or understanding such things is beyond this Potato Head.

I wore these at the gym - big mistake.  They kept popping out due to sweating, so I kept putting them back in, pushing sweat deeper into my ears.  I'm convinced that these things gave me an ear infection, which ultimately led to a plugged ear, ear drops, and a trip to the ENT.The sound quality is ok but not as good as the iPod headphones, IMO.  They are too heavy on the bass.  The noise reduction works ok, but your own breathing, coughing, humming, etc., reverberates loudly, also making them not good for wearing while exercising.So, if you're only using these at work or on the plane or while sitting quietly, maybe they're ok.  Do not use them while exercising, as you may end up with an ear infection.

I kept losing the covers off my old earbuds.  So I ordered a couple new pairs; not knowing which ones would sound good.  These were awful!  They were much worse than my old ones, as well as the other Skullcandy buds that I bought at the same time.  The JBuds were muffled and dull in sound.  Maybe I got a bum set, but I threw them out.
summary: The set I got weren't good

reviewText: I purchased these as a special and am quite pleased so far. I needed an inexpensive pair of headphones as I was not satisfied with my Apple earbuds as the sound was tinny and they were not comfortable in my ear. These J Buds are exceptionally comfortable and provide superior sound. The cord does not seem to get twisted up like the Apple ones did and the bass is much better, though not as good as my over the head large headphones. I have listened to several different ear buds and I must say these are hands down the best for the money. It stated in the instructions that these headphones will actually break in and will sound better after they have been used for a few days. Either way, I am really happy with the sound now and would recommend these highly.

These ear buds are cheap (at the $10 Amazon price I paid for them), so they won't hurt the wallet, but they don't handle bass very well. The iPod's EQ set to "bass booster" caused them to crackle and pop with the volume only turned up a quarter. On other settings the sound was a little flat, but otherwise ok.For the $10 I paid they are good purchase and a decent pair of spare, throw-away ear buds. I'll keep them in my car or bag as a spare set. I wouldn't pay any more than that though. I certainly wouldn't pay the $50 list price for them.

Just what I needed and the price was right. It also came with an extra set of ear covers; regular size and a small size. They is also included a 1 year warranty and a 20 free songs download. Haven't used them yet as they just arrived but am sure they will be great.

I purchased two pairs, one for work and one for home.  The pair I purchased for work are fine, but the pair for home is down to left earbud because right earbud has a short in it.  I should have read the 1 star reviews before purchasing, but I'm at least partially satisfied as my other pair don't seem to have the same issue.Interesting how it's always the right earbud.  You would think JLabs would correct the shorting issue by now.  FYI, my right earbud shorted out within the first week!
summary: I purchased 2 pairs and 1 already has a short

reviewText: They work great, sound great.  The headphones came with different sized ear pads so I was able to find the exact fit for my ear.  Cheap price.  Thanks Amazon.

bought these because of the low price and great reviews - but these do NOT stay in my ears no matter what. I have tried all 3 sizes, looped the cord around the top of my ear, etc.... - actually - I have never owned any buds that fell out so much. Even the cheap ones Apple includes with their products.Waste of money for me - but if you can get them to stay in - they sound pretty good for the price.
these headphones are the best I have ever had. they work great wth my ipod and have amazing sound!!!! They look great sound great and the price was right!

I ordered these headphones simple because of the longer cord.  I listen to podcasts from my computer while working.  How many times have I gotten up from my desk only to be jerked back down towards the laptop?  Too many times.  This cord is over one yard.  I love it.  They are also much more comfortable than my other earbuds that came from my ipod.  I am so glad I made this purchase.  The sound quality is quite good, they are comfortable, and best of all finally a longer a cord!
These ear pieces are very good.  They are the right shape for my ears, and they carry along a quality sound.

I bought these to replace the headphones that my iphone came with.  I spend 2.5 hours on the NYC subway every day and needed something to isolate the noise so I don't damage my hearing.  These headphones did the trick!  They block out enough ambient noise so I can keep the volume low, but they still let me hear announcements.  Sound quality is better than on the apple headphones.My only complaints are that they don't come with a microphone/button like the iphone headphones and the plug needs to filed down so it fits into the iphone jack.At $15 these are a steal!  Comparable headphones cost around $100.

Received from Amazon quickly - excellent 2-day shipping. Not sure if I have big ear canals, but these ear buds would not stay in while doing just moderate exercise. In addition, the sound quality was not as good as the earbuds that came with my ipod.

reviewText: THESE ARE COMFORTABLE AND THE SOUND IS GOOD THOUGH THE BASS IS NOT AS STRONG AS APPLE'S ARE. THAT IS TO BE EXPECTED AS THEY ARE NOT BIG LIKE APPLE'S AND THAT MAKES THEM MORE COMFORTABLE.

I have bought 5 pairs of these over the last 6 months, I am still using my first pair, but everytime I let someone listen to them I lose my spare and have to get more. They are comfortably enough to wear for a 12 hour shift at work and they sound great even in a loud plant, and best of all the won't break the bank. Highly recommend to anyone looking for a nice pair of earbuds at a good price.

I screwed up buying these; they sound fine considering the price, but I was hoping for better. I wish there was some way to listen to them before buying them (at home I listen through my home system so I believe I could tell the difference between simulated high and low quality)
summary: I was hoping for better sound quality

reviewText: I bought these headphones to replace my Sony MDR-EX51LP Fontopia Headphones.  I like these better for one two reasons1) completely superficial reason - it matches my black ipod2) completely non superficial reason - it's better for my hearingI typcially keep the sound on my ipod locked at 75% to minimize damage to my ears.  With these JBuds I don't have to take that precaution, because I never have to raise the volume up that high.  And I listen to my ipod chiefly going back and forth on the subway in D.C., where it can be pretty difficult to block out the sound of the train. I'm really glad I bought them.Two words of caution, however.  First, I don't think the sound is as good as it was with the Sony headphones.  I listen mostly to podcasts and audiobooks, though, so it doesn't affect me much.  Also, I'm not an audiophile so my standards aren't that high.  Secondly, I've gone through 3 pairs of these types of headphones due to the rubber tips falling off.  While I prefer these type of headphones to other in-ear phones (I've got small ears, and other types hurt), this is getting pretty aggravating.  So electronic companies?  Work on that.

I got these earphones when they are on sale at $10.Previously i owned a Sony EX088 ($12) and i love them until they broke after 3-4 months afer i got em =.=''...  So when i found these earbuds since they were cheap, i told myself "gezz it must be great earbuds they were $50 and now i'm getin them for just $10!"Turns out they were what i paid for , it didn't give me that $50 feeling that i was expecting... one possible mistake was not paying attention when i bought them, it wasn't "noise canceling" earbuds "noise reducing"... but still im disappointed..I'll say if you are looking for ok pair of earbuds they're great. But if you are a music psyco, plz just pay a few more dollars for better earbuds i regreated not paying a few more dollars for some sony or brookstone earbuds... Sony stuff break so easily but they just have better great quality than other random brands.:D

I'm amazed at all the rave reviews, considering that my pair of JBuds sound as if they were surround by cotton balls.  Supposedly they get better after the break-in period, but I've waited through at least 12 hours of play, and they haven't opened up yet.  I'll come back and revise this review if they do.  But I doubt I'll listen to them much longer.They're inexpensive, and they're kind of pretty, but don't expect these buds to blossom.

I use these plugged into my Dual Shock 4 for game audio and VoIP chat. My Apple Earpods created an annoying buzz that made my friends not want to chat with me, but these are crystal clear. Great price, decent sound, and the mic works. Can't ask for much more.

Ah....to keep this short and sweet:Perfect for tall people - cord is long enough to where you can keep your MP3 player in your pocketBass is above average....Voices are clear. I have listened to Lil Boosie and Stevie Wonder and could easily understand both of them.Earphones are COMFORTABLE. More comfortable then the ones that come with a zune (which to me are very good). They just sit in my ear with little reminding that they are there.Price is laughable. Only 20 dollars? Come on....charge more! I would have paid for it.This is a very good earphone for the price. I fully support these. The only complaint would be it really doesn't cancel noise that well but it sure does muffle the noise around you. I can't wait to finally get around to hitting the gym with this.

reviewText: I bought these along with the Coby CVE92 Isolation Stereo Earphones a few months ago. Well the Coby ones sucked lasting only a month and the sound was not as good as the Jbuds. The Jbuds weren't perfect but they were noticeably better than the Coby. Also they are quite comfortable and came with extra buds of varying sizes which was great.Unfortunately these Jbuds only lasted about 3 months. Sadly I have come to expect this as I have never owned a pair of headphones/earbuds that lasted more than a few months. Since I only buy inexpensive headphones (under $20) I once took a chance and bought expensive Panasonic Stereo headphones. Those did not fare any better.What I find quite disturbing however is that virtually everyone who has owned these for three months or so, seem to experience the exact same problem almost at the exact same time.Verdict: As I said before, I have never owned a set of headphone that lasted a year (or even close to one) even though I am usually quite careful with my stuff. That being the case, for $10 this is a relatively good purchase.
I have purchased this brand 3 times because I need the microphone. They are cheap and don't last more than six months. You might just spend the money and get a better pair that lasts  longer

At first I thought these would be like those plain generic headphones that they look like, or like skull candy. I'm SO glad I picked these headphones since they are so comfortable and incredible with their audio quality as well! I love them for the price!
definitely worth getting.. sound is great.  I have had several types of ear buds but these are comfortable and great price and sound is perfect...

I use these with my iphone and my kindle. They have great sound and works well when answering a call while on my iphone.

This product is very comfortable, you can wear them all day, Amazon's price is terrific on them.  One *huge* caution, though:  they are NOT compatible with the iPhone!!!  I purchased them for use with my iPhone and assumed that iPod compatible meant iPhone compatible -- it DOES NOT!!

reviewText: Oh - My - God!These things are amazing!I am getting another set soon.The sound is fabulous, and the "Noise-Reducing" factor works great.I had Koss before, I just didn't want to spend this much this time around so I thought I was going to give these a shot. Perfect.  Sometimes I don't want to share what I am listening to,  when using my MacBook Air laptop.  I like these earbuds a lot.They are super comfy and I chose a bright color, so that I can find them easily, amongst my tangled battery cords, USB cablesand all of that mess in my laptop pocket.My only suggestion to the manufacturers would be that they put some kind of small nib on the buds or cord, so that itwould be easy to know left from right----in the dark.

reviewText: Come with 2 sets of foam feeds.  Sound very good and makes my walks a lot easier.  I like them.

For $17, these are a solid, but middling performer.  The sound is kinda flat and muddy (insufficient high frequency, which diminishes intelligibility for voice podcasts -- my primary use).  This style provides some passive reduction of external noise because the soft silicone adapters fit inside the ear entrance.  But as soon as the price drops on the Apple M9394G in-ear headphones (similar design, but much brighter and clearer sound) back into the reasonable range (below $30), I'll buy another set of those (the dog ate my previous pair!) These JBuds' flat response might sound OK to some ears for music, but not for voice ranges or high frequency response.
summary: You Get What You Pay For - Flat & Muddy Sound

reviewText: really dose what it says it will do noise reducing awesome product fits my phone too. I get a crisp sound with it

These are comfortable to wear, and have excellent sound. Well worth getting.Word of note, they work so well that you might have to turn down the volume.

I like that the cord from the earphones and plug is a long distance and the sound is full and fantastic.  It does a good job clearing the outside noise; however, since the bass is full, the volume doesn't go as high as some might like.

reviewText: these are actually my back up headphonesthey're horrible to run in because, well, they're ear buds even though you do shove them in your ear. comes in three sizes to choose for your ear.sound quality is great. have yet still to find something as good for the price
These were a one-time super buy at $6 or $7!  I listened to them and compared them with my so-in-law's $79 JLab buds and you couldn't tell the difference.
Super good and cheap price. Retail is about 12-20 bucks. Makes me mad to see how much retail markup is...hrumph.

I'm not one of those people who can tell the difference between good sounding earbuds and those over $[...].These fit my ears perfectly and that was number one choice. The standard earbuds from Apple are crap, fall out all the time. These sound good to me and they fit perfectly and do not fall out.Price was right, delivered in 2 days using free delivery.
They seem to work well under harsh conditions, but it has only been 2 weeks. The price was a deal as well!

I didn't really buy these for the noise reduction. I have extremely sensitive ears, and I've never had headphones that could cut out background noise. Certainly not a set for under $20 like these. And who can afford those BOISE ones they show on TV?My sister was trying to get my attention just now. I had my laptop turned down to 2. She's sitting 8 feet away, and she had to throw something at me to get my attention.Let's just say...I love these.6/2011I've almost had these for 3 years now, and they are still the best ear buds that I've ever had. A friend gave me some fancy Skull Candy ear buds, and I still like the jbuds better. After so long though, I am thinking about buying a new set. Not because the old ones are worn out, but just in case something goes wrong. 3 years is a LONG time to be using the same set.
summary: Three Years Later and I still love them.

reviewText: I had the need to buy a cheap set for my new acquired Nexus 7 (2nd gen), after reading the reviews, I made the decision to buy this set - I saw most of the 1 stars are around durability, since I am not a heavy user, so I didn't really worry about it, plus it was only $8.When the package arrived, the first impression was not that good, it appeared to be cheaply made. But the worst part is the sound: the mid-range is so muddy; and high end totally lacks clarity; the base is okay, but still far from adequate.I am very disappointed. It's too cheap to return so I will probably just throw it in the drawer.Don't buy it unless you just want to hear some "sound".

For the price you can't beat these.  The sound quality is a step up from iPod earphones and the comfort is 1 million steps up.  I wear these all day at work with little to no discomfort, whereas iPod earphones hurt my ears after 20 minutes of use.  The difference is night and day.  I like that these are cheap, so I keep a pair at work, a pair in the gym, and a pair in my jacket.  I don't have to worry about being careful with these because they seem durable and even if they break it's no big deal.  It turns out that none of mine have broken and they all continue to work well.  For some background, at home I use high fidelity sound equipment, but for on-the-go sound I don't think getting top quality is worth the money since you typically won't be in a setting where you can appreciate it.  For example, if you're jogging there will be noise from cars and/or noise caused by the wind from your movement to drown out any sound details a hi-fi pair would offer.  Go with these for on-the-go use and you won't be disappointed.

reviewerName: The Old Chevro-let Set "But ain't we got love"
reviewText: Sound is muffled.
